41static inline int
42__iop_field_find_by_name2(const iop_struct_t *desc, const lstr_t name)
43{
44 const iop_field_t *field = desc->fields;
45
46 for (int i = 0; i < desc->fields_len; i++) {
47 if (lstr_equal(field->name, name)) {
48 return i;
49 }
50 field++;
51 }
52 return -1;
53}
54
55static inline const iop_field_t *
56__iop_field_find_by_name(const iop_struct_t *desc, const lstr_t name)
57{
58 int pos = RETHROW_NP(__iop_field_find_by_name2(desc, name));
59
60 return &desc->fields[pos];
61}
62
63int iop_field_find_by_name(const iop_struct_t *st, const lstr_t name,
64 const iop_struct_t **found_st,
65 const iop_field_t **found_fdesc)
66{
67 int acc = 0;
68 bool is_class = iop_struct_is_class(st);
69
70 do {
71 int pos = __iop_field_find_by_name2(st, name);
72
73 if (pos >= 0) {
74 if (found_st) {
75 *found_st = st;
76 }
77 if (found_fdesc) {
78 *found_fdesc = st->fields + pos;
79 }
80 return acc + pos;
81 }
82 acc += st->fields_len;
83 } while (is_class && (st = st->class_attrs->parent));
84
85 return -1;
86}
87
88/** Result parameters of a field parse. */
89typedef struct iop_field_path_parse_t {
90 pstream_t field_name;
91 opt_i32_t array_index;
92 bool wildcard;
93 const iop_struct_t *nullable cast_st;
94} iop_field_path_parse_t;
95
96/** Parses a field with syntax described for \ref mp_iop_field_path_compile.
97 */
98static int parse_field_from_path(pstream_t *field_path_ps,
99 const iop_struct_t *st,
100 iop_field_path_parse_t *field_parse,
101 sb_t *nullable err)
102{
103 pstream_t field_ps;
104
105 p_clear(field_parse, 1);
106
107 if (ps_skipc(field_path_ps, '<') >= 0) {
108 pstream_t cast_ps;
109
110 if (ps_get_ps_chr_and_skip(field_path_ps, '>', &cast_ps) < 0) {
111 if (err) {
112 sb_sets(err, "unable to find ending of explicit cast");
113 }
114 return -1;
115 }
116
117 if (!iop_struct_is_class(st)) {
118 if (err) {
119 sb_setf(err, "explicit cast `%*pM' can not be used on type "
120 "`%*pM` which is not a class", PS_FMT_ARG(&cast_ps),
121 LSTR_FMT_ARG(st->fullname));
122 }
123 return -1;
124 }
125
126 field_parse->cast_st = iop_get_class_by_fullname(
127 st, LSTR_PS_V(&cast_ps));
128 if (!field_parse->cast_st ||
129 !iop_class_is_a(field_parse->cast_st, st))
130 {
131 if (err) {
132 sb_setf(err, "cannot find sub-class `%*pM' of class `%*pM`",
133 PS_FMT_ARG(&cast_ps), LSTR_FMT_ARG(st->fullname));
134 }
135 return -1;
136 }
137 }
138
139 if (ps_get_ps_chr_and_skip(field_path_ps, '.', &field_ps) < 0) {
140 /* We reached the end of the path: this field is the last field. */
141 field_ps = *field_path_ps;
142 __ps_skip_upto(field_path_ps, ps_end(field_path_ps));
143 }
144
145 if (ps_get_ps_chr_and_skip(&field_ps, '[', &field_parse->field_name) >= 0)
146 {
147 errno = 0;
148 if (ps_skipc(&field_ps, '*') >= 0) {
149 field_parse->wildcard = true;
150 } else {
151 field_parse->array_index = (opt_i32_t)OPT(ps_geti(&field_ps));
152 }
153 if (errno || ps_skipc(&field_ps, ']') < 0 || !ps_done(&field_ps)) {
154 if (err) {
155 sb_setf(err, "cannot read index for field `%*pM': "
156 "syntax error", PS_FMT_ARG(&field_parse->field_name));
157 }
158
159 return -1;
160 }
161 } else {
162 field_parse->field_name = field_ps;
163 }
164
165 if (ps_done(&field_parse->field_name)) {
166 if (err) {
167 sb_sets(err, "empty field name");
168 }
169 return -1;
170 }
171
172 return 0;
173}
174
175const iop_field_t *
176iop_get_field_const(const void *ptr, const iop_struct_t *st, lstr_t path,
177 const void ** nullable out_ptr,
178 const iop_struct_t ** nullable out_st)
179{
180 pstream_t ps = ps_initlstr(&path);
181 const iop_field_t *iop_field = NULL;
182
183 while (!ps_done(&ps)) {
184 iop_field_path_parse_t field_parse;
185
186 RETHROW_P(ptr);
187 RETHROW_NP(parse_field_from_path(&ps, st, &field_parse, NULL));
188
189 if (iop_struct_is_class(st)) {
190 st = *(const iop_struct_t **)ptr;
191
192 /* Throw an error if the type of the object is not a sub-class of
193 * the explicit cast class. */
194 THROW_NULL_IF(field_parse.cast_st &&
195 !iop_class_is_a(st, field_parse.cast_st));
196 }
197
198 RETHROW_NP(iop_field_find_by_name(st,
199 LSTR_PS_V(&field_parse.field_name),
200 out_st, &iop_field));
201 if (st->is_union && *(int16_t *)ptr != iop_field->tag) {
202 return NULL;
203 }
204 ptr = (const byte *)ptr + iop_field->data_offs;
205
206 if (OPT_ISSET(field_parse.array_index)) {
207 int array_index = OPT_VAL(field_parse.array_index);
208 const IOP_ARRAY_OF(byte) *array_ptr = ptr;
209
210 THROW_NULL_IF(iop_field->repeat != IOP_R_REPEATED);
211 if (array_index < 0) {
212 /* Negative index means we read the array backward. */
213 array_index = array_ptr->len + array_index;
214 THROW_NULL_IF(array_index < 0);
215 }
216
217 THROW_NULL_IF(array_index >= array_ptr->len);
218 ptr = array_ptr->tab + iop_field->size * array_index;
219 } else
220 if (iop_field->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
221 THROW_NULL_IF(!ps_done(&ps));
222 }
223
224 switch (iop_field->type) {
225 case IOP_T_UNION:
226 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
227 if (!ps_done(&ps) && iop_field_is_pointed(iop_field)) {
228 ptr = *(const void **)ptr;
229 }
230 st = iop_field->u1.st_desc;
231 break;
232 default:
233 THROW_NULL_IF(!ps_done(&ps));
234 break;
235 }
236 }
237 if (out_ptr) {
238 *out_ptr = ptr;
239 }
240 return iop_field;
241}
242
243iop_value_field_t iop_value_field_from_type(iop_type_t type)
244{
245 switch (type) {
246 case IOP_T_I8:
247 case IOP_T_I16:
248 case IOP_T_I32:
249 case IOP_T_I64:
250 case IOP_T_ENUM:
251 return IOP_VALUE_I;
252
253 case IOP_T_U8:
254 case IOP_T_U16:
255 case IOP_T_U32:
256 case IOP_T_U64:
257 case IOP_T_BOOL:
258 return IOP_VALUE_U;
259
260 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
261 return IOP_VALUE_D;
262
263 case IOP_T_STRING:
264 case IOP_T_XML:
265 case IOP_T_DATA:
266 return IOP_VALUE_S;
267
268 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
269 case IOP_T_UNION:
270 return IOP_VALUE_PTR;
271
272 case IOP_T_VOID:
273 return IOP_VALUE_NONE;
274 }
275
276 assert(false && "unexpected");
277 return IOP_VALUE_NONE;
278}
279
280iop_value_from_field_res_t
281iop_value_from_field(const void *ptr, const iop_field_t *field,
282 iop_value_t *value)
283{
284 THROW_ERR_IF(field->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED);
285
286 ptr = (byte *)ptr + field->data_offs;
287
288#define GET_SCALAR(type, opt, f) \
289 if (field->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) { \
290 const opt *o = ptr; \
291 \
292 if (OPT_ISSET(*o)) { \
293 value->f = OPT_VAL(*o); \
294 } else { \
295 return IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET; \
296 } \
297 } else { \
298 value->f = *(const type *)ptr; \
299 }
300
301 switch (field->type) {
302 case IOP_T_I8:
303 GET_SCALAR(int8_t, opt_i8_t, i);
304 return 0;
305
306 case IOP_T_U8:
307 GET_SCALAR(uint8_t, opt_u8_t, u);
308 return 0;
309
310 case IOP_T_I16:
311 GET_SCALAR(int16_t, opt_i16_t, i);
312 return 0;
313
314 case IOP_T_U16:
315 GET_SCALAR(uint16_t, opt_u16_t, u);
316 return 0;
317
318 case IOP_T_ENUM:
319 case IOP_T_I32:
320 GET_SCALAR(int32_t, opt_i32_t, i);
321 return 0;
322
323 case IOP_T_U32:
324 GET_SCALAR(uint32_t, opt_u32_t, u);
325 return 0;
326
327 case IOP_T_I64:
328 GET_SCALAR(int64_t, opt_i64_t, i);
329 return 0;
330
331 case IOP_T_U64:
332 GET_SCALAR(uint64_t, opt_u64_t, u);
333 return 0;
334
335 case IOP_T_BOOL:
336 GET_SCALAR(bool, opt_bool_t, u);
337 return 0;
338
339 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
340 GET_SCALAR(double, opt_double_t, d);
341 return 0;
342
343#undef GET_SCALAR
344
345 case IOP_T_STRING:
346 case IOP_T_XML:
347 case IOP_T_DATA: {
348 const lstr_t *str = ptr;
349
350 if (field->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL && !str->s) {
351 return IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET;
352 } else {
353 value->s = lstr_dupc(*str);
354 }
355 return 0;
356 }
357 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
358 case IOP_T_UNION: {
359 if (iop_field_is_pointed(field)) {
360 ptr = *(const void **)ptr;
361 }
362
363 if (!ptr) {
364 return IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET;
365 }
366 value->p = (void *)ptr;
367 return 0;
368 }
369 case IOP_T_VOID:
370 /* FIXME Should be considered as not set only if optional *and* not
371 * set. */
372 return IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET;
373 }
374 return IOP_FIELD_ERROR;
375}
376
377static void iop_value_to_ptr(void *ptr, const iop_field_t *field,
378 const iop_value_t *value)
379{
380#define SET_SCALAR(type, opt, f) \
381 if (field->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) { \
382 opt *o = ptr; \
383 \
384 OPT_SET(*o, value->f); \
385 } else { \
386 *(type *)ptr = value->f; \
387 }
388
389 switch (field->type) {
390 case IOP_T_I8:
391 SET_SCALAR(int8_t, opt_i8_t, i);
392 break;
393
394 case IOP_T_U8:
395 SET_SCALAR(uint8_t, opt_u8_t, u);
396 break;
397
398 case IOP_T_I16:
399 SET_SCALAR(int16_t, opt_i16_t, i);
400 break;
401
402 case IOP_T_U16:
403 SET_SCALAR(uint16_t, opt_u16_t, u);
404 break;
405
406 case IOP_T_ENUM:
407 case IOP_T_I32:
408 SET_SCALAR(int32_t, opt_i32_t, i);
409 break;
410
411 case IOP_T_U32:
412 SET_SCALAR(uint32_t, opt_u32_t, u);
413 break;
414
415 case IOP_T_I64:
416 SET_SCALAR(int64_t, opt_i64_t, i);
417 break;
418
419 case IOP_T_U64:
420 SET_SCALAR(uint64_t, opt_u64_t, u);
421 break;
422
423 case IOP_T_BOOL:
424 SET_SCALAR(bool, opt_bool_t, b);
425 break;
426
427 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
428 SET_SCALAR(double, opt_double_t, d);
429 break;
430#undef SET_SCALAR
431
432 case IOP_T_VOID:
433 if (field->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
434 *(bool *)ptr = true;
435 }
436 e_trace(3, "ignored value_t for void field (field %d:%*pM)",
437 field->tag, LSTR_FMT_ARG(field->name));
438 break;
439
440 case IOP_T_STRING:
441 case IOP_T_XML:
442 case IOP_T_DATA: {
443 lstr_t *str = ptr;
444
445 *str = lstr_dupc(value->s);
446 break;
447 }
448 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
449 case IOP_T_UNION: {
450 if (iop_field_is_pointed(field)) {
451 *(void **)ptr = (void *)value->p;
452 } else
453 if (value->p != ptr) {
454 memcpy(ptr, value->p, field->size);
455 }
456 break;
457 }
458 }
459}
460
461size_t iop_value_get_bpack_size(const iop_value_t * nonnull value,
462 iop_type_t type,
463 const iop_struct_t * nullable st_desc)
464{
465 switch (type) {
466 case IOP_T_I8:
467 case IOP_T_BOOL:
468 return 1;
469
470 case IOP_T_U8:
471 return 1 + (((uint8_t)value->u32) >> 7);
472
473 case IOP_T_I16:
474 case IOP_T_U16:
475 case IOP_T_I32:
476 case IOP_T_ENUM:
477 return get_vint32_len(value->i32);
478
479 case IOP_T_U32:
480 case IOP_T_I64:
481 case IOP_T_U64:
482 return get_vint64_len(value->i64);
483
484 case IOP_T_VOID:
485 return 0;
486
487 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
488 return 8;
489
490 case IOP_T_STRING:
491 case IOP_T_DATA:
492 case IOP_T_XML:
493 return get_len_len(value->s.len + 1) + value->s.len + 1;
494
495 case IOP_T_UNION:
496 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
497 {
498 qv_t(i32) szs;
499 size_t sz;
500
501 qv_inita(&szs, 1024);
502 sz = iop_bpack_size(st_desc, value->p, &szs);
503 qv_wipe(&szs);
504
505 return get_len_len(sz) + sz;
506 }
507 }
508
509 assert (false);
510 return 0;
511}
512
513size_t iop_get_len_bpack_size(uint32_t length)
514{
515 return get_len_len(length);
516}
517
518int iop_value_to_repeated_field(void *ptr, const iop_field_t *field,
519 uint32_t pos, const iop_value_t *value)
520{
521 lstr_t data_s;
522 void *data_p;
523
524 if (!expect(field->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED)) {
525 return -1;
526 }
527
528 data_s = *(lstr_t *)((byte *)ptr + field->data_offs);
529 data_p = (byte *)data_s.data + pos * field->size;
530
531 iop_value_to_ptr(data_p, field, value);
532 return 0;
533}
534
535void iop_value_to_field(void *ptr, const iop_field_t *field,
536 const iop_value_t *value)
537{
538 ptr = iop_field_get_ptr(field, ptr);
539 iop_value_to_ptr(ptr, field, value);
540}
541
542void iop_set_opt_field(void *ptr, const iop_field_t *field)
543{
544 if (field->repeat != IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
545 e_panic("non-optional fields are not supported in iop_set_opt_field");
546 }
547
548 ptr = (byte *)ptr + field->data_offs;
549
550 switch ((iop_type_t)field->type) {
551 case IOP_T_U8: case IOP_T_I8: case IOP_T_BOOL:
552 ((opt_i8_t *)ptr)->has_field = true;
553 break;
554
555 case IOP_T_U16: case IOP_T_I16:
556 ((opt_i16_t *)ptr)->has_field = true;
557 break;
558
559 case IOP_T_U32: case IOP_T_I32: case IOP_T_ENUM:
560 ((opt_i32_t *)ptr)->has_field = true;
561 break;
562
563 case IOP_T_U64: case IOP_T_I64: case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
564 ((opt_i64_t *)ptr)->has_field = true;
565 break;
566
567 case IOP_T_STRING: case IOP_T_DATA: case IOP_T_XML: {
568 lstr_t *s = ptr;
569
570 if (!s->s) {
571 assert (!s->len);
572 s->s = "";
573 }
574 } break;
575
576 case IOP_T_UNION: case IOP_T_STRUCT:
577 e_panic("unions/structs are not supported in iop_set_opt_field");
578 break;
579
580 case IOP_T_VOID:
581 *(bool *)ptr = true;
582 break;
583 }
584}
585
586static int
587iop_field_set_defval(const iop_field_t *fdesc, void *ptr)
588{
589 assert (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_DEFVAL);
590 switch (fdesc->type) {
591 case IOP_T_I8: case IOP_T_U8:
592 *(uint8_t *)ptr = fdesc->u1.defval_u64;
593 break;
594 case IOP_T_I16: case IOP_T_U16:
595 *(uint16_t *)ptr = fdesc->u1.defval_u64;
596 break;
597 case IOP_T_ENUM:
598 *(uint32_t *)ptr = fdesc->u0.defval_enum;
599 break;
600 case IOP_T_I32: case IOP_T_U32:
601 *(uint32_t *)ptr = fdesc->u1.defval_u64;
602 break;
603 case IOP_T_I64: case IOP_T_U64:
604 *(uint64_t *)ptr = fdesc->u1.defval_u64;
605 break;
606 case IOP_T_BOOL:
607 *(bool *)ptr = !!fdesc->u1.defval_u64; /* Map to 0/1 */
608 break;
609 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
610 *(double *)ptr = fdesc->u1.defval_d;
611 break;
612 case IOP_T_STRING:
613 case IOP_T_XML:
614 case IOP_T_DATA:
615 *(lstr_t *)ptr = LSTR_INIT_V(fdesc->u1.defval_data,
616 fdesc->u0.defval_len);
617 break;
618 case IOP_T_UNION:
619 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
620 return -1;
621
622 case IOP_T_VOID:
623 assert (false);
624 return -1;
625 }
626
627 return 0;
628}
629
630lstr_t t_camelcase_to_c(lstr_t s)
631{
632 t_SB(buf, 64);
633
634 for (int i = 0; i < s.len; i++) {
635 if (i && isupper(s.s[i])) {
636 sb_addc(&buf, '_');
637 }
638 sb_addc(&buf, tolower(s.s[i]));
639 }
640
641 return lstr_init_(buf.data, buf.len, MEM_STACK);
642}
643
644const char *t_camelcase_to_c_str(const char *s)
645{
646 /* XXX We know that the string is null-terminated because the
647 * implementation is just a few lines above ;-). */
648 return t_camelcase_to_c(LSTR(s)).s;
649}
650
651lstr_t t_iop_type_to_c(lstr_t name)
652{
653 t_SB(buf, 64);
654 qv_t(lstr) parts;
655 pstream_t ps = ps_initlstr(&name);
656 ctype_desc_t dot;
657
658 t_qv_init(&parts, 3);
659 ctype_desc_build(&dot, ".");
660 ps_split(ps, &dot, 0, &parts);
661 if (!parts.len) {
662 return LSTR_EMPTY_V;
663 }
664
665 for (int i = 0; i < parts.len - 1; i++) {
666 sb_add_lstr(&buf, parts.tab[i]);
667 sb_adds(&buf, "__");
668 }
669 sb_add_lstr(&buf, t_camelcase_to_c(parts.tab[parts.len - 1]));
670
671 return lstr_init_(buf.data, buf.len, MEM_STACK);
672}
673
674int c_to_camelcase(lstr_t s, bool is_first_upper, sb_t *out)
675{
676 pstream_t ps = ps_initlstr(&s);
677
678 THROW_ERR_IF(lstr_endswithc(s, '_'));
679
680 sb_reset(out);
681 while (!ps_done(&ps)) {
682 pstream_t token;
683 pstream_t token2;
684
685 if (ps_get_ps_chr_and_skip(&ps, '_', &token) < 0) {
686 token = ps;
687 ps = ps_init(NULL, 0);
688 }
689
690 /* Validate token */
691 THROW_ERR_IF(ps_len(&token) == 0);
692
693 token2 = ps_get_span(&token, &ctype_isalnum);
694 THROW_ERR_IF(ps_len(&token) > 0);
695
696 token = ps_get_cspan(&token2, &ctype_isupper);
697 THROW_ERR_IF(ps_len(&token2) > 0);
698
699 /* fast path if the string needs no modification */
700 if (!is_first_upper && !out->len && ps_done(&ps)) {
701 sb_set_lstr(out, s);
702 return 0;
703 }
704
705 /* Transform token */
706 if (is_first_upper || out->len) {
707 sb_addc(out, toupper(ps_getc(&token)));
708 }
709 sb_add(out, token.s, ps_len(&token));
710 }
711 return 0;
712}
713
714lstr_t t_c_to_camelcase(lstr_t s, bool is_first_upper)
715{
716 t_SB(buf, s.len);
717
718 if (c_to_camelcase(s, is_first_upper, &buf) < 0) {
719 return LSTR_NULL_V;
720 }
721
722 return LSTR_SB_V(&buf);
723}
724
725bool iop_type_is_scalar(iop_type_t type)
726{
727 return !((1 << type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK);
728}
729
730bool iop_field_is_pointed(const iop_field_t *fdesc)
731{
732 if (iop_type_is_scalar(fdesc->type)) {
733 return false;
734 }
735
736 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
737 return true;
738 }
739
740 return iop_field_is_reference(fdesc) || iop_field_is_class(fdesc);
741}
742
743void *nullable iop_opt_field_getv(iop_type_t type, void *nonnull data)
744{
745 switch (type) {
746 case IOP_T_I8:
747 case IOP_T_U8:
748 return OPT_GET((opt_u8_t *)data);
749
750 case IOP_T_I16:
751 case IOP_T_U16:
752 return OPT_GET((opt_u16_t *)data);
753
754 case IOP_T_ENUM:
755 case IOP_T_I32:
756 case IOP_T_U32:
757 return OPT_GET((opt_u32_t *)data);
758
759 case IOP_T_I64:
760 case IOP_T_U64:
761 return OPT_GET((opt_u64_t *)data);
762
763 case IOP_T_BOOL:
764 return OPT_GET((opt_bool_t *)data);
765
766 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
767 return OPT_GET((opt_double_t *)data);
768
769 case IOP_T_STRING:
770 case IOP_T_XML:
771 case IOP_T_DATA:
772 return ((lstr_t *)data)->s ? data : NULL;
773
774 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
775 case IOP_T_UNION:
776 return *(void **)data;
777
778 case IOP_T_VOID:
779 /* XXX Return a slop pointer that means that the field is present. It
780 * isn't expected to be indirected though. */
781 return *(bool *)data ? data : NULL;
782 }
783
784 assert (false);
785 return NULL;
786}
787
788static const void *iop_opt_field_getv_const(iop_type_t type, const void *data)
789{
790 return iop_opt_field_getv(type, (void *)data);
791}
792
793void iop_get_field_values(const iop_field_t *fdesc, void *st_ptr,
794 void **values, int *len,
795 bool * nullable is_array_of_pointers)
796{
797 void *fptr = (byte *)st_ptr + fdesc->data_offs;
798
799 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
800 iop_array_i8_t *array = fptr;
801
802 *values = array->tab;
803 *len = array->len;
804 if (is_array_of_pointers) {
805 *is_array_of_pointers = iop_field_is_class(fdesc);
806 }
807
808 return;
809 }
810
811 if (is_array_of_pointers) {
812 /* For non-repeated fields, we will always apply the indirection. */
813 *is_array_of_pointers = false;
814 }
815
816 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
817 fptr = iop_opt_field_getv(fdesc->type, fptr);
818 if (!fptr) {
819 /* The optional field is absent. */
820 *len = 0;
821 *values = NULL;
822 return;
823 }
824 if (fdesc->type == IOP_T_VOID) {
825 *values = NULL;
826 } else {
827 *values = fptr;
828 }
829 } else
830 if (fdesc->type == IOP_T_VOID) {
831 *values = NULL;
832 *len = 0;
833 return;
834 } else
835 if (iop_field_is_pointed(fdesc)) {
836 *values = *(void **)fptr;
837 } else {
838 *values = fptr;
839 }
840
841 *len = 1;
842}
843
844void iop_get_field_values_const(const iop_field_t *fdesc, const void *st_ptr,
845 const void **values, int *len,
846 bool * nullable is_array_of_pointers)
847{
848 iop_get_field_values(fdesc, (void *)st_ptr, (void **)values, len,
849 is_array_of_pointers);
850}

853/* {{{ Iop type string description */
854
855const char *iop_type_get_string_desc(iop_type_t type)
856{
857 switch (type) {
858 case IOP_T_I8:
859 return "byte";
860 case IOP_T_I16:
861 return "short";
862 case IOP_T_I32:
863 return "int";
864 case IOP_T_I64:
865 return "long";
866 case IOP_T_U8:
867 return "ubyte";
868 case IOP_T_U16:
869 return "ushort";
870 case IOP_T_U32:
871 return "uint";
872 case IOP_T_U64:
873 return "ulong";
874 case IOP_T_BOOL:
875 return "bool";
876 case IOP_T_ENUM:
877 return "enum";
878 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
879 return "double";
880 case IOP_T_STRING:
881 return "string";
882 case IOP_T_DATA:
883 return "bytes";
884 case IOP_T_UNION:
885 return "union";
886 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
887 return "struct";
888 case IOP_T_XML:
889 return "xml";
890 case IOP_T_VOID:
891 return "void";
892 }
893 e_panic("iop_type unsupported");
894}
895
896iop_value_t iop_type_to_max(iop_type_t type)
897{
898 iop_value_t value;
899
900 switch (type) {
901 case IOP_T_BOOL:
902 value.u64 = true;
903 break;
904 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
905 value.d = INFINITY;
906 break;
907 case IOP_T_I8:
908 value.i64 = INT8_MAX;
909 break;
910 case IOP_T_I16:
911 value.i64 = INT16_MAX;
912 break;
913 case IOP_T_ENUM:
914 case IOP_T_I32:
915 value.i64 = INT32_MAX;
916 break;
917 case IOP_T_I64:
918 value.i64 = INT64_MAX;
919 break;
920 case IOP_T_U8:
921 value.u64 = UINT8_MAX;
922 break;
923 case IOP_T_U16:
924 value.u64 = UINT16_MAX;
925 break;
926 case IOP_T_U32:
927 value.u64 = UINT32_MAX;
928 break;
929 case IOP_T_U64:
930 value.u64 = UINT64_MAX;
931 break;
932 case IOP_T_STRING:
933 case IOP_T_DATA:
934 case IOP_T_XML:
935 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
936 case IOP_T_UNION:
937 case IOP_T_VOID:
938 e_panic("iop_type unsupported");
939 }
940
941 return value;
942}
943
944iop_value_t iop_type_to_min(iop_type_t type)
945{
946 iop_value_t value;
947
948 switch (type) {
949 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
950 value.d = -INFINITY;
951 break;
952 case IOP_T_I8:
953 value.i64 = INT8_MIN;
954 break;
955 case IOP_T_I16:
956 value.i64 = INT16_MIN;
957 break;
958 case IOP_T_ENUM:
959 case IOP_T_I32:
960 value.i64 = INT32_MIN;
961 break;
962 case IOP_T_I64:
963 value.i64 = INT64_MIN;
964 break;
965 case IOP_T_BOOL:
966 case IOP_T_U8:
967 case IOP_T_U16:
968 case IOP_T_U32:
969 case IOP_T_U64:
970 value.u64 = 0;
971 break;
972 case IOP_T_STRING:
973 case IOP_T_DATA:
974 case IOP_T_XML:
975 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
976 case IOP_T_UNION:
977 case IOP_T_VOID:
978 e_panic("iop_type unsupported");
979 }
980
981 return value;
982}

984/* }}} */
985/* {{{ Generic attributes */
986
987static int iop_convert_i64(int64_t i64, iop_type_t type, iop_value_t *value)
988{
989#define CHECK_RANGE(_min, _max) THROW_ERR_IF(i64 < _min || i64 > _max)
990
991 switch (type) {
992 case IOP_T_I8:
993 CHECK_RANGE(INT8_MIN, INT8_MAX);
994 value->i = i64;
995 break;
996 case IOP_T_U8:
997 CHECK_RANGE(0, UINT8_MAX);
998 value->u = i64;
999 break;
1000 case IOP_T_I16:
1001 CHECK_RANGE(INT16_MIN, INT16_MAX);
1002 value->i = i64;
1003 break;
1004 case IOP_T_U16:
1005 CHECK_RANGE(0, UINT16_MAX);
1006 value->u = i64;
1007 break;
1008 case IOP_T_I32:
1009 CHECK_RANGE(INT32_MIN, INT32_MAX);
1010 value->i = i64;
1011 break;
1012 case IOP_T_U32:
1013 CHECK_RANGE(0, UINT32_MAX);
1014 value->u = i64;
1015 break;
1016 case IOP_T_I64: case IOP_T_U64:
1017 value->i = i64;
1018 break;
1019 case IOP_T_BOOL:
1020 CHECK_RANGE(0, 1);
1021 value->b = i64;
1022 break;
1023 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
1024 value->d = i64;
1025 break;
1026 case IOP_T_ENUM:
1027 case IOP_T_STRING:
1028 case IOP_T_DATA:
1029 case IOP_T_XML:
1030 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
1031 case IOP_T_UNION:
1032 case IOP_T_VOID:
1033 return -1;
1034 }
1035
1036#undef CHECK_RANGE
1037 return 0;
1038}
1039
1040#define ATTR_IS_GENERIC(_attr, _what) \
1041 (_attr->type == IOP_##_what##_GEN_ATTR_S \
1042 || _attr->type == IOP_##_what##_GEN_ATTR_O \
1043 || _attr->type == IOP_##_what##_GEN_ATTR_I \
1044 || _attr->type == IOP_##_what##_GEN_ATTR_D)
1045
1046static int iop_convert_value(iop_type_t exp_type, iop_type_t val_type,
1047 iop_value_t *value)
1048{
1049 switch (val_type) {
1050 case IOP_T_STRING:
1051 return iop_type_is_string(exp_type) ? 0 : -1;
1052
1053 case IOP_T_I64:
1054 return iop_convert_i64(value->i64, exp_type, value);
1055
1056 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
1057 return exp_type == IOP_T_DOUBLE ? 0 : -1;
1058
1059 case IOP_T_I8:
1060 case IOP_T_I16:
1061 case IOP_T_I32:
1062 case IOP_T_BOOL:
1063 case IOP_T_ENUM:
1064 case IOP_T_U8:
1065 case IOP_T_U16:
1066 case IOP_T_U32:
1067 case IOP_T_U64:
1068 case IOP_T_DATA:
1069 case IOP_T_XML:
1070 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
1071 case IOP_T_UNION:
1072 case IOP_T_VOID:
1073 e_panic("iop_type unsupported");
1074 }
1075 return -1;
1076}
1077
1078#define __get_gen_attr_value(_attrs, _len, _key, _what, _what_l, \
1079 _exp_type, _val_type, _val) \
1080 ({ \
1081 int _res = -1; \
1082 iop_type_t _attr_type; \
1083 \
1084 for (int _i = 0; _i < _len; _i++) { \
1085 const iop_##_what_l##_attr_t *_attr = _attrs + _i; \
1086 \
1087 if (!ATTR_IS_GENERIC(_attr, _what) \
1088 || !lstr_equal(_key, _attr->args[0].v.s)) \
1089 { \
1090 continue; \
1091 } \
1092 \
1093 _res = 0; \
1094 switch (_attr->type) { \
1095 case IOP_##_what##_GEN_ATTR_O: \
1096 case IOP_##_what##_GEN_ATTR_S: \
1097 _val->s = _attr->args[1].v.s; \
1098 _attr_type = IOP_T_STRING; \
1099 break; \
1100 case IOP_##_what##_GEN_ATTR_I: \
1101 _val->i64 = _attr->args[1].v.i64; \
1102 _attr_type = IOP_T_I64; \
1103 break; \
1104 case IOP_##_what##_GEN_ATTR_D: \
1105 _val->d = _attr->args[1].v.d; \
1106 _attr_type = IOP_T_DOUBLE; \
1107 break; \
1108 default: \
1109 e_panic("invalid generic attribute type"); \
1110 } \
1111 break; \
1112 } \
1113 \
1114 if (_res == 0) { \
1115 if ((int)_exp_type >= 0) { \
1116 _res = iop_convert_value(_exp_type, _attr_type, _val); \
1117 } \
1118 if (_val_type) { \
1119 *_val_type = _attr_type; \
1120 } \
1121 } \
1122 \
1123 _res; \
1124 })
1125
1126int iop_struct_get_gen_attr(const iop_struct_t *st, lstr_t key,
1127 iop_type_t exp_type, iop_type_t *val_type,
1128 iop_value_t *value)
1129{
1130 unsigned flags = st->flags;
1131
1132 if (!TST_BIT(&flags, IOP_STRUCT_EXTENDED) || !st->st_attrs) {
1133 return -1;
1134 }
1135 return __get_gen_attr_value(st->st_attrs->attrs, st->st_attrs->attrs_len,
1136 key, STRUCT, struct, exp_type, val_type,
1137 value);
1138}
1139
1140int iop_enum_get_gen_attr(const iop_enum_t *en, lstr_t key,
1141 iop_type_t exp_type, iop_type_t *val_type,
1142 iop_value_t *value)
1143{
1144 if (!TST_BIT(&en->flags, IOP_ENUM_EXTENDED) || !en->en_attrs) {
1145 return -1;
1146 }
1147 return __get_gen_attr_value(en->en_attrs->attrs, en->en_attrs->attrs_len,
1148 key, ENUM, enum, exp_type, val_type, value);
1149}
1150
1151static int iop_enum_pos_from_val(const iop_enum_t *e, int val);
1152static int iop_enum_pos_from_str(const iop_enum_t *e, const char *s, int len);
1153
1154int iop_enum_get_gen_attr_from_val(const iop_enum_t *ed, int val, lstr_t key,
1155 iop_type_t exp_type, iop_type_t *val_type,
1156 iop_value_t *value)
1157{
1158 const iop_enum_value_attrs_t *va;
1159 int pos;
1160
1161 if (!TST_BIT(&ed->flags, IOP_ENUM_EXTENDED) || !ed->values_attrs) {
1162 return -1;
1163 }
1164 pos = RETHROW(iop_enum_pos_from_val(ed, val));
1165 va = &ed->values_attrs[pos];
1166 return __get_gen_attr_value(va->attrs, va->attrs_len, key, ENUM_VALUE,
1167 enum_value, exp_type, val_type, value);
1168}
1169
1170int iop_enum_get_gen_attr_from_str(const iop_enum_t *ed, lstr_t val,
1171 lstr_t key, iop_type_t exp_type,
1172 iop_type_t *val_type, iop_value_t *value)
1173{
1174 const iop_enum_value_attrs_t *va;
1175 int pos;
1176
1177 if (!TST_BIT(&ed->flags, IOP_ENUM_EXTENDED) || !ed->values_attrs) {
1178 return -1;
1179 }
1180 pos = RETHROW(iop_enum_pos_from_str(ed, val.s, val.len));
1181 va = &ed->values_attrs[pos];
1182 return __get_gen_attr_value(va->attrs, va->attrs_len, key, ENUM_VALUE,
1183 enum_value, exp_type, val_type, value);
1184}

1186int iop_iface_get_gen_attr(const iop_iface_t *iface, lstr_t key,
1187 iop_type_t exp_type, iop_type_t *val_type,
1188 iop_value_t *value)
1189{
1190 if (!TST_BIT(&iface->flags, IOP_IFACE_HAS_ATTRS) || !iface->iface_attrs) {
1191 return -1;

1230bool iop_field_get_bool_gen_attr(const iop_struct_t *st,
1231 const iop_field_t *field, lstr_t key,
1232 bool def)
1233{
1234 iop_value_t value;
1235
1236 if (iop_field_get_gen_attr(st, field, key, IOP_T_BOOL, NULL, &value) < 0)
1237 {
1238 return def;
1239 }
1240
1241 return value.b;
1242}

1244int iop_field_by_name_get_gen_attr(const iop_struct_t *st, lstr_t f_name,
1245 lstr_t key, iop_type_t exp_type,

1255
1256/* }}} */
1257/* {{{ iop_init / iop_new */
1258
1259static void
1260iop_init_fields(void *value, const iop_field_t *fdesc, const iop_field_t *end)
1261{
1262 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
1263 void *ptr = (char *)value + fdesc->data_offs;
1264
1265 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REQUIRED && fdesc->type == IOP_T_STRUCT) {
1266 /* We can't handle the unions here since we don't know which field
1267 * has been selected */
1268 const iop_struct_t *desc = fdesc->u1.st_desc;
1269
1270 if (iop_field_is_pointed(fdesc)) {
1271 /* Field should be initialized as an optional field: NULL
1272 * pointer. */
1273 continue;
1274 }
1275
1276 iop_init_fields(ptr, desc->fields, desc->fields +
1277 desc->fields_len);
1278 } else
1279 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_DEFVAL
1280 && iop_field_set_defval(fdesc, ptr) < 0)
1281 {
1282 e_panic("should not happen");
1283 }
1284 }
1285}
1286
1287void iop_init_union_desc(const iop_struct_t *desc, void *value,
1288 const iop_field_t *fdesc)
1289{
1290 memset(value, 0, desc->size);
1291
1292 if (!expect(desc->is_union)) {
1293 return;
1294 }
1295 iop_union_set_tag(desc, fdesc->tag, value);
1296 iop_init_fields(value, fdesc, fdesc + 1);
1297}
1298
1299void iop_init_desc(const iop_struct_t *desc, void *value)
1300{
1301 memset(value, 0, desc->size);
1302
1303 if (desc->is_union) {
1304 return;
1305 }
1306 if (iop_struct_is_class(desc)) {
1307 const iop_struct_t **__vptr = value;
1308 const iop_struct_t *parent = desc;
1309
1310 e_assert(panic, !desc->class_attrs->is_abstract,
1311 "initialization of abstract class '%*pM' is forbidden",
1312 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
1313
1314 *__vptr = desc;
1315
1316 while ((parent = parent->class_attrs->parent)) {
1317 iop_init_fields(value, parent->fields,
1318 parent->fields + parent->fields_len);
1319 }
1320 }
1321
1322 iop_init_fields(value, desc->fields, desc->fields + desc->fields_len);
1323}
1324
1325void *mp_iop_new_desc(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st)
1326{
1327 void *res = mp_imalloc(mp, st->size, 8, MEM_RAW);
1328
1329 iop_init_desc(st, res);
1330
1331 return res;
1332}
1333
1334/* }}} */
1335/* {{{ Duplicating values */
1336
1337static size_t __iop_dup_class_size(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val);
1338
1339static size_t __iop_dup_size(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val)
1340{
1341 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
1342 const iop_field_t *end;
1343 size_t len = 0;
1344
1345 if (desc->is_union) {
1346 fdesc = get_union_field(desc, val);
1347 end = fdesc + 1;
1348 } else {
1349 fdesc = desc->fields;
1350 end = fdesc + desc->fields_len;
1351 }
1352
1353 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
1354 const void *ptr = iop_field_get_cptr(fdesc, val);
1355 bool is_class = iop_field_is_class(fdesc);
1356 bool is_ref = iop_field_is_reference(fdesc);
1357 int n = 1;
1358
1359 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
1360 n = ((lstr_t *)ptr)->len;
1361 ptr = ((lstr_t *)ptr)->data;
1362 len += ROUND_UP(n * fdesc->size, 8);
1363 }
1364
1365 if (!((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_BLK_OK)) /* DATA,STRING,STRUCT,UNION */
1366 continue;
1367
1368 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
1369 if (!iop_opt_field_isset(fdesc->type, ptr)) {
1370 continue;
1371 }
1372 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK) {
1373 ptr = *(void **)ptr;
1374 if (is_class) {
1375 /* Do not take the field size, but the size of the
1376 * actually instanciated class */
1377 len += ROUND_UP((*(const iop_struct_t **)ptr)->size, 8);
1378 } else {
1379 len += ROUND_UP(fdesc->size, 8);
1380 }
1381 }
1382 }
1383
1384 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK) {
1385 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
1386 const void *v = &IOP_FIELD(const char, ptr, j * fdesc->size);
1387
1388 if ((is_class || is_ref) && fdesc->repeat != IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
1389 /* Non-optional reference fields have to be dereferenced
1390 * (dereferencing of optional fields was already done
1391 * just above).
1392 */
1393 v = *(void **)v;
1394 if (is_class) {
1395 len += ROUND_UP((*(const iop_struct_t **)v)->size, 8);
1396 }
1397 }
1398 if (is_class) {
1399 len += __iop_dup_class_size(fdesc->u1.st_desc, v);
1400 } else {
1401 if (is_ref) {
1402 len += ROUND_UP(fdesc->size, 8);
1403 }
1404 len += __iop_dup_size(fdesc->u1.st_desc, v);
1405 }
1406 }
1407 } else {
1408 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
1409 len += ROUND_UP(IOP_FIELD(lstr_t, ptr, j).len + 1, 8);
1410 }
1411 }
1412 }
1413
1414 return len;
1415}
1416
1417static size_t __iop_dup_class_size(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val)
1418{
1419 size_t len = 0;
1420
1421 desc = *(const iop_struct_t **)val;
1422 do {
1423 len += __iop_dup_size(desc, val);
1424 } while ((desc = desc->class_attrs->parent));
1425
1426 return len;
1427}
1428
1429static size_t iop_dup_size(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val)
1430{
1431 if (iop_struct_is_class(desc)) {
1432 return __iop_dup_class_size(desc, val);
1433 } else {
1434 return __iop_dup_size(desc, val);
1435 }
1436}
1437
1438static uint8_t *realign(uint8_t *ptr)
1439{
1440 return (uint8_t *)ROUND_UP((uintptr_t)ptr, 8);
1441}
1442
1443static uint8_t *
1444__iop_deep_copy_class(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st,
1445 uint8_t *dst, void *wval, const void *rval);
1446
1447static uint8_t *__iop_deep_copy(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st,
1448 uint8_t *dst, void *wval, const void *rval)
1449{
1450 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
1451 const iop_field_t *end;
1452
1453 if (st->is_union) {
1454 fdesc = get_union_field(st, rval);
1455 end = fdesc + 1;
1456 } else {
1457 fdesc = st->fields;
1458 end = fdesc + st->fields_len;
1459 }
1460
1461 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
1462 const void *rp = (char *)rval + fdesc->data_offs;
1463 const void *wp = (char *)wval + fdesc->data_offs;
1464 int n = 1;
1465
1466 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
1467 n = ((lstr_t *)rp)->len;
1468 if (n) {
1469 if (mp) {
1470 dst = mp_imalloc(mp, n * fdesc->size, 8, MEM_RAW);
1471 }
1472 rp = ((lstr_t *)rp)->data;
1473 wp = ((lstr_t *)wp)->data = dst;
1474 dst = realign(mempcpy(dst, rp, n * fdesc->size));
1475 } else {
1476 ((lstr_t *)wp)->data = NULL;
1477 dst = realign(dst);
1478 continue;
1479 }
1480 }
1481
1482 if (!((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_BLK_OK)) {
1483 /* The type is not DATA,STRING,STRUCT,UNION */
1484 continue;
1485 }
1486
1487 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL
1488 && !iop_opt_field_isset(fdesc->type, rp))
1489 {
1490 continue;
1491 }
1492
1493 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(fdesc->type)) {
1494 bool is_class = iop_field_is_class(fdesc);
1495 bool is_ref = iop_field_is_reference(fdesc);
1496 const iop_struct_t *fst = fdesc->u1.st_desc;
1497
1498 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
1499 const void *rv = &IOP_FIELD(const char, rp, j * fdesc->size);
1500 void *wv = &IOP_FIELD(char, wp, j * fdesc->size);
1501
1502 if (is_class || is_ref || fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
1503 /* Non-optional referenced fields have to be dereferenced
1504 * (dereferencing of optional fields was already done
1505 * just above).
1506 */
1507 rv = *(void **)rv;
1508
1509 if (is_class) {
1510 fst = *(const iop_struct_t **)rv;
1511 }
1512 if (mp) {
1513 dst = mp_imalloc(mp, fst->size, 8, MEM_RAW);
1514 }
1515
1516 wv = *(void **)wv = dst;
1517
1518 if (!is_class) {
1519 /* Will be done in __iop_copy_class for classes */
1520 dst = realign(mempcpy(dst, rv, fdesc->size));
1521 }
1522 }
1523 if (is_class) {
1524 dst = __iop_deep_copy_class(mp, fst, dst, wv, rv);
1525 } else {
1526 dst = __iop_deep_copy(mp, fst, dst, wv, rv);
1527 }
1528 }
1529 } else {
1530 assert (fdesc->type == IOP_T_STRING || fdesc->type == IOP_T_XML
1531 || fdesc->type == IOP_T_DATA);
1532
1533 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
1534 lstr_t *orig = &IOP_FIELD(lstr_t, rp, j);
1535 lstr_t *dest = &IOP_FIELD(lstr_t, wp, j);
1536
1537 if (mp) {
1538 dst = mp_imalloc(mp, orig->len + 1, alignof(char),
1539 MEM_RAW);
1540 }
1541
1542 /* We have to fix the lstr_t mem_pool manually because
1543 * some naughty programmers could have played with it */
1544 dest->data = dst;
1545 dest->mem_pool = MEM_STATIC;
1546 dst = realign(mempcpyz(dst, orig->s, orig->len));
1547 }
1548 }
1549 }
1550
1551 return dst;
1552}
1553
1554static uint8_t *
1555__iop_deep_copy_class_fields(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st,
1556 uint8_t *dst, void *wval, const void *rval)
1557{
1558 do {
1559 dst = __iop_deep_copy(mp, st, dst, wval, rval);
1560 } while ((st = st->class_attrs->parent));
1561
1562 return dst;
1563}
1564
1565static uint8_t *
1566__iop_deep_copy_class(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st,
1567 uint8_t *dst, void *wval, const void *rval)
1568{
1569 dst = realign(mempcpy(dst, rval, st->size));
1570 return __iop_deep_copy_class_fields(mp, st, dst, wval, rval);
1571}
1572
1573static void *
1574__mp_iop_copy_desc_flags_sz(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st,
1575 void *nullable *outp, const void *v,
1576 unsigned flags, size_t *nullable psz)
1577{
1578 bool is_class;
1579 size_t sz;
1580 uint8_t *dst, *res;
1581
1582 if (!v) {
1583 if (outp) {
1584 mp_ifree(mp, *outp);
1585 *outp = NULL;
1586 }
1587 return NULL;
1588 }
1589
1590 mp = mp_ipool(mp);
1591 if (flags & IOP_COPY_MULTIPLE_ALLOC) {
1592 e_assert(panic, mp->mem_pool & MEM_BY_FRAME,
1593 "using IOP_COPY_MULTIPLE_ALLOC on non frame-based memory "
1594 "pools is forbidden");
1595 if (!expect(!psz)) {
1596 /* Size can be set only in single allocation mode. */
1597 *psz = 0;
1598 psz = NULL;
1599 }
1600 }
1601
1602 if ((is_class = iop_struct_is_class(st))) {
1603 st = *(const iop_struct_t **)v;
1604 }
1605
1606 if (flags & IOP_COPY_NO_REALLOC) {
1607 size_t offset = 0;
1608
1609 e_assert(panic, outp && *outp, "IOP_COPY_NO_REALLOC require outp to "
1610 "point to an existing object");
1611
1612 res = *outp;
1613 if (is_class) {
1614 e_assert(panic, iop_obj_is_a_desc(res, st),
1615 "existing outp object is not a `%*pM`",
1616 LSTR_FMT_ARG(st->fullname));
1617 /* Skip the __vptr field. */
1618 offset = sizeof(iop_struct_t *);
1619 }
1620
1621 if (flags & (IOP_COPY_MULTIPLE_ALLOC | IOP_COPY_SHALLOW)) {
1622 sz = 0;
1623 } else {
1624 e_assert(panic, mp->mem_pool & MEM_BY_FRAME,
1625 "using IOP_COPY_NO_REALLOC on non frame-based memory "
1626 "pools without IOP_COPY_SHALLOW is forbidden");
1627 sz = iop_dup_size(st, v);
1628 }
1629 if (!expect(!psz)) {
1630 /* Size can be set only in realloc mode. */
1631 *psz = 0;
1632 }
1633 if ((flags & IOP_COPY_ALLOC_SAFE) && sz > MEM_ALLOC_MAX) {
1634 *outp = NULL;
1635 return NULL;
1636 }
1637
1638 memcpy(res + offset, (const uint8_t *)v + offset, st->size - offset);
1639 dst = sz ? mp_imalloc(mp, sz, 8, MEM_RAW) : NULL;
1640 } else {
1641 if (flags & (IOP_COPY_MULTIPLE_ALLOC | IOP_COPY_SHALLOW)) {
1642 sz = st->size;
1643 } else {
1644 sz = ROUND_UP(st->size, 8) + iop_dup_size(st, v);
1645 }
1646
1647 if (psz) {
1648 *psz = sz;
1649 }
1650 if ((flags & IOP_COPY_ALLOC_SAFE) && sz > MEM_ALLOC_MAX) {
1651 if (outp) {
1652 mp_delete(mp, outp);
1653 }
1654 return NULL;
1655 }
1656
1657 if (outp) {
1658 res = *outp;
1659 res = mp_irealloc(mp, res, 0, sz, 8, MEM_RAW);
1660 *outp = res;
1661 } else {
1662 res = mp_imalloc(mp, sz, 8, MEM_RAW);
1663 }
1664
1665 dst = realign(mempcpy(res, v, st->size));
1666 }
1667
1668 if (!(flags & IOP_COPY_SHALLOW)) {
1669 if (!(flags & IOP_COPY_MULTIPLE_ALLOC)) {
1670 /* XXX Everything's already allocated at this point. There is no
1671 * assumption that 'mp == NULL' means that we should use
1672 * mem_pool_libc in __iop_copy_class and __iop_copy.
1673 */
1674 mp = NULL;
1675 }
1676
1677 if (is_class) {
1678 dst = __iop_deep_copy_class_fields(mp, st, dst, res, v);
1679 } else {
1680 dst = __iop_deep_copy(mp, st, dst, res, v);
1681 }
1682 }
1683
1684 assert ((flags & (IOP_COPY_MULTIPLE_ALLOC | IOP_COPY_NO_REALLOC))
1685 || dst == res + sz);
1686 return res;
1687}
1688
1689void *mp_iop_dup_desc_flags_sz(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st,
1690 const void *v, unsigned flags,
1691 size_t *nullable psz)
1692{
1693 return __mp_iop_copy_desc_flags_sz(mp, st, NULL, v, flags, psz);
1694}
1695
1696void mp_iop_copy_desc_flags_sz(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st,
1697 void **outp, const void *v, unsigned flags,
1698 size_t *nullable psz)
1699{
1700 __mp_iop_copy_desc_flags_sz(mp, st, outp, v, flags, psz);
1701}
1702
1703/* }}} */
1704/* {{{ Comparing values */
1705
1706__cold static void
1707sb_prepend_field(sb_t *sb, const iop_field_t *fdesc, int j);
1708
1709static int iop_first_diff(const iop_struct_t *st,
1710 const void *v1, const void *v2,
1711 sb_t *field_path, sb_t *diff_desc);
1712
1713static inline void iop_value_print(iop_type_t type, const iop_enum_t *en_desc,
1714 const void *v, sb_t *buf)
1715{
1716 switch (type) {
1717 case IOP_T_BOOL:
1718 sb_adds(buf, *(const bool *)v ? "true" : "false");
1719 break;
1720
1721#define CASE_NUMBER(type, fmt, type_t) \
1722 case type: \
1723 sb_addf(buf, fmt, *(const type_t *)v); \
1724 break;
1725
1726 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_U8, "%u", uint8_t);
1727 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_I8, "%d", int8_t);
1728 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_U16, "%u", uint16_t);
1729 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_I16, "%d", int16_t);
1730 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_U32, "%u", uint32_t);
1731 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_I32, "%d", int32_t);
1732 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_U64, "%ju", uint64_t);
1733 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_I64, "%jd", int64_t);
1734 CASE_NUMBER(IOP_T_DOUBLE, "%f", double);
1735
1736#undef CASE_NUMBER
1737
1738 case IOP_T_ENUM:
1739 sb_addf(buf, "%*pE", IOP_ENUM_DESC_FMT_ARG_FLAGS(en_desc,
1740 *(const int32_t *)v,
1741 IOP_ENUM_FMT_FULL));
1742 break;
1743
1744 case IOP_T_STRING:
1745 case IOP_T_XML:
1746 sb_add_lstr(buf, *(const lstr_t *)v);
1747 break;
1748
1749 case IOP_T_DATA: {
1750 lstr_t data = *(const lstr_t *)v;
1751
1752 sb_add_lstr_hex(buf, data);
1753 } break;
1754
1755 case IOP_T_VOID:
1756 sb_sets(buf, "void");
1757 break;
1758
1759 case IOP_T_UNION:
1760 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
1761 e_panic("not supported");
1762 }
1763}
1764
1765/* Returns -1 if no diff found, 0 otherwise. */
1766static int __iop_first_diff(const iop_struct_t *st,
1767 const void *v1, const void *v2,
1768 sb_t *field_path, sb_t *diff_desc)
1769{
1770 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
1771 int i = 0;
1772 const iop_field_t *end;
1773
1774 if (st->is_union) {
1775 int tag_v1 = RETHROW(iop_union_get_tag(st, v1));
1776 int tag_v2 = RETHROW(iop_union_get_tag(st, v2));
1777 if (tag_v1 != tag_v2) {
1778 sb_setf(diff_desc, "union field differs (`%*pU` vs `%*pU`)",
1779 (uint16_t)tag_v1, st, (uint16_t)tag_v2, st);
1780 return -1;
1781 }
1782
1783 fdesc = get_union_field(st, v1);
1784 end = fdesc + 1;
1785 } else {
1786 fdesc = st->fields;
1787 end = fdesc + st->fields_len;
1788 }
1789
1790 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
1791 const void *r1;
1792 const void *r2;
1793 int len1;
1794 int len2;
1795 bool is_array_of_pointers;
1796
1797 iop_get_field_values_const(fdesc, v1, &r1, &len1,
1798 &is_array_of_pointers);
1799 iop_get_field_values_const(fdesc, v2, &r2, &len2, NULL);
1800
1801 if (len1 != len2) {
1802 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
1803 sb_setf(diff_desc, "array length differs (%d vs %d)",
1804 len1, len2);
1805 } else {
1806 sb_setf(diff_desc,
1807 "field presence differs (field absent on %s value)",
1808 len1 ? "second" : "first");
1809 }
1810 goto print_field;
1811 }
1812
1813 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK) {
1814 /* We need to recurse to compare structures & unions. */
1815 for (i = 0; i < len1; i++) {
1816 const void *t1, *t2;
1817
1818 t1 = &IOP_FIELD(const uint8_t, r1, i * fdesc->size);
1819 t2 = &IOP_FIELD(const uint8_t, r2, i * fdesc->size);
1820
1821 if (is_array_of_pointers) {
1822 t1 = *(void **)t1;
1823 t2 = *(void **)t2;
1824 }
1825
1826 if (iop_first_diff(fdesc->u1.st_desc, t1, t2,
1827 field_path, diff_desc) >= 0)
1828 {
1829 goto print_field;
1830 }
1831 }
1832 } else {
1833 for (i = 0; i < len1; i++) {
1834 const void *t1, *t2;
1835
1836 t1 = &IOP_FIELD(const uint8_t, r1, i * fdesc->size);
1837 t2 = &IOP_FIELD(const uint8_t, r2, i * fdesc->size);
1838
1839 if (!iop_value_equals(fdesc->type, t1, t2)) {
1840 const iop_enum_t *en_desc = NULL;
1841
1842 if (fdesc->type == IOP_T_ENUM) {
1843 en_desc = fdesc->u1.en_desc;
1844 }
1845
1846 sb_sets(diff_desc, "value differs (`");
1847 iop_value_print(fdesc->type, en_desc, t1, diff_desc);
1848 sb_adds(diff_desc, "` vs `");
1849 iop_value_print(fdesc->type, en_desc, t2, diff_desc);
1850 sb_adds(diff_desc, "`)");
1851
1852 goto print_field;
1853 }
1854 }
1855 }
1856 }
1857
1858 return -1;
1859
1860 print_field:
1861 sb_prepend_field(field_path, fdesc, i);
1862 return 0;
1863}
1864
1865static int iop_first_diff(const iop_struct_t *st,
1866 const void *v1, const void *v2,
1867 sb_t *field_path, sb_t *diff_desc)
1868{
1869 THROW_ERR_IF(v1 == v2);
1870
1871 if (iop_struct_is_class(st)) {
1872 const iop_struct_t *st2 = *(const iop_struct_t **)v2;
1873
1874 st = *(const iop_struct_t **)v1;
1875 if (st != st2) {
1876 sb_setf(diff_desc, "class type differs (%*pM vs %*pM)",
1877 LSTR_FMT_ARG(st->fullname),
1878 LSTR_FMT_ARG(st2->fullname));
1879 return 0;
1880 }
1881
1882 do {
1883 if (__iop_first_diff(st, v1, v2, field_path, diff_desc) >= 0) {
1884 return 0;
1885 }
1886 } while ((st = st->class_attrs->parent));
1887
1888 return -1;
1889 }
1890
1891 return __iop_first_diff(st, v1, v2, field_path, diff_desc);
1892}
1893
1894int iop_first_diff_desc(const iop_struct_t *st,
1895 const void *v1, const void *v2, sb_t *diff_desc)
1896{
1897 SB_1k(field_path);
1898
1899 sb_reset_reverse(&field_path);
1900 RETHROW(iop_first_diff(st, v1, v2, &field_path, diff_desc));
1901
1902 if (field_path.len) {
1903 assert (field_path.data[0] == '.');
1904 sb_skip(&field_path, 1);
1905 sb_prependf(diff_desc, "field `%*pM`: ", SB_FMT_ARG(&field_path));
1906 }
1907
1908 return 0;
1909}
1910
1911static bool
1912__iop_equals(const iop_struct_t *st, const uint8_t *v1, const uint8_t *v2)
1913{
1914 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
1915 const iop_field_t *end;
1916
1917 if (st->is_union) {
1918 int tag_v1 = RETHROW(iop_union_get_tag(st, v1));
1919 int tag_v2 = RETHROW(iop_union_get_tag(st, v2));
1920 if (tag_v1 != tag_v2)
1921 return false;
1922 fdesc = get_union_field(st, v1);
1923 end = fdesc + 1;
1924 } else {
1925 fdesc = st->fields;
1926 end = fdesc + st->fields_len;
1927 }
1928
1929 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
1930 const void *r1 = v1 + fdesc->data_offs;
1931 const void *r2 = v2 + fdesc->data_offs;
1932 int n = 1;
1933
1934 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
1935 /* Here we just check the length of the repeated field, then we
1936 * position our pointers on values to compare them later. */
1937 n = ((lstr_t *)r1)->len;
1938 if (((lstr_t *)r2)->len != n)
1939 return false;
1940 r1 = ((lstr_t *)r1)->data;
1941 r2 = ((lstr_t *)r2)->data;
1942 }
1943
1944 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
1945 /* Optional blocks types cannot be compared using a single memcmp
1946 * we need to handle absent values first. */
1947 bool has = iop_opt_field_isset(fdesc->type, r1);
1948
1949 if (has != iop_opt_field_isset(fdesc->type, r2)) {
1950 return false;
1951 }
1952 if (!has) {
1953 continue;
1954 }
1955 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK) {
1956 /* Structures & unions must be dereferenced */
1957 r1 = *(void **)r1;
1958 r2 = *(void **)r2;
1959 }
1960 }
1961
1962 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK) {
1963 bool is_class = iop_field_is_class(fdesc);
1964 bool is_ref = iop_field_is_reference(fdesc);
1965
1966 /* We need to recurse to compare structures & unions. */
1967 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
1968 const void *t1, *t2;
1969
1970 t1 = &IOP_FIELD(const uint8_t, r1, i * fdesc->size);
1971 t2 = &IOP_FIELD(const uint8_t, r2, i * fdesc->size);
1972
1973 if ((is_class || is_ref) && fdesc->repeat != IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
1974 /* Non-optional class fields have to be dereferenced
1975 * (dereferencing of optional fields was already done just
1976 * above).
1977 */
1978 t1 = *(void **)t1;
1979 t2 = *(void **)t2;
1980 }
1981 if (is_class) {
1982 THROW_IF(!iop_equals_desc(fdesc->u1.st_desc, t1, t2),
1983 false);
1984 } else {
1985 THROW_IF(!__iop_equals(fdesc->u1.st_desc, t1, t2), false);
1986 }
1987 }
1988 } else
1989 if (fdesc->type == IOP_T_VOID) {
1990 /* Two void fields are always equal if present. */
1991 continue;
1992 } else
1993 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_BLK_OK) {
1994 /* Blocks (string & co) must be compared one by one */
1995 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
1996 const lstr_t *t1 = &IOP_FIELD(const lstr_t, r1, i);
1997 const lstr_t *t2 = &IOP_FIELD(const lstr_t, r2, i);
1998
1999 if (t1->len != t2->len || memcmp(t1->data, t2->data, t1->len))
2000 return false;
2001 }
2002 } else {
2003 assert (fdesc->size > 0 && "IOPC is probably outdated");
2004 if (!iop_scalar_equals(fdesc, r1, r2, n))
2005 return false;
2006 }
2007 }
2008
2009 return true;
2010}
2011
2012bool iop_equals_desc(const iop_struct_t *st, const void *v1, const void *v2)
2013{
2014 if (v1 && v2) {
2015 if (iop_struct_is_class(st)) {
2016 const iop_struct_t *st2 = *(const iop_struct_t **)v2;
2017
2018 st = *(const iop_struct_t **)v1;
2019 if (st != st2) {
2020 return false;
2021 }
2022
2023 do {
2024 if (!__iop_equals(st, v1, v2)) {
2025 return false;
2026 }
2027 } while ((st = st->class_attrs->parent));
2028
2029 return true;
2030 }
2031
2032 return __iop_equals(st, v1, v2);
2033 } else {
2034 return v1 == v2 || (st->size == 0);
2035 }
2036}
2037
2038/* }}} */
2039/* {{{ Sorting values */
2040/* {{{ Field path */
2041
2042typedef enum field_step_type_t {
2043 FIELD_STEP_TYPE_MOVE,
2044 FIELD_STEP_TYPE_INDIRECTION,
2045 FIELD_STEP_TYPE_UNION_FIELD,
2046 FIELD_STEP_TYPE_GOTO_INDEX,
2047 FIELD_STEP_TYPE_OBJ_CAST,
2048 FIELD_STEP_TYPE_SCAN_ARRAY,
2049} field_step_type_t;
2050
2051typedef struct field_step_t {
2052 field_step_type_t type : 16;
2053
2054 /* For step type FIELD_STEP_TYPE_GOTO_INDEX and
2055 * FIELD_STEP_TYPE_SCAN_ARRAY: size of the elements of the array. */
2056 uint16_t array_element_sz;
2057
2058 union {
2059 /* For step type FIELD_STEP_TYPE_MOVE. Distance (in byte) between the
2060 * current position and the next field to read. */
2061 uint16_t offset;
2062
2063 /* For step type FIELD_STEP_TYPE_UNION_FIELD. Expected union tag for
2064 * current union. If another field is selected, then the field is
2065 * considered as missing. */
2066 uint16_t union_tag;
2067
2068 /* For step type FIELD_STEP_TYPE_GOTO_INDEX, index of the field in the
2069 * array. */
2070 int index;
2071
2072 /* For step type FIELD_STEP_TYPE_OBJ_CAST, description of the
2073 * subclass to cast to. */
2074 const iop_struct_t *subclass_st;
2075 } u;
2076} field_step_t;
2077GENERIC_INIT(field_step_t, field_step);
2078
2079qvector_t(field_step, field_step_t);
2080
2081/* A field path contains the instructions for a quick access to a given field.
2082 * The path is split in:
2083 *
2084 * - "indirection steps" that contains the number of bytes to skip to the
2085 * next pointer to indirect.
2086 * - "union steps" that contains the number of bytes to skip to get to the
2087 * union and the tag of the field we expect to be selected.
2088 *
2089 * Therefore, sequences of inlined struct field will be packed in a single
2090 * indirection step.
2091 */
2092struct iop_field_path_t {
2093 /* Steps needed to get to the field. */
2094 qv_t(field_step) steps;
2095
2096 /* Description of the field to get. */
2097 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
2098
2099 /* True if the field is an element of an array (eg. the path ends with an
2100 * index like in the following example: "foo.bar[42]"). */
2101 bool is_array_element : 1;
2102
2103 /* True if the field is the name of an IOP class (in this case, the
2104 * field name is supposed to be '_class'). */
2105 bool is_typename : 1;
2106
2107 /* True if the field we're trying to obtain is the length of an array. */
2108 bool is_array_len : 1;
2109};
2110
2111static iop_field_path_t *mp_iop_field_path_init(mem_pool_t *nullable mp,
2112 iop_field_path_t *fp)
2113{
2114 p_clear(fp, 1);
2115 mp_qv_init(mp, &fp->steps, 16);
2116
2117 return fp;
2118}
2119
2120static inline iop_field_path_t *t_iop_field_path_init(iop_field_path_t *fp)
2121{
2122 return mp_iop_field_path_init(t_pool(), fp);
2123}
2124
2125static void iop_field_path_wipe(iop_field_path_t *fp)
2126{
2127 qv_wipe(&fp->steps);
2128}
2129
2130/* {{{ Get */
2131
2132static iop_value_from_field_res_t
2133field_step_run(const field_step_t *step, const void **data,
2134 sb_t *nullable err)
2135{
2136 switch (step->type) {
2137 case FIELD_STEP_TYPE_MOVE:
2138 *data = ((const byte *)*data) + step->u.offset;
2139 break;
2140
2141 case FIELD_STEP_TYPE_INDIRECTION:
2142 /* Pointed structure or union (optional), or classes */
2143 *data = *((void **)*data);
2144 if (!(*data)) {
2145 /* TODO Error for mandatory fields maybe? */
2146 if (err) {
2147 sb_sets(err, "missing data on indirection");
2148 }
2149 return IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET;
2150 }
2151 break;
2152
2153 case FIELD_STEP_TYPE_UNION_FIELD:
2154 /* Check if the selected member of the union is the one we want
2155 * (the one specified in field_path), and if not this object is
2156 * considered as NULL in the sort/filter. */
2157 if (*(const uint16_t *)*data != step->u.union_tag) {
2158 if (err) {
2159 sb_setf(err, "invalid union tag, expected %u, got %u",
2160 step->u.union_tag, *(const uint16_t *)*data);
2161
2162 }
2163 return IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET;
2164 }
2165 break;
2166
2167 case FIELD_STEP_TYPE_GOTO_INDEX: {
2168 const i8__array_t *array = *data;
2169 ssize_t index = step->u.index;
2170
2171 if (index < 0) {
2172 /* Negative index: array[-1] is the last element of 'array'.
2173 */
2174 index = array->len + index;
2175 }
2176 if (index >= array->len || index < 0) {
2177 if (err) {
2178 sb_setf(err, "index %zd out of range for array of length %d",
2179 index, array->len);
2180 }
2181 return IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET;
2182 }
2183
2184 *data = array->tab + index * step->array_element_sz;
2185 } break;
2186
2187 case FIELD_STEP_TYPE_OBJ_CAST: {
2188 const iop_struct_t *real_st = *(const iop_struct_t **)*data;
2189
2190 if (!iop_class_is_a(real_st, step->u.subclass_st)) {
2191 if (err) {
2192 sb_setf(err, "invalid type of object, expected a sub-class "
2193 "of `%*pM`, got `%*pM`",
2194 LSTR_FMT_ARG(step->u.subclass_st->fullname),
2195 LSTR_FMT_ARG(real_st->fullname));
2196 }
2197 return IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET;
2198 }
2199 } break;
2200
2201 case FIELD_STEP_TYPE_SCAN_ARRAY:
2202 if (err) {
2203 sb_sets(err, "cannot use wildcard indexing with dynamic class "
2204 "cast, use explicit class cast instead");
2205 }
2206 return IOP_FIELD_ERROR;
2207 }
2208
2209 return 0;
2210}
2211
2212/* Get the field(s) associated to a field path for a given IOP
2213 * struct/class/union either with a callback. */
2214static iop_value_from_field_res_t
2215iop_field_path_run(const iop_field_path_t *nonnull field_path,
2216 const void *nonnull data, int step_offset,
2217 iop_ptr_cb_b nonnull on_value)
2218{
2219 const iop_field_t *fdesc = field_path->fdesc;
2220
2221 for (int i = step_offset; i < field_path->steps.len; i++) {
2222 const field_step_t *step = &field_path->steps.tab[i];
2223
2224 switch (step->type) {
2225 case FIELD_STEP_TYPE_SCAN_ARRAY: {
2226 const i8__array_t *array = data;
2227
2228 data = array->tab;
2229 tab_for_each_pos(j, array) {
2230 iop_value_from_field_res_t res;
2231
2232 res = iop_field_path_run(field_path, data, i + 1, on_value);
2233 THROW_ERR_IF(res == IOP_FIELD_ERROR);
2234 data = (const byte *)data + step->array_element_sz;
2235 }
2236
2237 return 0;
2238 } break;
2239
2240 default:
2241 RETHROW(field_step_run(step, &data, NULL));
2242 break;
2243 }
2244 }
2245
2246 if (field_path->is_typename) {
2247 const iop_struct_t *st = *(const void **)data;
2248
2249 data = &st->fullname;
2250 } else
2251 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
2252 if (!field_path->is_array_element && !field_path->is_array_len) {
2253 const i8__array_t *array = data;
2254
2255 THROW_IF(!array->len, IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET);
2256 }
2257 } else
2258 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL && iop_type_is_scalar(fdesc->type)) {
2259 data = iop_opt_field_getv_const(fdesc->type, data);
2260 THROW_IF(!data, IOP_FIELD_NOT_SET);
2261 }
2262
2263 if (on_value(data) < 0) {
2264 return IOP_FIELD_ERROR;
2265 }
2266 return 0;
2267}
2268
2269static int iop_get_fieldp(const void *nonnull data,
2270 const iop_field_path_t *nonnull field_path,
2271 const void **nonnull value)
2272{
2273 _Bool found = false;
2274 _Bool *found_ptr = &found;
2275
2276 iop_field_path_run(field_path, data, 0, ^int (const void *field_ptr) {
2277 *found_ptr = true;
2278 *value = field_ptr;
2279 /* Stop the scan when the first value has been found. */
2280 return -1;
2281 });
2282 THROW_ERR_UNLESS(found);
2283 return 0;
2284}
2285
2286/* }}} */
2287/* {{{ Compile */
2288
2289static int
2290field_step_fast_forward(qv_t(field_step) *nonnull steps,
2291 int *nonnull step_offset, const void **nonnull value,
2292 sb_t *nullable err)
2293{
2294 while (*step_offset < steps->len) {
2295 if (field_step_run(&steps->tab[*step_offset], value, err) < 0) {
2296 *value = NULL;
2297 return -1;
2298 }
2299 (*step_offset)++;
2300 }
2301 return 0;
2302}
2303
2304static int
2305iop_compile_field_path(const iop_struct_t *st, lstr_t field_path_s,
2306 const void *nullable value, iop_field_path_t *fp,
2307 sb_t *nullable err)
2308{
2309 const iop_field_t *fdesc = NULL;
2310 pstream_t field_path_ps = ps_initlstr(&field_path_s);
2311 const iop_struct_t *it = st;
2312 field_step_t *step;
2313 bool step_is_array_element = false;
2314 int step_offset = 0;
2315
2316 /* Don't use the same field path twice. */
2317 assert (!fp->steps.len);
2318
2319 if (ps_done(&field_path_ps)) {
2320 if (err) {
2321 sb_adds(err, "cannot process empty field path");
2322 }
2323 return -1;
2324 }
2325
2326 step = NULL;
2327 while (!ps_done(&field_path_ps)) {
2328 iop_field_path_parse_t field_parse;
2329
2330 RETHROW(parse_field_from_path(&field_path_ps, it, &field_parse,
2331 err));
2332
2333 if (field_parse.cast_st) {
2334 it = field_parse.cast_st;
2335 step = field_step_init(qv_growlen(&fp->steps, 1));
2336 step->type = FIELD_STEP_TYPE_OBJ_CAST;
2337 step->u.subclass_st = it;
2338 }
2339
2340 if (ps_strequal(&field_parse.field_name, "_class")) {
2341 if (!iop_struct_is_class(it)) {
2342 if (err) {
2343 sb_adds(err,
2344 "cannot fetch typename of a non-class field");
2345 }
2346 return -1;
2347 }
2348 if (!ps_done(&field_path_ps)) {
2349 if (err) {
2350 sb_adds(err, "cannot fetch subfield of a typename");
2351 }
2352 return -1;
2353 }
2354 fp->is_typename = true;
2355 break;
2356 }
2357
2358 if (iop_field_find_by_name(it, LSTR_PS_V(&field_parse.field_name),
2359 NULL, &fdesc) < 0)
2360 {
2361 if (value && iop_struct_is_class(it)) {
2362 /* Go through the path built until now. If the value is
2363 * properly resolved, get the real type instead of the parent
2364 * type, and try to resolve the field name with that real
2365 * type. */
2366 if (field_step_fast_forward(&fp->steps, &step_offset, &value,
2367 err) < 0)
2368 {
2369 if (err) {
2370 sb_prependf(err, "the path up to the field `%*pM` is "
2371 "not valid for the provided value: ",
2372 PS_FMT_ARG(&field_parse.field_name));
2373 }
2374 return -1;
2375 }
2376 it = *(const iop_struct_t **)value;
2377
2378 assert(!field_parse.cast_st ||
2379 iop_class_is_a(it, field_parse.cast_st));
2380
2381 if (iop_field_find_by_name(it,
2382 LSTR_PS_V(&field_parse.field_name),
2383 &it, &fdesc) >= 0)
2384 {
2385 step = field_step_init(qv_growlen(&fp->steps, 1));
2386 step->type = FIELD_STEP_TYPE_OBJ_CAST;
2387 step->u.subclass_st = it;
2388 goto valid_field;
2389 }
2390 }
2391 if (err) {
2392 sb_addf(err, "cannot process field path `%*pM', "
2393 "field `%*pM' is unknown in structure `%*pM'",
2394 LSTR_FMT_ARG(field_path_s),
2395 PS_FMT_ARG(&field_parse.field_name),
2396 LSTR_FMT_ARG(it->fullname));
2397 }
2398 return -1;
2399 }
2400
2401 valid_field:
2402 if (it->is_union) {
2403 step = field_step_init(qv_growlen(&fp->steps, 1));
2404 step->type = FIELD_STEP_TYPE_UNION_FIELD;
2405 step->u.union_tag = fdesc->tag;
2406 }
2407 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED &&
2408 !OPT_ISSET(field_parse.array_index) &&
2409 lstr_equal(LSTR_PS_V(&field_path_ps), LSTR("len")))
2410 {
2411 ps_skip_upto(&field_path_ps, ps_end(&field_path_ps));
2412
2413 /* Length of arrays containing values of repeated fields can be
2414 * accessed with '.len'. */
2415 fp->is_array_len = true;
2416 }
2417 if (ps_done(&field_path_ps)) {
2418 fp->fdesc = fdesc;
2419 }
2420
2421 if (fdesc->data_offs || fp->is_array_len) {
2422 if (!step || step->type != FIELD_STEP_TYPE_MOVE) {
2423 step = field_step_init(qv_growlen(&fp->steps, 1));
2424 step->type = FIELD_STEP_TYPE_MOVE;
2425 }
2426 step->u.offset += fdesc->data_offs;
2427
2428 if (fp->is_array_len) {
2429 /* Position the pointer on the array length. */
2430 step->u.offset += offsetof(i8__array_t, len);
2431
2432 return 0;
2433 }
2434 }
2435
2436 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
2437 if (field_parse.wildcard || OPT_ISSET(field_parse.array_index)) {
2438 step = field_step_init(qv_growlen(&fp->steps, 1));
2439 step->array_element_sz = fdesc->size;
2440
2441 if (field_parse.wildcard) {
2442 step->type = FIELD_STEP_TYPE_SCAN_ARRAY;
2443 } else {
2444 step->type = FIELD_STEP_TYPE_GOTO_INDEX;
2445 step->u.index = OPT_VAL(field_parse.array_index);
2446 }
2447 step_is_array_element = true;
2448 if (ps_done(&field_path_ps)) {
2449 fp->is_array_element = true;
2450 }
2451 } else
2452 if (!ps_done(&field_path_ps)) {
2453 if (err) {
2454 sb_addf(err, "cannot process field path `%*pM', "
2455 "field `%*pM' is repeated in structure `%*pM'",
2456 LSTR_FMT_ARG(field_path_s),
2457 PS_FMT_ARG(&field_parse.field_name),
2458 LSTR_FMT_ARG(it->fullname));
2459 }
2460 return -1;
2461 }
2462 } else
2463 if (OPT_ISSET(field_parse.array_index)) {
2464 if (err) {
2465 sb_addf(err, "got index but field `%*pM:%*pM' "
2466 "is not repeated", LSTR_FMT_ARG(it->fullname),
2467 PS_FMT_ARG(&field_parse.field_name));
2468 }
2469 return -1;
2470 }
2471
2472 /* We need an indirection if we reference an element that is pointed.
2473 * We should not do the indirection if we target the array itself and
2474 * not its elements.
2475 */
2476 if ((fdesc->type == IOP_T_STRUCT || fdesc->type == IOP_T_UNION) &&
2477 (fdesc->repeat != IOP_R_REPEATED || step_is_array_element))
2478 {
2479 it = fdesc->u1.st_desc;
2480
2481 if (iop_field_is_pointed(fdesc)) {
2482 step = field_step_init(qv_growlen(&fp->steps, 1));
2483 step->type = FIELD_STEP_TYPE_INDIRECTION;
2484 }
2485 }
2486 }
2487
2488 return 0;
2489}
2490
2491/* }}} */
2492/* {{{ IOP field path public API */
2493
2494const iop_field_path_t *nullable
2495mp_iop_field_path_compile(mem_pool_t *nullable mp,
2496 const iop_struct_t *nonnull st, lstr_t path,
2497 sb_t *nullable err)
2498{
2499 iop_field_path_t *fp;
2500
2501 fp = mp_iop_field_path_init(mp, mp_new_raw(mp, iop_field_path_t, 1));
2502 RETHROW_NP(iop_compile_field_path(st, path, NULL, fp, err));
2503 return fp;
2504}
2505
2506void
2507mp_iop_field_path_delete(mem_pool_t *nullable mp,
2508 const iop_field_path_t *nullable *nonnull fp_ptr)
2509{
2510 if (*fp_ptr) {
2511 iop_field_path_t **fp_ptr_mut = (iop_field_path_t **)fp_ptr;
2512
2513 iop_field_path_wipe(*fp_ptr_mut);
2514 mp_delete(mp, fp_ptr_mut);
2515 }
2516}
2517
2518void iop_field_path_get_type(const iop_field_path_t *nonnull fp,
2519 iop_full_type_t *nonnull type,
2520 bool *nonnull is_array)
2521{
2522 if (fp->is_typename) {
2523 *type = IOP_FTYPE_STRING;
2524 *is_array = false;
2525 } else
2526 if (fp->is_array_len) {
2527 *type = IOP_FTYPE_I32;
2528 *is_array = false;
2529 } else {
2530 p_clear(type, 1);
2531 type->type = fp->fdesc->type;
2532 if (type->type == IOP_T_ENUM) {
2533 type->en = fp->fdesc->u1.en_desc;
2534 } else
2535 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(type->type)) {
2536 type->st = fp->fdesc->u1.st_desc;
2537 }
2538 if (fp->is_array_element) {
2539 *is_array = false;
2540 } else {
2541 *is_array = fp->fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED;
2542 }
2543 }
2544}
2545
2546int iop_field_path_for_each_value(const iop_field_path_t *nonnull fp,
2547 const void *nonnull st_ptr,
2548 iop_ptr_cb_b nonnull on_value)
2549{
2550 THROW_ERR_IF(iop_field_path_run(fp, st_ptr, 0, on_value) ==
2551 IOP_FIELD_ERROR);
2552 return 0;
2553}
2554
2555int iop_obj_get_field_type(const iop_struct_t *nonnull st,
2556 const void *nonnull value, lstr_t path,
2557 iop_full_type_t *nonnull type,
2558 bool *nonnull is_array, sb_t *nullable err)
2559{
2560 t_scope;
2561 iop_field_path_t *fp;
2562
2563 fp = t_iop_field_path_init(t_new_raw(iop_field_path_t, 1));
2564 RETHROW(iop_compile_field_path(st, path, value, fp, err));
2565
2566 iop_field_path_get_type(fp, type, is_array);
2567 return 0;
2568}

2570/* }}} */
2571/* }}} */
2572/* {{{ cmp functions */
2573
2574static cmp_f iop_get_cmp_fun(iop_type_t type)
2575{
2576 switch (type) {
2577 case IOP_T_I8:
2578 return &cmp_i8;
2579 case IOP_T_U8:
2580 return &cmp_u8;
2581 case IOP_T_I16:
2582 return &cmp_i16;
2583 case IOP_T_U16:
2584 return &cmp_u16;
2585 case IOP_T_ENUM:
2586 return &cmp_i32;
2587 case IOP_T_I32:
2588 return &cmp_i32;
2589 case IOP_T_U32:
2590 return &cmp_u32;
2591 case IOP_T_I64:
2592 return &cmp_i64;
2593 case IOP_T_U64:
2594 return &cmp_u64;
2595 case IOP_T_BOOL:
2596 return &cmp_bool;
2597 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
2598 return &cmp_double;
2599 case IOP_T_UNION:
2600 return &cmp_u16; /* XXX: we compare the union tag. */
2601 case IOP_T_STRING:
2602 return &cmp_lstr_iutf8;
2603 case IOP_T_XML:
2604 return &cmp_lstr_iutf8;
2605 case IOP_T_DATA:
2606 return &cmp_lstr_bin;
2607 case IOP_T_VOID:
2608 return NULL; /* XXX: cmp func is get but never called for void */
2609
2610 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
2611 break;
2612 }
2613 e_panic("iop_type unsupported");
2614}
2615
2616/*}}}*/
2617/* {{{ equality functions */
2618
2619/* Equality functions must return 0 if values are equal and another value of
2620 * values are different. */
2621
2622static int iop_string_sql_like(const void *s1, const void *s2)
2623{
2624 return lstr_utf8_is_ilike(*(const lstr_t *)s1,
2625 *(const lstr_t *)s2) ? 0 : -1;
2626}
2627
2628static cmp_f iop_get_equal_fun_sql_like(iop_type_t type)
2629{
2630 if (type == IOP_T_STRING) {
2631 return &iop_string_sql_like;
2632 }
2633
2634 return iop_get_cmp_fun(type);
2635}
2636
2637/*}}}*/
2638/* {{{ iop_msort */
2639
2640typedef struct iop_sort_priv_t {
2641 iop_field_path_t fp;
2642 int flags;
2643} iop_sort_priv_t;
2644
2645qvector_t(iop_sort_p, iop_sort_priv_t);
2646
2647static int
2648iop_cmp_value(iop_type_t ftype, const iop_struct_t *nullable st_desc,
2649 size_t fsize, iop_repeat_t repeat, bool need_indirection,
2650 const void *nonnull r1, const void *nonnull r2);
2651
2652static int
2653compare_field(const void *d1, const void *d2, const iop_sort_priv_t *priv)
2654{
2655 bool d1_is_set = iop_get_fieldp(d1, &priv->fp, &d1) >= 0;
2656 bool d2_is_set = iop_get_fieldp(d2, &priv->fp, &d2) >= 0;
2657 int res;
2658
2659 if (!d1_is_set && !d2_is_set) {
2660 return 0;
2661 }
2662 if (!d1_is_set) {
2663 return (priv->flags & IOP_SORT_NULL_FIRST) ? -1 : 1;
2664 }
2665 if (!d2_is_set) {
2666 return (priv->flags & IOP_SORT_NULL_FIRST) ? 1 : -1;
2667 }
2668 if (d1 == d2) {
2669 return 0;
2670 }
2671
2672 if (priv->fp.is_typename) {
2673 res = lstr_utf8_icmp(*(lstr_t *)d1, *(lstr_t *)d2);
2674 } else
2675 if (priv->fp.is_array_len) {
2676 res = CMP(*(int *)d1, *(int *)d2);
2677 } else {
2678 const iop_field_t *fdesc = priv->fp.fdesc;
2679 iop_repeat_t repeat;
2680 const iop_struct_t *st_desc = NULL;
2681 bool need_indirection = false;
2682
2683 repeat = fdesc->repeat;
2684 if (repeat != IOP_R_REPEATED || priv->fp.is_array_element) {
2685 /* XXX iop_get_fieldp() already did whatever is necessary to get a
2686 * proper field pointer. */
2687 repeat = IOP_R_REQUIRED;
2688 }
2689
2690 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(fdesc->type)) {
2691 st_desc = fdesc->u1.st_desc;
2692
2693 if (repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
2694 /* XXX We only need indirection on arrays of objects. In other
2695 * cases, 'iop_get_fieldp()' always give a simple pointer on
2696 * the targeted field. */
2697 /* XXX We check whether the fdesc is a reference in case
2698 * arrays of references become an IOP feature. */
2699 need_indirection = iop_struct_is_class(st_desc) ||
2700 iop_field_is_reference(fdesc);
2701 }
2702 }
2703
2704 res = iop_cmp_value(fdesc->type, st_desc, fdesc->size, repeat,
2705 need_indirection, d1, d2);
2706 }
2707
2708 return priv->flags & IOP_SORT_REVERSE ? -res : res;
2709}
2710
2711int iop_msort_desc(const iop_struct_t *st, void *vec, int len,
2712 const qv_t(iop_sort) *params, sb_t *err)
2713{
2714 t_scope;
2715 bool is_class = iop_struct_is_class(st);
2716 qv_t(iop_sort_p) sorts;
2717
2718 if (unlikely(params->len == 0)) {
2719 return 0;
2720 }
2721
2722 t_qv_init(&sorts, params->len);
2723 qv_growlen(&sorts, params->len);
2724
2725 tab_enumerate_ptr(pos, sort, params) {
2726 iop_sort_priv_t *priv = &sorts.tab[pos];
2727
2728 t_iop_field_path_init(&priv->fp);
2729 RETHROW(iop_compile_field_path(st, sort->field_path, NULL, &priv->fp,
2730 err));
2731
2732 if (priv->fp.fdesc
2733 && priv->fp.fdesc->type == IOP_T_VOID
2734 && priv->fp.fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REQUIRED)
2735 {
2736 if (err) {
2737 sb_addf(err, "cannot sort on void required field `%*pM'",
2738 LSTR_FMT_ARG(sort->field_path));
2739 }
2740 return -1;
2741 }
2742
2743 priv->flags = sort->flags;
2744 }
2745
2746 __qv_sort(vec, is_class ? sizeof(void *) : st->size, len,
2747 ^int (const void *d1, const void *d2) {
2748 const qv_t(iop_sort_p) *_sorts = &sorts;
2749
2750 if (is_class) {
2751 d1 = *(void **)d1;
2752 d2 = *(void **)d2;
2753 }
2754
2755 tab_for_each_ptr(sort, _sorts) {
2756 int ret = compare_field(d1, d2, sort);
2757
2758 if (ret) {
2759 return ret;
2760 }
2761 }
2762 return 0;
2763 });
2764
2765 return 0;
2766}
2767
2768int iop_sort_desc(const iop_struct_t *st, void *vec, int len,
2769 lstr_t field_path, int flags, sb_t *err)
2770{
2771 qv_t(iop_sort) params;
2772 iop_sort_t param = {
2773 .field_path = field_path,
2774 .flags = flags,
2775 };
2776
2777 qv_init_static(&params, &param, 1);
2778 return iop_msort_desc(st, vec, len, &params, err);
2779}
2780
2781/* }}} */
2782/* {{{ IOP arbitrary sorting function */
2783
2784#define CMP_RETHROW(expr) \
2785 do { \
2786 int __cmp_res = (expr); \
2787 THROW_IF(__cmp_res, __cmp_res); \
2788 } while (0)
2789
2790static int __iop_cmp(const iop_struct_t *st, const void *v1, const void *v2);
2791
2792static int
2793iop_cmp_value(iop_type_t ftype, const iop_struct_t *nullable st_desc,
2794 size_t fsize, iop_repeat_t repeat, bool need_indirection,
2795 const void *nonnull r1, const void *nonnull r2)
2796{
2797 int n = 1;
2798 int n1 = 1;
2799 int n2 = 1;
2800
2801 if (repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
2802 /* Here we just check the length of the repeated field, then we
2803 * position our pointers on values to compare them later. */
2804 n1 = ((iop_array_u8_t *)r1)->len;
2805 n2 = ((iop_array_u8_t *)r2)->len;
2806 r1 = ((iop_array_u8_t *)r1)->tab;
2807 r2 = ((iop_array_u8_t *)r2)->tab;
2808 n = MIN(n1, n2);
2809 } else
2810 if (repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
2811 /* Optional blocks types cannot be compared using a single memcmp
2812 * we need to handle absent values first. */
2813 bool has = iop_opt_field_isset(ftype, r1);
2814
2815 CMP_RETHROW(CMP(has, iop_opt_field_isset(ftype, r2)));
2816 if (!has) {
2817 return 0;
2818 }
2819 }
2820
2821 if (ftype == IOP_T_VOID) {
2822 /* Two void fields are always equal if present. */
2823 return 0;
2824 } else {
2825 cmp_f cmp_scalar = st_desc ? NULL : iop_get_cmp_fun(ftype);
2826 const uint8_t *p1 = r1;
2827 const uint8_t *p2 = r2;
2828
2829 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
2830 if (st_desc) {
2831 /* We need to recurse to compare structures & unions. */
2832 CMP_RETHROW(iop_cmp_desc(st_desc,
2833 need_indirection ? *(void **)p1 : p1,
2834 need_indirection ? *(void **)p2 : p2));
2835 } else {
2836 CMP_RETHROW(cmp_scalar(p1, p2));
2837 }
2838 p1 += fsize;
2839 p2 += fsize;
2840 }
2841 }
2842
2843 CMP_RETHROW(CMP(n1, n2));
2844
2845 return 0;
2846}
2847
2848int iop_cmp_field(const iop_field_t *nonnull fdesc,
2849 const void *nonnull st1, const void *nonnull st2)
2850{
2851 const void *r1 = (const uint8_t *)st1 + fdesc->data_offs;
2852 const void *r2 = (const uint8_t *)st2 + fdesc->data_offs;
2853 const iop_struct_t *st_desc = NULL;
2854
2855 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(fdesc->type)) {
2856 st_desc = fdesc->u1.st_desc;
2857 }
2858
2859 return iop_cmp_value(fdesc->type, st_desc, fdesc->size, fdesc->repeat,
2860 iop_field_is_pointed(fdesc), r1, r2);
2861}
2862
2863static int
2864__iop_cmp(const iop_struct_t *st, const void *v1, const void *v2)
2865{
2866 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
2867 const iop_field_t *end;
2868
2869 THROW_IF(v1 == v2, 0);
2870
2871 if (st->is_union) {
2872 int tag_v1 = RETHROW(iop_union_get_tag(st, v1));
2873 int tag_v2 = RETHROW(iop_union_get_tag(st, v2));
2874
2875 fdesc = get_union_field(st, v1);
2876 if (tag_v1 != tag_v2) {
2877 const iop_field_t *f2;
2878
2879 f2 = get_union_field(st, v2);
2880 /* TODO Flag to compare tag only. */
2881 CMP_RETHROW(lstr_utf8_icmp(fdesc->name, f2->name));
2882 assert (false);
2883
2884 return CMP(tag_v1, tag_v2);
2885 }
2886 end = fdesc + 1;
2887 } else {
2888 fdesc = st->fields;
2889 end = fdesc + st->fields_len;
2890 }
2891
2892 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
2893 CMP_RETHROW(iop_cmp_field(fdesc, v1, v2));
2894 }
2895
2896 return 0;
2897}
2898
2899int iop_cmp_desc(const iop_struct_t *st, const void *v1, const void *v2)
2900{
2901 if (!v1 || !v2) {
2902 return st->size ? CMP(v1, v2) : 0;
2903 }
2904
2905 if (iop_struct_is_class(st)) {
2906 const iop_struct_t *st2 = *(const iop_struct_t **)v2;
2907
2908 st = *(const iop_struct_t **)v1;
2909 if (st != st2) {
2910 /* TODO Have a flag to compare class IDs instead. */
2911 CMP_RETHROW(lstr_utf8_icmp(st->fullname, st2->fullname));
2912 assert (false);
2913
2914 return CMP(st, st2);
2915 }
2916
2917 do {
2918 CMP_RETHROW(__iop_cmp(st, v1, v2));
2919 } while ((st = st->class_attrs->parent));
2920
2921 return 0;
2922 }
2923
2924 return __iop_cmp(st, v1, v2);
2925}
2926
2927#undef CMP_RETHROW
2928
2929static void
2930__iop_xsort_desc(const iop_struct_t *st, void *vec, int len, bool pointed)
2931{
2932 __qv_sort(vec, pointed ? sizeof(void *) : st->size, len,
2933 ^int (const void *d1, const void *d2) {
2934 if (pointed) {
2935 d1 = *(void **)d1;
2936 d2 = *(void **)d2;
2937 }
2938
2939 return iop_cmp_desc(st, d1, d2);
2940 });
2941}
2942
2943void iop_xsort_desc(const iop_struct_t *st, void *vec, int len)
2944{
2945 __iop_xsort_desc(st, vec, len, iop_struct_is_class(st));
2946}
2947
2948void iop_xpsort_desc(const iop_struct_t *st, const void **vec, int len)
2949{
2950 __iop_xsort_desc(st, vec, len, true);
2951}

2953/* }}} */

2955/* }}} */
2956/* {{{ Filtering values */
2957
2958static bool iop_filter_is_value_in_array(const void *val,
2959 void * const * values, int len,
2960 cmp_f equal)
2961{
2962 /* TODO: sort values and use a bisection. */
2963 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
2964 if (equal(val, values[i]) == 0) {
2965 return true;
2966 }
2967 }
2968 return false;
2969}
2970
2971static bool iop_filter_val_matches(const byte *vec_read,
2972 const iop_field_path_t *fp,
2973 bool is_pointer, opt_bool_t is_set,
2974 unsigned flags, void * const *values,
2975 int len, cmp_f equal)
2976{
2977 bool val_is_set;
2978 const void *tmp;
2979 const void *val;
2980 bool val_match_res;
2981
2982 tmp = is_pointer ? *(void **)vec_read : vec_read;
2983 val_is_set = iop_get_fieldp(tmp, fp, &val) >= 0;
2984
2985 if (OPT_ISSET(is_set)) {
2986 return val_is_set == OPT_VAL(is_set);
2987 }
2988
2989 val_match_res = !(flags & IOP_FILTER_INVERT_MATCH);
2990
2991 if (!val_is_set) {
2992 return !val_match_res;
2993 }
2994
2995 if (fp->fdesc && fp->fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED
2996 && !fp->is_array_len && !fp->is_array_element)
2997 {
2998 const iop_array_i8_t *array = val;
2999
3000 for (int i = 0; i < array->len; i++) {
3001 val = (const char *)array->tab + i * fp->fdesc->size;
3002
3003 if (iop_filter_is_value_in_array(val, values, len, equal)) {
3004 return val_match_res;
3005 }
3006 }
3007 } else {
3008 if (iop_filter_is_value_in_array(val, values, len, equal)) {
3009 return val_match_res;
3010 }
3011 }
3012
3013 return !val_match_res;
3014}
3015
3016static int
3017__t_iop_filter(const iop_struct_t *st, const void *vec, int len,
3018 lstr_t field_path, void * const *values,
3019 int values_len, opt_bool_t is_set, unsigned flags,
3020 iop_filter_bitmap_op_t bitmap_op, byte **bitmap, sb_t *err)
3021{
3022 bool is_pointer = iop_struct_is_class(st);
3023 iop_field_path_t fp;
3024 cmp_f equal = NULL;
3025 const byte *vec_read = vec;
3026 size_t elem_size = is_pointer ? sizeof(void *) : st->size;
3027
3028 t_iop_field_path_init(&fp);
3029 RETHROW(iop_compile_field_path(st, field_path, NULL, &fp, err));
3030 assert (fp.is_typename || fp.fdesc);
3031
3032 if (OPT_ISSET(is_set)) {
3033 assert (!values_len);
3034 if (!fp.is_typename && !fp.is_array_len
3035 && fp.fdesc->repeat != IOP_R_OPTIONAL
3036 && fp.fdesc->repeat != IOP_R_REPEATED)
3037 {
3038 if (err) {
3039 sb_addf(err, "field `%*pM' in the structure `%*pM' is "
3040 "neither optional nor repeated",
3041 LSTR_FMT_ARG(field_path), LSTR_FMT_ARG(st->fullname));
3042 }
3043 return -1;
3044 }
3045 } else {
3046 iop_type_t type;
3047
3048 if (fp.is_typename) {
3049 type = IOP_T_STRING;
3050 } else
3051 if (fp.is_array_len) {
3052 type = IOP_T_I32;
3053 } else {
3054 if (fp.fdesc->type == IOP_T_STRUCT) {
3055 if (err) {
3056 sb_addf(err, "cannot filter on sub-structure `%*pM'",
3057 LSTR_FMT_ARG(field_path));
3058 }
3059 return -1;
3060 }
3061 if (fp.fdesc->type == IOP_T_VOID) {
3062 if (err) {
3063 sb_addf(err, "cannot filter on void field `%*pM'",
3064 LSTR_FMT_ARG(field_path));
3065 }
3066 return -1;
3067 }
3068 type = fp.fdesc->type;
3069 }
3070
3071 if (flags & IOP_FILTER_SQL_LIKE) {
3072 equal = iop_get_equal_fun_sql_like(type);
3073 } else {
3074 equal = iop_get_cmp_fun(type);
3075 }
3076 }
3077
3078 if (!*bitmap) {
3079 *bitmap = t_new(byte, BITS_TO_ARRAY_LEN(byte, len));
3080 bitmap_op = BITMAP_OP_OR;
3081 }
3082
3083 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
3084 switch (bitmap_op) {
3085#define VAL_MATCHES() \
3086 iop_filter_val_matches(vec_read, &fp, is_pointer, is_set, \
3087 flags, values, values_len, equal)
3088
3089 case BITMAP_OP_AND:
3090 if (TST_BIT(*bitmap, i) && !VAL_MATCHES()) {
3091 RST_BIT(*bitmap, i);
3092 }
3093 break;
3094
3095 case BITMAP_OP_OR:
3096 if (!TST_BIT(*bitmap, i) && VAL_MATCHES()) {
3097 SET_BIT(*bitmap, i);
3098 }
3099 break;
3100
3101#undef VAL_MATCHES
3102 }
3103
3104 vec_read += elem_size;
3105 }
3106
3107 return 0;
3108}
3109
3110int iop_filter(const iop_struct_t *st, void *vec, int *len, lstr_t field_path,
3111 void * const *values, int values_len, unsigned flags,
3112 sb_t *err)
3113{
3114 t_scope;
3115 byte *bitmap = NULL;
3116
3117 RETHROW(t_iop_filter_bitmap(st, vec, *len, field_path,
3118 values, values_len, flags,
3119 BITMAP_OP_OR, &bitmap, err));
3120 iop_filter_bitmap_apply(st, vec, len, bitmap);
3121 return 0;
3122}
3123
3124int iop_filter_opt(const iop_struct_t *st, void *vec, int *len,
3125 lstr_t field_path, bool is_set, sb_t *err)
3126{
3127 t_scope;
3128 byte *bitmap = NULL;
3129
3130 RETHROW(t_iop_filter_opt_bitmap(st, vec, *len, field_path,
3131 is_set, BITMAP_OP_AND, &bitmap, err));
3132 iop_filter_bitmap_apply(st, vec, len, bitmap);
3133 return 0;
3134}
3135
3136int t_iop_filter_bitmap(const iop_struct_t *st, const void *vec, int len,
3137 lstr_t field_path, void * const *values,
3138 int values_len, unsigned flags,
3139 iop_filter_bitmap_op_t bitmap_op, byte **bitmap,

3141{

3145}
3146
3147int t_iop_filter_opt_bitmap(const iop_struct_t *st, const void *vec, int len,
3148 lstr_t field_path, bool is_set,
3149 iop_filter_bitmap_op_t bitmap_op, byte **bitmap,
