3155
3156void iop_filter_bitmap_apply(const iop_struct_t *st, void *vec, int *len,
3157 const byte *bitmap)
3158{
3159 bool is_pointer = iop_struct_is_class(st);
3160 size_t elem_size = is_pointer ? sizeof(void *) : st->size;
3161 const byte *vec_read = vec;
3162 const byte *vec_start = vec;
3163 byte *vec_write = vec;
3164
3165 for (int i = 0; i < *len; i++) {
3166 if (!TST_BIT(bitmap, i)) {
3167 if (vec_start != vec_read && vec_write != vec_read) {
3168 p_move(vec_write, vec_start, vec_read - vec_start);
3169 }
3170 vec_write += vec_read - vec_start;
3171 vec_start = vec_read + elem_size;
3172 }
3173
3174 vec_read += elem_size;
3175 }
3176
3177 if (vec_start != vec_read && vec_write != vec_read) {
3178 p_move(vec_write, vec_start, vec_read - vec_start);
3179 vec_write += vec_read - vec_start;
3180 }
3181 assert (elem_size > 0);
3182 *len = (vec_write - (byte *)vec) / elem_size;
3183}
3184
3185/* }}} */
3186/* {{{ Hashing values */
3187
3188#define ATTRS
3189#define F(x) x
3190#include "hashing-values.in.c"
3191#undef F
3192#undef ATTRS

3197typedef struct iop_err_t {
3198 sb_t err;

3200 const iop_struct_t *desc;
3201} iop_err_t;

3204
3205__attribute__((constructor))
3206static void iop_init_err(void)
3207{
3208 if (unlikely(iop_err_g.err.size == 0)) {
3209 p_clear(&iop_err_g, 1);
3210 sb_init(&iop_err_g.err);
3211 sb_init(&iop_err_g.path);
3212 }
3213}
3214
3215static void iop_wipe_err(void)
3216{
3217 if (iop_err_g.err.size) {
3218 sb_wipe(&iop_err_g.err);
3219 sb_wipe(&iop_err_g.path);
3220 iop_err_g.desc = NULL;
3221 }
3222}
3223
3224thr_hooks(iop_init_err, iop_wipe_err);

3227{

3229}

3236 iop_set_verr(fmt, ap);

3253
3254static void iop_expand_err(void)
3255{
3256 if (!iop_err_g.desc) {
3257 return;
3258 }
3259 if (iop_err_g.path.len) {
3260 sb_prependf(&iop_err_g.err, "in %s of type %s: ",
3261 iop_err_g.path.data + 1, iop_err_g.desc->fullname.s);
3262 } else {
3263 sb_prependf(&iop_err_g.err, "in type %s: ",
3264 iop_err_g.desc->fullname.s);
3265 }
3266 iop_err_g.desc = NULL;
3267}

3270{

3272 iop_expand_err();

3274 }
3275 return NULL;
3276}

3279{

3281 iop_expand_err();

3283 }
3284 return LSTR_NULL_V;
3285}
3286
3287static int
3288__iop_check_constraints_struct(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val);
3289static int
3290__iop_check_constraints_class(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val);
3291
3292__cold static void sb_prepend_field(sb_t *sb, const iop_field_t *fdesc, int j)
3293{
3294 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
3295 sb_prependf(sb, ".%s[%d]", fdesc->name.s, j);
3296 } else {
3297 sb_prependf(sb, ".%s", fdesc->name.s);
3298 }
3299}
3300
3301static const char *t_fmt_field(const iop_field_t *fdesc, int j)
3302{
3303 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
3304 return t_fmt("%s[%d]", fdesc->name.s, j);
3305 } else {
3306 return fdesc->name.s;
3307 }
3308}
3309
3310int iop_field_check_constraints(const iop_struct_t *desc, const iop_field_t
3311 *fdesc, const void *ptr, int n, bool recurse)
3312{
3313 check_constraints_f *check_constraints = NULL;
3314
3315 if ((check_constraints = iop_field_get_constraints_cb(desc, fdesc))) {
3316 if (unlikely(check_constraints(ptr, n) < 0)) {
3317 iop_err_g.desc = desc;
3318 sb_reset(&iop_err_g.path);
3319 return -1;
3320 }
3321 }
3322 switch (fdesc->type) {
3323 case IOP_T_ENUM:
3324 if (TST_BIT(&fdesc->u1.en_desc->flags, IOP_ENUM_STRICT)) {
3325 const iop_enum_t *en_desc = fdesc->u1.en_desc;
3326
3327 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
3328 int32_t intval = IOP_FIELD(int32_t, ptr, j);
3329
3330 if (iop_ranges_search(en_desc->ranges,
3331 en_desc->ranges_len, intval) != -1)
3332 {
3333 continue;
3334 } else {
3335 t_scope;
3336
3337 iop_err_g.desc = desc;
3338 sb_reset(&iop_err_g.path);
3339 iop_set_err("%d is not a valid value for enum %*pM"
3340 " (field %s)",
3341 intval, LSTR_FMT_ARG(en_desc->fullname),
3342 t_fmt_field(fdesc, j));
3343 return -1;
3344 }
3345 }
3346 }
3347 break;
3348
3349 case IOP_T_I8:
3350 case IOP_T_U8:
3351 case IOP_T_I16:
3352 case IOP_T_U16:
3353 case IOP_T_I32:
3354 case IOP_T_U32:
3355 case IOP_T_I64:
3356 case IOP_T_U64:
3357 case IOP_T_BOOL:
3358 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
3359 case IOP_T_STRING:
3360 case IOP_T_DATA:
3361 case IOP_T_XML:
3362 case IOP_T_VOID:
3363 break;
3364
3365 case IOP_T_UNION:
3366 case IOP_T_STRUCT: {
3367 bool is_class;
3368 bool is_ref;
3369
3370 if (!recurse) {
3371 return 0;
3372 }
3373
3374 is_class = iop_field_is_class(fdesc);
3375 is_ref = iop_field_is_reference(fdesc);
3376 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
3377 int ret;
3378 const void *v = &IOP_FIELD(const char, ptr, j * fdesc->size);
3379
3380 if ((is_class || is_ref) && fdesc->repeat != IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
3381 /* Non-optional class fields have to be dereferenced
3382 * (dereferencing of optional fields was already done
3383 * by the caller).
3384 */
3385 v = *(void **)v;
3386 }
3387 if (is_class) {
3388 ret = __iop_check_constraints_class(fdesc->u1.st_desc, v);
3389 } else {
3390 ret = __iop_check_constraints_struct(fdesc->u1.st_desc, v);
3391 }
3392 if (ret < 0) {
3393 sb_prepend_field(&iop_err_g.path, fdesc, j);
3394 return -1;
3395 }
3396 }
3397 break;
3398 }
3399 }
3400
3401 return 0;
3402}
3403
3404static int
3405__iop_check_constraints_struct(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val)
3406{
3407 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
3408 const iop_field_t *end;
3409 unsigned desc_flags = desc->flags;
3410
3411 if (!TST_BIT(&desc_flags, IOP_STRUCT_HAS_CONSTRAINTS))
3412 return 0;
3413
3414 if (desc->is_union) {
3415 fdesc = get_union_field(desc, val);
3416 end = fdesc + 1;
3417 } else {
3418 fdesc = desc->fields;
3419 end = fdesc + desc->fields_len;
3420 }
3421
3422 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
3423 const void *ptr = (char *)val + fdesc->data_offs;
3424 int n = 1;
3425
3426 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
3427 if (!iop_opt_field_isset(fdesc->type, ptr)) {
3428 continue;
3429 }
3430 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK) {
3431 ptr = *(void **)ptr;
3432 }
3433 } else
3434 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
3435 n = ((lstr_t *)ptr)->len;
3436 ptr = ((lstr_t *)ptr)->data;
3437 if (n == 0) {
3438 unsigned fdesc_flags = fdesc->flags;
3439
3440 if (TST_BIT(&fdesc_flags, IOP_FIELD_NO_EMPTY_ARRAY)) {
3441 iop_err_g.desc = desc;
3442 sb_reset(&iop_err_g.path);
3443 iop_set_err("empty array not allowed for field `%*pM`",
3444 LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name));
3445 return -1;
3446 }
3447 continue;
3448 }
3449 } else
3450 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_DEFVAL) {
3451 /* Skip the field if it's still equal to its default value */
3452 if (iop_field_is_defval(fdesc, ptr, true))
3453 continue;
3454 }
3455
3456 RETHROW(iop_field_check_constraints(desc, fdesc, ptr, n, true));
3457 }
3458
3459 return 0;
3460}
3461
3462static int
3463__iop_check_constraints_class(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val)
3464{
3465 desc = *(const iop_struct_t **)val;
3466
3467 if (unlikely(desc->class_attrs->is_abstract)) {
3468 iop_err_g.desc = desc;
3469 sb_reset(&iop_err_g.path);
3470 return iop_set_err("'%*pM' is an abstract class",
3471 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
3472 }
3473
3474 do {
3475 RETHROW(__iop_check_constraints_struct(desc, val));
3476 } while ((desc = desc->class_attrs->parent));
3477
3478 return 0;
3479}
3480
3481int iop_check_constraints_desc(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val)
3482{
3483 int ret;
3484
3485 if (iop_struct_is_class(desc)) {
3486 ret = __iop_check_constraints_class(desc, val);
3487 } else {
3488 ret = __iop_check_constraints_struct(desc, val);
3489 }
3490 return ret;
3491}
3492
3493/* }}} */
3494/* {{{ Get value encoding size */
3495
3496void iop_bpack_set_threaded_threshold(size_t threshold)
3497{
3498 /* XXX: Repeated fields having at least threaded_pack_threshold elements
3499 * will be packed using multi-threading (if thread jobs are enabled).
3500 * It must be at least 2 because one-element arrays are handled in a
3501 * specific way that prevents the multi-threaded path to work (and anyway,
3502 * this would be useless). */
3503 if (!expect(threshold >= 2)) {
3504 return;
3505 }
3506
3507 _G.threaded_pack_threshold = threshold;
3508}
3509
3510static bool
3511iop_bpack_is_threadable(const iop_field_t *fdesc, int flags, size_t n)
3512{
3513 return ((fdesc->type == IOP_T_STRUCT || fdesc->type == IOP_T_UNION)
3514 && fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED
3515 && !(flags & IOP_BPACK_MONOTHREAD)
3516 && module_is_loaded(MODULE(thr))
3517 && thr_parallelism_g > 1
3518 && n >= _G.threaded_pack_threshold);
3519}
3520
3521static int __iop_bpack_size_class(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val,
3522 const unsigned flags, qv_t(i32) *szs,
3523 bool in_thread);
3524static void iop_bpack_size_struct_union_job(thr_job_t *job, thr_syn_t *syn);
3525static void iop_bpack_size_class_job(thr_job_t *job, thr_syn_t *syn);
3526
3527typedef struct pack_size_job_t {
3528 thr_job_t job;
3529 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
3530 const void *v;
3531 unsigned flags;
3532 int32_t n;
3533 int chunk_id;
3534} pack_size_job_t;
3535
3536typedef struct pack_size_res_t {
3537 int32_t packed_len;
3538 qv_t(i32) szs;
3539 int chunk_id;
3540} pack_size_res_t;
3541qvector_t(pack_size_res, pack_size_res_t);
3542
3543typedef struct pack_size_td_t {
3544 thr_td_t td;
3545 qv_t(pack_size_res) res;
3546} pack_size_td_t;
3547
3548static int get_chunk_count(size_t n)
3549{
3550 /* chunks of size 200 provide a good performance improvement
3551 * on 4 and 16 cores machines */
3552 size_t chunks = DIV_ROUND_UP(n, 200);
3553
3554 /* at least 1, at most 3 times the processors */
3555 return CLIP(chunks, MIN(thr_parallelism_g, n), thr_parallelism_g * 3);
3556}
3557
3558static int __iop_bpack_size_threaded(const iop_field_t *fdesc,
3559 const void *val, const unsigned flags,
3560 int n, qv_t(i32) *szs)
3561{
3562 pack_size_job_t *jobs;
3563 thr_syn_t syn;
3564 __block int len = 0;
3565 __block size_t szs_len_blk = 0;
3566 size_t szs_len;
3567 qv_t(pack_size_res) res;
3568 int chunks_packed_size_offs, chunks_szs_offs;
3569 unsigned chunk_size;
3570 int chunk_remainder;
3571 int n_count = 0;
3572 bool is_class = iop_field_is_class(fdesc);
3573
3574 int chunks = get_chunk_count(n);
3575
3576 jobs = p_new(pack_size_job_t, chunks);
3577 qv_init(&res);
3578 qv_growlen(&res, chunks);
3579
3580 /* Chunk metadata is added between the array length and the element sizes.
3581 *
3582 * ╔══════════════════════════════╗ -----------------------------
3583 * ║ array len ║ present in mono packing
3584 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ -----------------------------
3585 * ║ chunk count = n ║
3586 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ added for multi-threaded
3587 * ║ chunk 0 offset in this array ║ ═══╗ packing
3588 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║
3589 * ║ ... ║ ║
3590 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║
3591 * ║ chunk n offset in this array ║ ═══╬═══╗
3592 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║ ║
3593 * ║ chunk 0 packed size ║ ║ ║
3594 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║ ║
3595 * ║ ... ║ ║ ║
3596 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║ ║
3597 * ║ chunk n packed size ║ ║ ║
3598 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║ ║ -----------------------------
3599 * ║ size of array element 0 ║<═══╝ ║
3600 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║ present in mono packing
3601 * ║ ... ║ ║
3602 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║
3603 * ║ ... ║ ║
3604 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣ ║
3605 * ║ size of array element N ║<═══════╝ (N = n * chunk size)
3606 * ╠══════════════════════════════╣
3607 * ║ size of array element N+1 ║
3608 * ╚══════════════════════════════╝ -----------------------------
3609 */
3610 qv_growlen(szs, 1);
3611 szs->tab[szs->len - 1] = chunks;
3612 chunks_packed_size_offs = szs->len;
3613 qv_growlen(szs, chunks);
3614 chunks_szs_offs = szs->len;
3615 qv_growlen(szs, chunks);
3616 chunk_size = n / chunks;
3617 chunk_remainder = n % chunks;
3618
3619 thr_syn_init(&syn);
3620 thr_syn_declare_td(&syn, ^{
3621 pack_size_td_t *td = p_new(pack_size_td_t, 1);
3622
3623 qv_init(&td->res);
3624 return &td->td;
3625 }, ^(thr_td_t **ptd) {
3626 pack_size_td_t *r;
3627
3628 r = container_of(*ptd, pack_size_td_t, td);
3629 qv_wipe(&r->res);
3630 p_delete(ptd);
3631 });
3632
3633 /* chunks are handled manually (instead of thr_for_each)
3634 * because we need to retrieve and store chunk infos
3635 * (packed size and szs len) for packing. */
3636 for (int i = 0; i < chunks; i++) {
3637 pack_size_job_t *job = &jobs[i];
3638
3639 if (is_class) {
3640 job->job.run = iop_bpack_size_class_job;
3641 } else {
3642 job->job.run = iop_bpack_size_struct_union_job;
3643 }
3644 job->fdesc = fdesc;
3645 job->n = i < chunk_remainder ? chunk_size + 1 : chunk_size;
3646 job->flags = flags;
3647 job->v = (byte *)val + (n_count * fdesc->size);
3648 job->chunk_id = i;
3649 thr_syn_schedule(&syn, &job->job);
3650 n_count += job->n;
3651 }
3652 thr_syn_wait(&syn);
3653
3654 /* each td contains 1-n results, which need to be
3655 * put in order before inserting in szs */
3656 thr_syn_collect_td(&syn, ^(const thr_td_t *td) {
3657 const pack_size_td_t *r;
3658
3659 r = container_of(td, const pack_size_td_t, td);
3660 tab_for_each_ptr(e, &r->res) {
3661 res.tab[e->chunk_id] = *e;
3662 len += e->packed_len;
3663 szs_len_blk += e->szs.len;
3664 }
3665 });
3666
3667 /* cannot use the __block variable in qv_grow macro */
3668 szs_len = szs_len_blk;
3669 qv_grow(szs, szs_len);
3670 for (int i = 0; i < res.len; i++) {
3671 szs->tab[chunks_szs_offs + i] = res.tab[i].packed_len;
3672 szs->tab[chunks_packed_size_offs + i] =
3673 szs->len - chunks_packed_size_offs;
3674 qv_extend_tab(szs, &res.tab[i].szs);
3675 qv_wipe(&res.tab[i].szs);
3676 }
3677 thr_syn_wipe(&syn);
3678 qv_wipe(&res);
3679 p_delete(&jobs);
3680 /* XXX: substract n because we already added it in
3681 * __iop_bpack_size when we found an IOP_R_REPEATED. */
3682 return len - n;
3683}
3684
3685static int __iop_bpack_size(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val,
3686 const unsigned flags, qv_t(i32) *szs,
3687 bool in_thread)
3688{
3689 const iop_field_t *fdesc;
3690 const iop_field_t *end;
3691 int len = 0;
3692
3693 if (desc->is_union) {
3694 fdesc = get_union_field(desc, val);
3695 end = fdesc + 1;
3696 } else {
3697 fdesc = desc->fields;
3698 end = fdesc + desc->fields_len;
3699 }
3700
3701 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
3702 const void *ptr = (char *)val + fdesc->data_offs;
3703 int n = 1;
3704
3705 if (flags & IOP_BPACK_SKIP_PRIVATE) {
3706 const iop_field_attrs_t *attrs = iop_field_get_attrs(desc, fdesc);
3707
3708 if (attrs && TST_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_PRIVATE)) {
3709 continue;
3710 }
3711 }
3712
3713 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
3714 if (!iop_opt_field_isset(fdesc->type, ptr)) {
3715 continue;
3716 }
3717 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK) {
3718 ptr = *(void **)ptr;
3719 }
3720 } else
3721 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
3722 n = ((lstr_t *)ptr)->len;
3723 ptr = ((lstr_t *)ptr)->data;
3724 if (n == 0)
3725 continue;
3726 if (n > 1) {
3727 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_REPEATED_OPTIMIZE_OK) {
3728 int32_t i32 = n * fdesc->size;
3729
3730 len += 1 + fdesc->tag_len;
3731 len += get_len_len(i32) + i32;
3732 continue;
3733 }
3734 /* Add:
3735 * - 4 to encode the len on 32 bits,
3736 * - n because there will be n tags 0 to separate elements.
3737 */
3738 len += 4 + n;
3739 }
3740 } else
3741 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_DEFVAL) {
3742 /* Skip the field if still equals to its default value */
3743 if ((flags & IOP_BPACK_SKIP_DEFVAL)
3744 && iop_field_is_defval(fdesc, ptr, true))
3745 {
3746 continue;
3747 }
3748 }
3749
3750 len += 1 + fdesc->tag_len;
3751 switch (fdesc->type) {
3752 case IOP_T_I8:
3753 len += n;
3754 break;
3755 case IOP_T_U8:
3756 len += n;
3757 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
3758 len += IOP_FIELD(uint8_t, ptr, j) >> 7;
3759 break;
3760 case IOP_T_I16:
3761 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
3762 len += get_vint32_len(IOP_FIELD(int16_t, ptr, j));
3763 break;
3764 case IOP_T_U16:
3765 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
3766 len += get_vint32_len(IOP_FIELD(uint16_t, ptr, j));
3767 break;
3768 case IOP_T_I32:
3769 case IOP_T_ENUM:
3770 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
3771 len += get_vint32_len(IOP_FIELD(int32_t, ptr, j));
3772 break;
3773 case IOP_T_U32:
3774 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
3775 len += get_vint64_len(IOP_FIELD(uint32_t, ptr, j));
3776 break;
3777 case IOP_T_I64:
3778 case IOP_T_U64:
3779 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
3780 len += get_vint64_len(IOP_FIELD(int64_t, ptr, j));
3781 break;
3782 case IOP_T_BOOL:
3783 len += n;
3784 break;
3785 case IOP_T_VOID:
3786 if (desc->is_union || fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
3787 assert (n == 1);
3788 len += 1;
3789 } else {
3790 /* mandatory void in structs are not packed, remove tag_len */
3791 len -= (1 + fdesc->tag_len);
3792 }
3793 break;
3794 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
3795 len += n * 8;
3796 break;
3797 case IOP_T_STRING:
3798 case IOP_T_DATA:
3799 case IOP_T_XML:
3800 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
3801 int32_t i32 = IOP_FIELD(lstr_t, ptr, j).len;
3802 len += get_len_len(i32 + 1) + i32 + 1;
3803 }
3804 break;
3805
3806 case IOP_T_UNION:
3807 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
3808 default: {
3809 bool is_class = iop_field_is_class(fdesc);
3810 bool is_ref = iop_field_is_reference(fdesc);
3811 bool threadable = iop_bpack_is_threadable(fdesc, flags, n);
3812
3813 /* do not multi thread packing of an array if we are already
3814 * multithreading, to avoid recursive thr_syn_wait() that can
3815 * cause a thread explosion */
3816 if (threadable && !in_thread) {
3817 len += __iop_bpack_size_threaded(fdesc, ptr, flags, n, szs);
3818 break;
3819 }
3820 for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
3821 const void *v = &IOP_FIELD(const char, ptr, j * fdesc->size);
3822 int32_t offs = szs->len;
3823 int32_t i32;
3824
3825 qv_growlen(szs, 1);
3826
3827 if ((is_class || is_ref) && fdesc->repeat != IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
3828 /* Non-optional class fields have to be dereferenced
3829 * (dereferencing of optional fields was already done
3830 * just above).
3831 */
3832 v = *(void **)v;
3833 }
3834 if (is_class) {
3835 i32 = __iop_bpack_size_class(fdesc->u1.st_desc, v, flags,
3836 szs, in_thread);
3837 } else {
3838 i32 = __iop_bpack_size(fdesc->u1.st_desc, v, flags, szs,
3839 in_thread);
3840 }
3841
3842 szs->tab[offs] = i32;
3843 len += get_len_len(i32) + i32;
3844
3845 }
3846 break;
3847 }
3848 }
3849 }
3850
3851 return len;
3852}
3853
3854/* "in_thread" argument is set to true to avoid thread explosions */
3855#define bpack_size_struct_union(st_desc, v, flags, szsp) \
3856 __iop_bpack_size(st_desc, v, flags, szsp, true);
3857#define bpack_size_class(st_desc, v, flags, szsp) \
3858 __iop_bpack_size_class(st_desc, *(void **)v, flags, &szs, true);
3859
3860#define GEN_PACK_SIZE_JOB(type) \
3861static void \
3862iop_bpack_size_##type##_job(thr_job_t *job, thr_syn_t *syn) \
3863{ \
3864 pack_size_job_t *pj = (pack_size_job_t *)job; \
3865 qv_t(i32) szs; \
3866 int chunk_len = 0; \
3867 pack_size_td_t *td; \
3868 int n = pj->n; \
3869 const iop_struct_t *st_desc = pj->fdesc->u1.st_desc; \
3870 uint32_t flags = pj->flags; \
3871 const void *orig_v = pj->v; \
3872 int fdesc_size = pj->fdesc->size; \
3873 \
3874 qv_init(&szs); \
3875 qv_grow(&szs, 1024); /* arbitrary could use some heuristics */ \
3876 \
3877 for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { \
3878 const void *v = &IOP_FIELD(const char, orig_v, i * fdesc_size); \
3879 int32_t offs = szs.len, i32; \
3880 \
3881 qv_growlen(&szs, 1); \
3882 i32 = bpack_size_##type (st_desc, v, flags, &szs); \
3883 \
3884 szs.tab[offs] = i32; \
3885 chunk_len += get_len_len(i32) + i32 + 1; \
3886 } \
3887 \
3888 /* write result to td */ \
3889 td = container_of(thr_syn_acquire_td(syn), pack_size_td_t, td); \
3890 qv_growlen(&td->res, 1); \
3891 td->res.tab[td->res.len - 1].szs = szs; \
3892 td->res.tab[td->res.len - 1].packed_len = chunk_len; \
3893 td->res.tab[td->res.len - 1].chunk_id = pj->chunk_id; \
3894 thr_syn_release_td(syn, &td->td); \
3895}
3896
3897GEN_PACK_SIZE_JOB(class)
3898GEN_PACK_SIZE_JOB(struct_union)
3899#undef bpack_size_struct_union
3900#undef bpack_size_class
3901#undef GEN_PACK_SIZE_JOB
3902
3903static int __iop_bpack_size_class(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val,
3904 const unsigned flags, qv_t(i32) *szs,
3905 bool in_thread)
3906{
3907 int size = 0, level_size;
3908 bool first = true;
3909
3910 desc = *(const iop_struct_t **)val;
3911
3912 e_assert(panic, !desc->class_attrs->is_abstract,
3913 "packing of abstract class '%*pM' is forbidden",
3914 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
3915
3916 /* If this assert fails, you are exporting private classes through
3917 * a public interface... this is BAD!
3918 */
3919 assert (!desc->class_attrs->is_private
3920 || !(flags & IOP_BPACK_SKIP_PRIVATE));
3921
3922 do {
3923 int szs_pos = szs->len;
3924
3925 qv_growlen(szs, 1);
3926 level_size = __iop_bpack_size(desc, val, flags, szs, in_thread);
3927 szs->tab[szs_pos] = level_size;
3928 size += level_size;
3929 if (first || level_size) {
3930 /* Add 1 for tag 0, followed by the class id */
3931 size += 1 + get_vint32_len(desc->class_attrs->class_id);
3932 first = false;
3933 }
3934 } while ((desc = desc->class_attrs->parent));
3935
3936 return size;
3937}
3938
3939int iop_bpack_size_flags(const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *val,
3940 const unsigned flags, qv_t(i32) *szs)
3941{
3942 if (flags & IOP_BPACK_STRICT) {
3943 RETHROW(iop_check_constraints_desc(desc, val));
3944 }
3945
3946 /* Put the packer flags in first to reuse them when packing */
3947 qv_append(szs, flags);
3948
3949 if (iop_struct_is_class(desc)) {
3950 return __iop_bpack_size_class(desc, val, flags, szs, false);
3951 } else {
3952 return __iop_bpack_size(desc, val, flags, szs, false);
3953 }
3954}
3955
3956/* }}} */
3957/* {{{ Packing */
3958
3959static uint8_t *pack_struct(void *dst, const iop_struct_t *, const void *,
3960 const unsigned, const int **, bool in_thread);
3961static uint8_t *pack_class(void *dst, const iop_struct_t *, const void *,
3962 const unsigned, const int **, bool in_thread);
3963static uint8_t *pack_union(void *dst, const iop_struct_t *, const void *,
3964 const unsigned, const int **, bool in_thread);
3965
3966static uint8_t *
3967pack_value(uint8_t *dst, const iop_struct_t *desc, const iop_field_t *f,
3968 const void *v, const unsigned flags, const int **szsp,
3969 bool in_thread)
3970{
3971 uint32_t len;
3972
3973 switch (f->type) {
3974 case IOP_T_I8:
3975 dst = pack_tag(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, IOP_WIRE_MASK(INT1));
3976 *dst++ = *(int8_t *)v;
3977 return dst;
3978 case IOP_T_U8:
3979 return pack_int32(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, *(uint8_t *)v);
3980 case IOP_T_I16:
3981 return pack_int32(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, *(int16_t *)v);
3982 case IOP_T_U16:
3983 return pack_int32(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, *(uint16_t *)v);
3984 case IOP_T_I32:
3985 case IOP_T_ENUM:
3986 return pack_int32(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, *(int32_t *)v);
3987 case IOP_T_U32:
3988 return pack_int64(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, *(uint32_t *)v);
3989 case IOP_T_I64:
3990 case IOP_T_U64:
3991 return pack_int64(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, *(int64_t *)v);
3992 case IOP_T_BOOL:
3993 /* bool are mapped to 0 or 1 */
3994 assert (*(uint8_t *)v == 0 || *(uint8_t *)v == 1);
3995 dst = pack_tag(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, IOP_WIRE_MASK(INT1));
3996 /* XXX: cast in uint8_t because casting in bool would have no effect.
3997 */
3998 *dst++ = !!*(uint8_t *)v;
3999 return dst;
4000 case IOP_T_VOID:
4001 /* Do not pack required void in structs */
4002 if (desc->is_union || f->repeat != IOP_R_REQUIRED) {
4003 /* void types do not contain any value, but the wire format
4004 * requires we send at least one byte of data with the tag. */
4005 return pack_len(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, 0);
4006 }
4007 return dst;
4008 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
4009 dst = pack_tag(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, IOP_WIRE_MASK(QUAD));
4010 return put_unaligned_double_le(dst, *(double *)v);
4011 case IOP_T_STRING:
4012 case IOP_T_DATA:
4013 case IOP_T_XML:
4014 len = ((lstr_t *)v)->len;
4015 dst = pack_len(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, len + 1);
4016 dst = mempcpyz(dst, ((lstr_t *)v)->data, len);
4017 return dst;
4018 case IOP_T_UNION:
4019 if (iop_field_is_reference(f)) {
4020 v = *(void **)v;
4021 }
4022 dst = pack_len(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, *(*szsp)++);
4023 return pack_union(dst, f->u1.st_desc, v, flags, szsp, in_thread);
4024 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
4025 default: {
4026 bool is_class = iop_field_is_class(f);
4027 bool is_ref = iop_field_is_reference(f);
4028
4029 dst = pack_len(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, *(*szsp)++);
4030 if ((is_class || is_ref) && f->repeat != IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
4031 /* Non-optional class fields have to be dereferenced
4032 * (dereferencing of optional fields was done in pack_struct).
4033 */
4034 v = *(void **)v;
4035 }
4036 if (is_class) {
4037 return pack_class(dst, f->u1.st_desc, v, flags, szsp, in_thread);
4038 } else {
4039 return pack_struct(dst, f->u1.st_desc, v, flags, szsp, in_thread);
4040 }
4041 }
4042 }
4043}
4044
4045typedef struct pack_job_t {
4046 thr_job_t job;
4047 uint8_t *dst;
4048 const iop_field_t *f;
4049 const void *v;
4050 uint32_t n;
4051 unsigned flags;
4052 const int *szs;
4053 bool is_class;
4054 bool last_chunk;
4055} pack_job_t;
4056
4057typedef struct pack_td_t {
4058 thr_td_t td;
4059 const void *v;
4060 const int *szs;
4061 uint8_t *dst;
4062} pack_td_t;
4063
4064#define _pack_class(dst, st_desc, v, flags, szs) \
4065 pack_class(dst, st_desc, *(void **)v, flags, szs, true)
4066#define _pack_union(dst, st_desc, v, flags, szs) \
4067 pack_union(dst, st_desc, v, flags, szs, true)
4068#define _pack_struct(dst, st_desc, v, flags, szs) \
4069 pack_struct(dst, st_desc, v, flags, szs, true)
4070
4071#define GEN_PACK_JOB(type) \
4072static void pack_value_vec_##type##_job(thr_job_t *job, thr_syn_t *syn) \
4073{ \
4074 pack_job_t *pj = (pack_job_t *)job; \
4075 uint32_t n = pj->n; \
4076 uint8_t *dst = pj->dst; \
4077 const iop_struct_t *st_desc = pj->f->u1.st_desc; \
4078 const void *v = pj->v; \
4079 unsigned flags = pj->flags; \
4080 const int *szs = pj->szs; \
4081 const int fsize = pj->f->size; \
4082 \
4083 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < n; i++) { \
4084 dst = pack_len(dst, 0, 0, *(szs++)); \
4085 dst = _pack_##type(dst, st_desc, v, flags, &szs); \
4086 v = (const byte *)v + fsize; \
4087 } \
4088 \
4089 if (pj->last_chunk) { \
4090 pack_td_t *td = container_of(thr_syn_acquire_td(syn), pack_td_t, td);\
4091 td->v = v; \
4092 td->szs = szs; \
4093 td->dst = dst; \
4094 thr_syn_release_td(syn, &td->td); \
4095 } \
4096}
4097
4098GEN_PACK_JOB(class);
4099GEN_PACK_JOB(struct);
4100GEN_PACK_JOB(union);
4101
4102#undef _pack_class
4103#undef _pack_struct
4104#undef _pack_union
4105#undef GEN_PACK_JOB
4106
4107static uint8_t *
4108pack_value_vec_threaded(uint8_t *dst, const iop_field_t *f, const void *v,
4109 uint32_t n, const unsigned flags, const int **szsp)
4110{
4111 pack_job_t *jobs;
4112 thr_syn_t syn;
4113 __block uint8_t *dst_res = dst;
4114 int32_t *len_chunks;
4115 bool is_class = iop_field_is_class(f);
4116 int chunks = *(*szsp)++;
4117 int chunk_size = n / chunks;
4118 int chunk_remainder = n % chunks;
4119 int n_count = 0;
4120
4121 jobs = p_new(pack_job_t, chunks);
4122 len_chunks = p_new(int32_t, chunks);
4123
4124 thr_syn_init(&syn);
4125 thr_syn_declare_td(&syn, ^{
4126 pack_td_t *td = p_new(pack_td_t, 1);
4127 return &td->td;
4128 }, ^(thr_td_t **ptd) {
4129 p_delete(ptd);
4130 });
4131
4132 for (int i = 0; i < chunks; i++) {
4133 int32_t offs;
4134 pack_job_t *job = &jobs[i];
4135
4136 /* get relative offset of chunk in szs */
4137 offs = *((*szsp) + i);
4138 /* get chunk packed size from metadata in szs */
4139 len_chunks[i] = *((*szsp) + i + chunks);
4140
4141 job->szs = (*szsp) + offs;
4142 /* chunk output ptr = previous chunk output ptr
4143 * + packed size of previous chunk */
4144 job->dst = i == 0 ? dst : jobs[i - 1].dst + len_chunks[i - 1];
4145 job->f = f;
4146 /* last chunk may has remainder elements */
4147 job->n = i < chunk_remainder ? chunk_size + 1 : chunk_size;
4148 job->v = (byte *)v + (n_count * f->size);
4149 job->flags = flags;
4150 switch (f->type) {
4151 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
4152 if (is_class) {
4153 job->job.run = pack_value_vec_class_job;
4154 } else {
4155 job->job.run = pack_value_vec_struct_job;
4156 }
4157 break;
4158 case IOP_T_UNION:
4159 job->job.run = pack_value_vec_union_job;
4160 break;
4161 default:
4162 assert (false);
4163 break;
4164 }
4165 job->last_chunk = i == chunks - 1;
4166 thr_syn_schedule(&syn, &job->job);
4167 n_count += job->n;
4168 }
4169 *szsp += chunks;
4170
4171 thr_syn_wait(&syn);
4172 thr_syn_collect_td(&syn, ^(const thr_td_t *td) {
4173 const pack_td_t *r = container_of(td, const pack_td_t, td);
4174
4175 *szsp = r->szs;
4176 dst_res = r->dst;
4177 });
4178 thr_syn_wipe(&syn);
4179
4180 p_delete(&jobs);
4181 p_delete(&len_chunks);
4182
4183 return dst_res;
4184}
4185
4186static uint8_t *
4187pack_value_vec(uint8_t *dst, const iop_field_t *f, const void *v, uint32_t n,
4188 const unsigned flags, const int **szsp, bool in_thread)
4189{
4190 const lstr_t *d;
4191 uint32_t len;
4192 bool is_class;
4193
4194 /* do not multi thread packing of an array if we are already
4195 * multithreading, to avoid recursive thr_syn_wait() that can
4196 * cause a thread explosion */
4197 if (iop_bpack_is_threadable(f, flags, n) && !in_thread) {
4198 return pack_value_vec_threaded(dst, f, v, n, flags, szsp);
4199 }
4200
4201 switch (f->type) {
4202 case IOP_T_I32:
4203 case IOP_T_ENUM:
4204 do {
4205 dst = pack_int32(dst, 0, 0, *(int32_t *)v);
4206 v = (char *)v + 4;
4207 } while (--n > 0);
4208 return dst;
4209 case IOP_T_U32:
4210 do {
4211 dst = pack_int64(dst, 0, 0, *(uint32_t *)v);
4212 v = (char *)v + 4;
4213 } while (--n > 0);
4214 return dst;
4215 case IOP_T_I64:
4216 case IOP_T_U64:
4217 do {
4218 dst = pack_int64(dst, 0, 0, *(int64_t *)v);
4219 v = (char *)v + 8;
4220 } while (--n > 0);
4221 return dst;
4222 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
4223 do {
4224 dst = pack_tag(dst, 0, 0, IOP_WIRE_MASK(QUAD));
4225 dst = put_unaligned_double_le(dst, *(double *)v);
4226 v = (char *)v + 8;
4227 } while (--n > 0);
4228 return dst;
4229 case IOP_T_STRING:
4230 case IOP_T_DATA:
4231 case IOP_T_XML:
4232 do {
4233 d = v;
4234 len = d->len;
4235 dst = pack_len(dst, 0, 0, len + 1);
4236 dst = mempcpyz(dst, d->data, len);
4237 v = (char *)v + f->size;
4238 } while (--n > 0);
4239 return dst;
4240 case IOP_T_UNION:
4241 do {
4242 dst = pack_len(dst, 0, 0, *(*szsp)++);
4243 dst = pack_union(dst, f->u1.st_desc, v, flags, szsp, in_thread);
4244 v = (char *)v + f->size;
4245 } while (--n > 0);
4246 return dst;
4247 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
4248 is_class = iop_field_is_class(f);
4249 do {
4250 dst = pack_len(dst, 0, 0, *(*szsp)++);
4251 if (is_class) {
4252 dst = pack_class(dst, f->u1.st_desc, *(void **)v, flags,
4253 szsp, in_thread);
4254 } else {
4255 dst = pack_struct(dst, f->u1.st_desc, v, flags, szsp,
4256 in_thread);
4257 }
4258 v = (char *)v + f->size;
4259 } while (--n > 0);
4260 return dst;
4261 default:
4262 e_panic("should not happen");
4263 }
4264}
4265
4266static uint8_t *
4267pack_struct(void *dst, const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *v,
4268 const unsigned flags, const int **szsp, bool in_thread)
4269{
4270 assert(!desc->is_union); /* We don't want a union here */
4271
4272 for (int i = 0; i < desc->fields_len; i++) {
4273 const iop_field_t *f = desc->fields + i;
4274 const void *ptr = (char *)v + f->data_offs;
4275
4276 if (flags & IOP_BPACK_SKIP_PRIVATE) {
4277 const iop_field_attrs_t *attrs = iop_field_get_attrs(desc, f);
4278
4279 if (attrs && TST_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_PRIVATE)) {
4280 continue;
4281 }
4282 }
4283
4284 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL) {
4285 if (!iop_opt_field_isset(f->type, ptr)) {
4286 continue;
4287 }
4288 if ((1 << f->type) & IOP_STRUCTS_OK) {
4289 ptr = *(void **)ptr;
4290 }
4291 } else
4292 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
4293 const lstr_t *data = ptr;
4294
4295 if (data->len == 0)
4296 continue;
4297 ptr = data->data;
4298 if (data->len > 1) {
4299 if ((1 << f->type) & IOP_REPEATED_OPTIMIZE_OK) {
4300 /* When data unit is really small (byte, bool, …) we
4301 * prefer to pack them in one big block */
4302 uint32_t sz = data->len * f->size;
4303
4304 assert (f->size <= 2);
4305 dst = pack_len(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len, sz);
4306 dst = mempcpy(dst, data->data, sz);
4307 } else {
4308 dst = pack_tag(dst, f->tag, f->tag_len,
4309 IOP_WIRE_MASK(REPEAT));
4310 dst = put_unaligned_le32(dst, data->len);
4311 dst = pack_value_vec(dst, f, ptr, data->len, flags, szsp,
4312 in_thread);
4313 }
4314 continue;
4315 }
4316 } else
4317 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_DEFVAL) {
4318 /* Skip the field if it's still equal to its default value */
4319 if ((flags & IOP_BPACK_SKIP_DEFVAL)
4320 && iop_field_is_defval(f, ptr, true))
4321 {
4322 continue;
4323 }
4324 }
4325
4326 dst = pack_value(dst, desc, f, ptr, flags, szsp, in_thread);
4327 }
4328 return dst;
4329}
4330
4331static uint8_t *pack_class(void *dst, const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *v,
4332 const unsigned flags, const int **szsp,
4333 bool in_thread)
4334{
4335 bool first = true;
4336
4337 desc = *(const iop_struct_t **)v;
4338
4339 do {
4340 int level_size = *(*szsp)++;
4341
4342 if (first || level_size) {
4343 /* We write the class id in a tag 0 only if:
4344 * - this is the first level, because we always want to write the
4345 * real class id of the packed object,
4346 * - if there is actually something to pack.
4347 */
4348 dst = pack_int32(dst, 0, 0, desc->class_attrs->class_id);
4349 first = false;
4350 }
4351 if (level_size) {
4352 dst = pack_struct(dst, desc, v, flags, szsp, in_thread);
4353 }
4354 } while ((desc = desc->class_attrs->parent));
4355
4356 return dst;
4357}
4358
4359static uint8_t *
4360pack_union(void *dst, const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *v,
4361 const unsigned flags, const int **szsp, bool in_thread)
4362{
4363 const iop_field_t *f = get_union_field(desc, v);
4364
4365 return pack_value(dst, desc, f, (char *)v + f->data_offs, flags, szsp,
4366 in_thread);
4367}
4368
4369void iop_bpack(void *dst, const iop_struct_t *desc, const void *v,
4370 const int *szs)
4371{
4372 /* Read packing flags from first `szs' value */
4373 const unsigned flags = *szs++;
4374
4375 if (desc->is_union) {
4376 pack_union(dst, desc, v, flags, &szs, false);
4377 } else
4378 if (iop_struct_is_class(desc)) {
4379 pack_class(dst, desc, v, flags, &szs, false);
4380 } else {
4381 pack_struct(dst, desc, v, flags, &szs, false);
4382 }
4383}
4384
4385lstr_t mp_iop_bpack_struct_flags(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *st,
4386 const void *v, const unsigned flags)
4387{
4388 qv_t(i32) sizes;
4389 byte *data;
4390 int len;
4391
4392 if (!v) {
4393 return LSTR_NULL_V;
4394 }
4395 qv_inita(&sizes, 1024);
4396
4397 len = iop_bpack_size_flags(st, v, flags, &sizes);
4398 if (len < 0) {
4399 qv_wipe(&sizes);
4400 return LSTR_NULL_V;
4401 }
4402 data = mp_new_raw(mp, byte, len + 1);
4403 data[len] = '\0';
4404
4405 iop_bpack(data, st, v, sizes.tab);
4406 qv_wipe(&sizes);
4407 return mp_lstr_init(mp, data, len);
4408}
4409
4410lstr_t t_iop_bpack_struct_flags(const iop_struct_t *st, const void *v,
4411 const unsigned flags)
4412{
4413 return mp_iop_bpack_struct_flags(t_pool(), st, v, flags);
4414}

4416/* }}} */

4418
4419static int iop_union_get_data_offset(const iop_struct_t *nonnull desc)
4420{
4421 int size = desc->size;
4422
4423 assert (desc->is_union);
4424
4425 for (int i = 0; i < desc->fields_len; i++) {
4426 uint16_t offs = desc->fields[i].data_offs;
4427
4428 if (offs) {
4429 return offs;
4430 }
4431 }
4432
4433 return size;
4434}
4435
4436void iop_union_set_tag(const iop_struct_t *nonnull desc, int value,
4437 void *nonnull st)
4438{
4439 switch (iop_union_get_data_offset(desc)) {
4440 case 1:
4441 *(uint8_t *)st = (uint8_t)value;
4442 break;
4443 case 2:
4444 *(uint16_t *)st = (uint16_t)value;
4445 break;
4446 case 4:
4447 case 8:
4448 *(uint32_t *)st = (uint32_t)value;
4449 break;
4450 default:
4451 assert (false);
4452 }
4453}
4454
4455int iop_union_get_tag(const iop_struct_t *nonnull desc,
4456 const void *nonnull st)
4457{
4458 switch (iop_union_get_data_offset(desc)) {
4459 case 1:
4460 return *(uint8_t *)st;
4461 case 2:
4462 case 4:
4463 case 8:
4464 return *(uint16_t *)st;
4465 default:
4466 assert (false);
4467 return -1;
4468 }
4469}
4470
4471static inline int get_uint32(pstream_t *ps, int ilen, uint32_t *u32)
4472{
4473 switch (ilen) {
4474 case 1:
4475 *u32 = RETHROW(ps_getc(ps));
4476 return 0;
4477
4478 case 2: {
4479 uint16_t u16 = 0;
4480 RETHROW(ps_get_le16(ps, &u16));
4481 *u32 = u16;
4482 } return 0;
4483
4484 case 4:
4485 return ps_get_le32(ps, u32);
4486 }
4487 e_panic("this should not happen");
4488}
4489
4490/*
4491 * XXX: an iop_range helps doing run-length encoded binary search. We know
4492 * that IOPs tags are mostly contiguous, hence we encode "full" runs of tags
4493 * this way:
4494 * [ offset0, start_tag0, offset1, ..., offset_n, start_tag_n, offset_end]
4495 *
4496 * This means that the offset0-th up to the offset1-th values described by
4497 * this iop_range take values contiguously from the range:
4498 * [ start_tag0 .. start_tag0 + offset1 - offset0 [
4499 *
4500 * Of course, offset0 is always equal to 0, and offset_n should be equal to
4501 * ranges_len.
4502 *
4503 * Example: the iop_range for "10 11 12 13 100 101 102" is "0 10 4 100 7"
4504 * - positions [0 .. 4[ have values in [10 .. 10 + 4 - 0[
4505 * - positions [4 .. 7[ have values in [100 .. 100 + 7 - 4[
4506 *
4507 */
4508int iop_ranges_search(int const * ranges, int ranges_len, int tag)
4509{
4510 int l = 0, r = ranges_len;
4511
4512 while (l < r) {
4513 int i = (l + r) / 2;
4514 int offs = ranges[i * 2];
4515 int start = ranges[i * 2 + 1];
4516
4517 if (tag < start) {
4518 r = i;
4519 continue;
4520 }
4521 if (tag + offs >= start + ranges[i * 2 + 2]) {
4522 l = i + 1;
4523 continue;
4524 }
4525 return ranges[i * 2] + (tag - start);
4526 }
4527 return -1;
4528}
4529
4530static int iop_enum_pos_from_val(const iop_enum_t *e, int val)
4531{
4532 return iop_ranges_search(e->ranges, e->ranges_len, val);
4533}
4534
4535static int iop_enum_pos_from_str(const iop_enum_t *e, const char *s, int len)
4536{
4537 lstr_t ename;
4538
4539 if (len < 0) {
4540 ename = LSTR(s);
4541 } else {
4542 ename = LSTR_INIT_V(s, len);
4543 }
4544 for (int i = 0; i < e->enum_len; i++) {
4545 if (lstr_ascii_iequal(e->names[i], ename)) {
4546 return i;
4547 }
4548 }
4549 if (TST_BIT(&e->flags, IOP_ENUM_ALIASES) && e->aliases) {
4550 for (int i = 0; i < e->aliases->len; i++) {
4551 if (lstr_ascii_iequal(e->aliases->aliases[i].name, ename)) {
4552 return e->aliases->aliases[i].pos;
4553 }
4554 }
4555 }
4556 return -1;
4557}
4558
4559int iop_enum_from_str2_desc(const iop_enum_t *e, const char *s, int len,
4560 bool *found)
4561{
4562 int pos = iop_enum_pos_from_str(e, s, len);
4563
4564 if (pos < 0) {
4565 *found = false;
4566 return -1;
4567 }
4568 *found = true;
4569 return e->values[pos];
4570}
4571
4572int iop_enum_from_str_desc(const iop_enum_t *e, const char *s, int len,
4573 int err)
4574{
4575 bool found;
4576 int val = iop_enum_from_str2_desc(e, s, len, &found);
4577
4578 return (found) ? val : err;
4579}
4580
4581int iop_enum_from_lstr_desc(const iop_enum_t *e, const lstr_t s, bool *found)
4582{
4583 return iop_enum_from_str2_desc(e, s.s, s.len, found);
4584}
4585
4586
4587static int iop_skip_field(pstream_t *ps, iop_wire_type_t wt)
4588{
4589 uint32_t u32 = 0;
4590
4591 switch (wt) {
4592 case IOP_WIRE_BLK1: PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 1, &u32)); break;
4593 case IOP_WIRE_BLK2: PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 2, &u32)); break;
4594 case IOP_WIRE_BLK4: PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 4, &u32)); break;
4595
4596 case IOP_WIRE_INT1:
4597 case IOP_WIRE_INT2:
4598 case IOP_WIRE_INT4:
4599 u32 = 1 << (wt - IOP_WIRE_INT1);
4600 break;
4601 case IOP_WIRE_QUAD:
4602 u32 = 8;
4603 break;
4604
4605 case IOP_WIRE_REPEAT: {
4606 uint32_t n = 0;
4607
4608 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 4, &n));
4609 PS_WANT(n >= 1);
4610
4611 while (n--) {
4612 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 1) && IOP_TAG(ps->b[0]) == 0);
4613 wt = IOP_WIRE_FMT(__ps_getc(ps));
4614 RETHROW(iop_skip_field(ps, wt));
4615 }
4616 } break;
4617
4618 default:
4619 return -1;
4620 }
4621
4622 return ps_skip(ps, u32);
4623}
4624
4625static ALWAYS_INLINE
4626int iop_patch_int(const iop_field_t *fdesc, void *ptr, int64_t i64)
4627{
4628#define CHECK_RANGE(_min, _max) THROW_ERR_IF(i64 < _min || i64 > _max)
4629
4630 switch (fdesc->type) {
4631 case IOP_T_I8:
4632 CHECK_RANGE(INT8_MIN, INT8_MAX);
4633 *(int8_t *)ptr = i64;
4634 break;
4635 case IOP_T_U8:
4636 CHECK_RANGE(0, UINT8_MAX);
4637 *(uint8_t *)ptr = i64;
4638 break;
4639 case IOP_T_I16:
4640 CHECK_RANGE(INT16_MIN, INT16_MAX);
4641 *(int16_t *)ptr = i64;
4642 break;
4643 case IOP_T_U16:
4644 CHECK_RANGE(0, UINT16_MAX);
4645 *(uint16_t *)ptr = i64;
4646 break;
4647 case IOP_T_ENUM:
4648 case IOP_T_I32:
4649 CHECK_RANGE(INT32_MIN, INT32_MAX);
4650 *(int32_t *)ptr = i64;
4651 break;
4652 case IOP_T_U32:
4653 CHECK_RANGE(0, UINT32_MAX);
4654 *(uint32_t *)ptr = i64;
4655 break;
4656 case IOP_T_I64: case IOP_T_U64:
4657 *(int64_t *)ptr = i64;
4658 break;
4659 case IOP_T_BOOL:
4660 CHECK_RANGE(0, 1);
4661 *(bool *)ptr = i64;
4662 break;
4663 case IOP_T_VOID:
4664 /* Never write a void field into a struct, it does not exist */
4665 e_named_trace(3, "iop/c/unpacker", "dropped value (0x%jx) into void "
4666 "field `%*pM`", i64, LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name));
4667 break;
4668 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
4669 case IOP_T_STRING:
4670 case IOP_T_DATA:
4671 case IOP_T_UNION:
4672 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
4673 case IOP_T_XML:
4674 e_panic("iop_type unsupported");
4675 }
4676
4677#undef CHECK_RANGE
4678 return 0;
4679}
4680
4681static ALWAYS_INLINE int
4682__get_tag_wt(pstream_t *ps, uint32_t *tag, iop_wire_type_t *wt)
4683{
4684 *wt = IOP_WIRE_FMT(ps->b[0]);
4685 *tag = IOP_TAG(__ps_getc(ps));
4686 if (likely(*tag < IOP_LONG_TAG(1)))
4687 return 0;
4688 if (likely(*tag == IOP_LONG_TAG(1)))
4689 return get_uint32(ps, 1, tag);
4690 return get_uint32(ps, 2, tag);
4691}
4692
4693static ALWAYS_INLINE int
4694__get_class_id(pstream_t *ps, iop_wire_type_t wt, uint16_t *class_id)
4695{
4696 switch (wt) {
4697 case IOP_WIRE_INT1:
4698 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 1));
4699 *class_id = (int8_t)__ps_getc(ps);
4700 return 0;
4701
4702 case IOP_WIRE_INT2:
4703 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 2));
4704 *class_id = (int16_t)__ps_get_le16(ps);
4705 return 0;
4706
4707 case IOP_WIRE_INT4:
4708 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 4));
4709 *class_id = (int16_t)__ps_get_le32(ps);
4710 return 0;
4711
4712 default:
4713 return -1;
4714 }
4715}
4716
4717int iop_skip_absent_field_desc(mem_pool_t *mp, void *value,
4718 const iop_struct_t *sdesc,
4719 const iop_field_t *fdesc)
4720{
4721 void *ptr = (char *)value + fdesc->data_offs;
4722
4723 switch (fdesc->repeat) {
4724 case IOP_R_REQUIRED: {
4725 const iop_struct_t *desc = fdesc->u1.st_desc;
4726 bool is_class;
4727
4728 /* A required void field can be skipped */
4729 if (fdesc->type == IOP_T_VOID) {
4730 return 0;
4731 }
4732
4733 /* For a required field, only structs can be absents, be careful that
4734 * union must be present */
4735 PS_WANT(fdesc->type == IOP_T_STRUCT);
4736
4737 if ((is_class = iop_field_is_class(fdesc))) {
4738 /* For classes, we consider that the absent object is of the
4739 * expected type, and not a child.
4740 * We have to allocate it since it's pointed. */
4741 PS_WANT(!desc->class_attrs->is_abstract);
4742 *(void **)ptr = mp_imalloc(mp, desc->size, 8, MEM_RAW);
4743 ptr = *(void **)ptr;
4744 *(const iop_struct_t **)ptr = desc;
4745 } else
4746 if (iop_field_is_reference(fdesc)) {
4747 *(void **)ptr = mp_imalloc(mp, desc->size, 8, MEM_RAW);
4748 ptr = *(void **)ptr;
4749 }
4750 do {
4751 for (int i = 0; i < desc->fields_len; i++) {
4752 RETHROW(iop_skip_absent_field_desc(mp, ptr, desc,
4753 desc->fields + i));
4754 }
4755 } while (is_class && (desc = desc->class_attrs->parent));
4756 } return 0;
4757
4758 case IOP_R_DEFVAL:
4759 RETHROW(iop_field_set_defval(fdesc, ptr));
4760 break;
4761
4762 case IOP_R_REPEATED: {
4763 unsigned fdesc_flags = fdesc->flags;
4764
4765 if (TST_BIT(&fdesc_flags, IOP_FIELD_NO_EMPTY_ARRAY)) {
4766 sb_reset(&iop_err_g.path);
4767 iop_err_g.desc = sdesc;
4768 iop_set_err("empty array not allowed for field `%*pM`",
4769 LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name));
4770 return -1;
4771 }
4772 p_clear((lstr_t *)ptr, 1);
4773 } break;
4774
4775 case IOP_R_OPTIONAL:
4776 iop_field_set_absent(fdesc, ptr);
4777 break;
4778 }
4779 return 0;
4780}
4781
4782static int
4783unpack_struct(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc, void *value,
4784 pstream_t *ps, unsigned flags, iop_wire_type_t *class_id_wt);
4785static int unpack_class(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc,
4786 void **value, pstream_t *ps, unsigned flags);
4787static int unpack_union(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc, void *value,
4788 pstream_t *ps, unsigned flags);
4789
4790static int unpack_value(mem_pool_t *mp, iop_wire_type_t wt,
4791 const iop_field_t *fdesc, void *v,
4792 pstream_t *ps, unsigned flags)
4793{
4794 uint32_t u32 = 0;
4795 pstream_t ps_tmp;
4796
4797 if (iop_field_is_reference(fdesc)) {
4798 v = iop_field_ptr_alloc(mp, fdesc, v);
4799 }
4800
4801 switch (wt) {
4802 case IOP_WIRE_BLK1:
4803 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 1, &u32));
4804 goto read_blk;
4805
4806 case IOP_WIRE_BLK2:
4807 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 2, &u32));
4808 goto read_blk;
4809
4810 case IOP_WIRE_BLK4:
4811 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 4, &u32));
4812 /* FALLTHROUGH */
4813
4814 read_blk:
4815 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_BLK_OK || fdesc->type == IOP_T_VOID);
4816 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, u32));
4817 switch (fdesc->type) {
4818 case IOP_T_STRING:
4819 case IOP_T_DATA:
4820 case IOP_T_XML:
4821 *(lstr_t *)v = LSTR_INIT_V(((flags & IOP_UNPACK_COPY_STRINGS)
4822 ? mp_dup(mp, ps->s, u32)
4823 : ps->p), u32 - 1);
4824 return __ps_skip(ps, u32);
4825 case IOP_T_UNION:
4826 ps_tmp = __ps_get_ps(ps, u32);
4827 return unpack_union(mp, fdesc->u1.st_desc, v, &ps_tmp, flags);
4828 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
4829 ps_tmp = __ps_get_ps(ps, u32);
4830 if (iop_field_is_class(fdesc)) {
4831 *(void **)v = NULL;
4832 return unpack_class(mp, fdesc->u1.st_desc, v, &ps_tmp, flags);
4833 } else {
4834 return unpack_struct(mp, fdesc->u1.st_desc, v, &ps_tmp, flags,
4835 NULL);
4836 }
4837 case IOP_T_VOID:
4838 /* do not write anything into void */
4839 if (u32 > 0) {
4840 e_named_trace(3, "iop/c/unpacker", "dropped block (%u bytes) "
4841 "into void field `%*pM`", u32,
4842 LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name));
4843 }
4844 return __ps_skip(ps, u32);
4845 default:
4846 break;
4847 }
4848 return -1;
4849
4850 case IOP_WIRE_INT1:
4851 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 1));
4852 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_INT_OK);
4853 return iop_patch_int(fdesc, v, (int8_t)__ps_getc(ps));
4854
4855 case IOP_WIRE_INT2:
4856 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 2));
4857 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_INT_OK);
4858 return iop_patch_int(fdesc, v, (int16_t)__ps_get_le16(ps));
4859
4860 case IOP_WIRE_INT4:
4861 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 4));
4862 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_INT_OK);
4863 return iop_patch_int(fdesc, v, (int32_t)__ps_get_le32(ps));
4864
4865 case IOP_WIRE_QUAD:
4866 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_INT_OK) {
4867 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 8));
4868 return iop_patch_int(fdesc, v, __ps_get_le64(ps));
4869 }
4870#if __FLOAT_WORD_ORDER != __BYTE_ORDER
4871 if (fdesc->type == IOP_T_DOUBLE)
4872 return ps_get_double_le(ps, v);
4873#endif
4874 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_QUAD_OK);
4875 return ps_get_le64(ps, v);
4876 default:
4877 return -1;
4878 }
4879}
4880
4881/* Returns:
4882 * * 1 when "change of level" (used for classes) tag was seen; in that case,
4883 * the wire type associated to this tag is written in class_id_wt.
4884 * * 0 otherwise on success.
4885 * * a negative value on error.
4886 */
4887static int
4888unpack_struct(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc, void *value,
4889 pstream_t *ps, unsigned flags, iop_wire_type_t *class_id_wt)
4890{
4891 bool is_class = iop_struct_is_class(desc);
4892 const iop_field_t *fdesc = desc->fields;
4893 const iop_field_t *end = desc->fields + desc->fields_len;
4894 iop_wire_type_t wt = 0;
4895 uint32_t tag = 1;
4896
4897 while (!ps_done(ps)) {
4898 uint32_t n = 1;
4899 void *v;
4900
4901 PS_CHECK(__get_tag_wt(ps, &tag, &wt));
4902 if (tag == 0) {
4903 /* This is a "change of level" tag in a packed class; check that
4904 * all the remaining fields at this level are optional. */
4905 PS_WANT(is_class);
4906 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker",
4907 "unpacking class %*pM, got change of level tag",
4908 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
4909 while (fdesc < end) {
4910 PS_CHECK(iop_skip_absent_field_desc(mp, value, desc, fdesc));
4911 fdesc++;
4912 }
4913 *class_id_wt = wt;
4914 return 1;
4915 }
4916 if (fdesc >= end) {
4917 goto end;
4918 }
4919
4920 while (unlikely(tag > fdesc->tag)) {
4921 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker", "unpacking struct %*pM, "
4922 "skipping absent field %*pM (tag %u)",
4923 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname),
4924 LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name), fdesc->tag);
4925 PS_CHECK(iop_skip_absent_field_desc(mp, value, desc, fdesc));
4926 if (++fdesc == end) {
4927 goto end;
4928 }
4929 }
4930 if (unlikely(tag < fdesc->tag)) {
4931 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker",
4932 "unpacking struct %*pM, skipping unknown tag %u",
4933 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname), tag);
4934 PS_CHECK(iop_skip_field(ps, wt));
4935 continue;
4936 }
4937
4938 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker",
4939 "unpacking struct %*pM, unpacking field %*pM (tag %u)",
4940 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname),
4941 LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name), tag);
4942
4943 if (fdesc && flags & IOP_UNPACK_FORBID_PRIVATE) {
4944 const iop_field_attrs_t *attrs = iop_field_get_attrs(desc, fdesc);
4945
4946 if (attrs && TST_BIT(&attrs->flags, IOP_FIELD_PRIVATE)) {
4947 iop_set_err("field `%*pM` of struct `%*pM` is private",
4948 LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name),
4949 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
4950 return -1;
4951 }
4952 }
4953
4954 if (wt == IOP_WIRE_REPEAT) {
4955 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 4, &n));
4956 PS_WANT(n >= 1);
4957 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 1) && IOP_TAG(ps->b[0]) == 0);
4958 wt = IOP_WIRE_FMT(__ps_getc(ps));
4959 }
4960
4961 v = (char *)value + fdesc->data_offs;
4962 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
4963 lstr_t *data = v;
4964
4965 if (wt != IOP_WIRE_REPEAT
4966 && ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_REPEATED_OPTIMIZE_OK))
4967 {
4968 /* optimized version of repeated fields are packed in simples
4969 * IOP blocks */
4970 uint32_t len = 0;
4971
4972 switch (wt) {
4973 case IOP_WIRE_BLK1:
4974 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 1, &len));
4975 break;
4976 case IOP_WIRE_BLK2:
4977 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 2, &len));
4978 break;
4979 case IOP_WIRE_BLK4:
4980 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 4, &len));
4981 break;
4982 default:
4983 /* Here we expect to have a uniq-value packed as a normal
4984 * field (data->len == 1) */
4985 goto unpack_array;
4986 }
4987 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, len));
4988
4989 if (fdesc->size == 1) {
4990 data->len = len;
4991 data->data = ((flags & IOP_UNPACK_COPY_STRINGS)
4992 ? mp_dup(mp, ps->s, len)
4993 : (void *)ps->p);
4994 } else {
4995 assert (fdesc->size == 2);
4996 PS_WANT(len % 2 == 0);
4997 data->len = len / 2;
4998 data->data = mp_dup(mp, ps->s, len);
4999 }
5000
5001 __ps_skip(ps, len);
5002 v = data->data;
5003 n = data->len;
5004 goto next;
5005 }
5006
5007 unpack_array:
5008 data->len = n;
5009 data->data = v = mp_imalloc(mp, n * fdesc->size, 8, MEM_RAW);
5010
5011 while (n-- > 1) {
5012 if (unpack_value(mp, wt, fdesc, v, ps, flags) < 0) {
5013 sb_prepend_field(&iop_err_g.path, fdesc,
5014 data->len - n - 1);
5015 return -1;
5016 }
5017 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 1) && IOP_TAG(ps->b[0]) == 0);
5018 wt = IOP_WIRE_FMT(__ps_getc(ps));
5019 v = (char *)v + fdesc->size;
5020 }
5021 if (unpack_value(mp, wt, fdesc, v, ps, flags) < 0) {
5022 sb_prepend_field(&iop_err_g.path, fdesc, 0);
5023 return -1;
5024 }
5025 v = data->data;
5026 n = data->len;
5027 } else {
5028 while (n-- > 1) {
5029 PS_CHECK(iop_skip_field(ps, wt));
5030 PS_WANT(ps_has(ps, 1) && IOP_TAG(ps->b[0]) == 0);
5031 wt = IOP_WIRE_FMT(__ps_getc(ps));
5032 }
5033 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL && !iop_field_is_class(fdesc))
5034 {
5035 v = iop_field_set_present(mp, fdesc, v);
5036 }
5037 if (unpack_value(mp, wt, fdesc, v, ps, flags) < 0) {
5038 sb_prepend_field(&iop_err_g.path, fdesc, 0);
5039 return -1;
5040 }
5041 n = 1;
5042 }
5043
5044 next:
5045 if (unlikely(iop_field_has_constraints(desc, fdesc))) {
5046 RETHROW(iop_field_check_constraints(desc, fdesc, v, n, false));
5047 }
5048 fdesc++;
5049 }
5050
5051 end:
5052 /* consume tags that no longer exists */
5053 while (!ps_done(ps)
5054 && (desc->fields_len == 0
5055 || tag > desc->fields[desc->fields_len - 1].tag))
5056 {
5057 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker",
5058 "unpacking struct %*pM, skipping unknown tag %u",
5059 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname), tag);
5060 PS_CHECK(iop_skip_field(ps, wt));
5061 if (ps_done(ps)) {
5062 break;
5063 }
5064 PS_CHECK(__get_tag_wt(ps, &tag, &wt));
5065 if (tag == 0) {
5066 PS_WANT(is_class);
5067 *class_id_wt = wt;
5068 break;
5069 }
5070 }
5071
5072 /* consume fields that are not set */
5073 for (; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
5074 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker",
5075 "unpacking struct %*pM, skipping %*pM field",
5076 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname),
5077 LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name));
5078 PS_CHECK(iop_skip_absent_field_desc(mp, value, desc, fdesc));
5079 }
5080
5081 /* return 1 if change of level tag has been found */
5082 return (tag == 0) ? 1 : 0;
5083}
5084
5085static inline int
5086unpack_skip_all_fields(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc, void *value)
5087{
5088 const iop_field_t *fdesc = desc->fields;
5089 const iop_field_t *end = fdesc + desc->fields_len;
5090
5091 for ( ; fdesc < end; fdesc++) {
5092 PS_CHECK(iop_skip_absent_field_desc(mp, value, desc, fdesc));
5093 }
5094 return 0;
5095}
5096
5097static int unpack_class(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc,
5098 void **value, pstream_t *ps, unsigned flags)
5099{
5100 const iop_struct_t *real_desc;
5101 iop_wire_type_t wt;
5102 uint32_t tag = 1;
5103 uint16_t child_id = 0;
5104 pstream_t saved_ps = *ps;
5105
5106 if (likely(!ps_done(ps))) {
5107 /* Get the class id of the packed class instance */
5108 PS_CHECK(__get_tag_wt(ps, &tag, &wt));
5109 }
5110
5111 if (unlikely(tag != 0)) {
5112 /* struct -> class backward compat handling, ok if the class has no
5113 * parents. */
5114 if (desc->class_attrs->parent) {
5115 iop_set_err("invalid binary encoding for value of type `%*pM`",
5116 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
5117 return -1;
5118 }
5119 *ps = saved_ps;
5120 real_desc = desc;
5121 } else {
5122 PS_CHECK(__get_class_id(ps, wt, &child_id));
5123
5124 if (unlikely(!(real_desc = iop_get_class_by_id(desc, child_id)))) {
5125 SB_1k(err);
5126
5127 sb_addf(&err, "cannot find child %d of class '%*pM'",
5128 child_id, LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
5129 e_trace(0, "%*pM; missing IOP_REGISTER_PACKAGES?",
5130 SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
5131 iop_set_err2(&LSTR_SB_V(&err));
5132 return -1;
5133 }
5134 }
5135
5136 if (real_desc != desc) {
5137 /* We are trying to unpack a class of type "desc", and the packed
5138 * class is of type "real_desc". Check that this is authorized. */
5139 if (unlikely(!iop_class_is_a(real_desc, desc))) {
5140 SB_1k(err);
5141
5142 sb_addf(&err, "class '%*pM' (id %d) is not a child of '%*pM' "
5143 "(id %d) as expected",
5144 LSTR_FMT_ARG(real_desc->fullname), child_id,
5145 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname),
5146 desc->class_attrs->class_id);
5147 e_trace(0, "%*pM", SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
5148 iop_set_err2(&LSTR_SB_V(&err));
5149 return -1;
5150 }
5151 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker",
5152 "unpacking a class of type %*pM, real type %*pM",
5153 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname),
5154 LSTR_FMT_ARG(real_desc->fullname));
5155 }
5156
5157 if (flags & IOP_UNPACK_FORBID_PRIVATE
5158 && real_desc->class_attrs->is_private)
5159 {
5160 iop_set_err("class `%*pM` is private",
5161 LSTR_FMT_ARG(real_desc->fullname));
5162 return -1;
5163 }
5164
5165 PS_WANT(!real_desc->class_attrs->is_abstract);
5166 *value = mp_irealloc(mp, *value, 0, real_desc->size, 8, MEM_RAW);
5167
5168 /* Set the __vptr pointer */
5169 *(const iop_struct_t **)(*value) = real_desc;
5170
5171 /* Unpack the several levels */
5172 for (;;) {
5173 uint16_t class_id = 0;
5174 int res;
5175
5176 PS_CHECK((res = unpack_struct(mp, real_desc, *value, ps, flags, &wt)));
5177
5178 if (!(real_desc = real_desc->class_attrs->parent)) {
5179 return 0;
5180 }
5181
5182 if (res != 1) {
5183 /* "Change of level" tag was not seen yet */
5184 if (ps_done(ps)) {
5185 /* Such a tag won't be there because pstream is finished. This
5186 * is possible if all the remaining levels have only optional
5187 * fields. */
5188 do {
5189 PS_CHECK(unpack_skip_all_fields(mp, real_desc, *value));
5190 } while ((real_desc = real_desc->class_attrs->parent));
5191 return 0;
5192 }
5193 /* Read it */
5194 PS_CHECK(__get_tag_wt(ps, &tag, &wt));
5195 PS_WANT(tag == 0);
5196 }
5197
5198 /* Get the next class id, and run the tree up to it; the skipped
5199 * classes must have only optional fields. */
5200 PS_CHECK(__get_class_id(ps, wt, &class_id));
5201 while (class_id != real_desc->class_attrs->class_id) {
5202 PS_CHECK(unpack_skip_all_fields(mp, real_desc, *value));
5203 PS_WANT((real_desc = real_desc->class_attrs->parent));
5204 }
5205 }
5206}
5207
5208/* note: returns 0 on success, -1 on error and 1 if the pstream hasn't been
5209 * fully consumed. */
5210static int unpack_union(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc, void *value,
5211 pstream_t *ps, unsigned flags)
5212{
5213 const iop_field_t *fdesc = desc->fields;
5214
5215 iop_wire_type_t wt;
5216 uint32_t tag;
5217 int ifield;
5218
5219 PS_WANT(!ps_done(ps));
5220 /* We get the selected tag in the union */
5221 PS_CHECK(__get_tag_wt(ps, &tag, &wt));
5222 /* Repeated fields are forbidden in union */
5223 PS_WANT(wt != IOP_WIRE_REPEAT);
5224
5225 ifield = iop_ranges_search(desc->ranges, desc->ranges_len, tag);
5226 PS_CHECK(ifield);
5227 fdesc += ifield;
5228
5229 /* Write the selected field */
5230 iop_union_set_tag(desc, fdesc->tag, value);
5231 value = (char *)value + fdesc->data_offs;
5232
5233 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker", "unpacking union %*pM field %*pM",
5234 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname), LSTR_FMT_ARG(fdesc->name));
5235 if (unpack_value(mp, wt, fdesc, value, ps, flags) < 0) {
5236 sb_prepend_field(&iop_err_g.path, fdesc, 0);
5237 return -1;
5238 }
5239 if (unlikely(iop_field_has_constraints(desc, fdesc))) {
5240 RETHROW(iop_field_check_constraints(desc, fdesc, value, 1, false));
5241 }
5242 return ps_done(ps) ? 0 : 1;
5243}
5244
5245int iop_bunpack_flags(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc, void *value,
5246 pstream_t ps, unsigned flags)
5247{
5248 assert (!iop_struct_is_class(desc));
5249 assert (mp && mp->mem_pool & MEM_BY_FRAME);
5250 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker", "unpacking IOP object %*pM",
5251 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
5252 iop_clear_err();
5253 if (desc->is_union) {
5254 return unpack_union(mp, desc, value, &ps, flags) ? -1 : 0;
5255 }
5256 return unpack_struct(mp, desc, value, &ps, flags, NULL) < 0 ? -1 : 0;
5257}
5258
5259int iop_bunpack_ptr_flags(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc,
5260 void **value, pstream_t ps, unsigned flags)
5261{
5262 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker", "unpacking IOP object %*pM",
5263 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
5264 iop_clear_err();
5265
5266 if (!iop_struct_is_class(desc)) {
5267 *value = mp_irealloc(mp, *value, 0, desc->size, 8, MEM_RAW);
5268 return iop_bunpack_flags(mp, desc, *value, ps, flags);
5269 }
5270 assert (mp && mp->mem_pool & MEM_BY_FRAME);
5271
5272 return unpack_class(mp, desc, value, &ps, flags);
5273}
5274
5275/* XXX: this function can unpack only union because the struct can't be
5276 * delimited in a stream.
5277 * */
5278int iop_bunpack_multi_flags(mem_pool_t *mp, const iop_struct_t *desc,
5279 void *value, pstream_t *ps, unsigned flags)
5280{
5281 pstream_t ps_save = *ps;
5282
5283 assert(desc->is_union);
5284
5285 e_named_trace(5, "iop/c/unpacker", "unpacking IOP union(s) %*pM",
5286 LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname));
5287 iop_clear_err();
5288 if (unpack_union(mp, desc, value, ps, flags) < 0) {
5289 *ps = ps_save;
5290 return -1;
5291 }
5292
5293 return 0;
5294}
5295
5296/* XXX this function doesn't check the IOP content and trust what it reads
5297 * XXX: this function can unpack only union because the struct can't be
5298 * delimited in a stream. */
5299int iop_bskip(const iop_struct_t *desc, pstream_t *ps)
5300{
5301 const iop_field_t *fdesc = desc->fields;
5302 iop_wire_type_t wt;
5303 uint32_t tag, u32 = 0;
5304 int ifield;
5305
5306 assert(desc->is_union);
5307
5308 PS_WANT(!ps_done(ps));
5309 /* We get the selected tag in the union */
5310 PS_CHECK(__get_tag_wt(ps, &tag, &wt));
5311 /* Repeated fields are forbidden in union */
5312 PS_WANT(wt != IOP_WIRE_REPEAT);
5313
5314 ifield = iop_ranges_search(desc->ranges, desc->ranges_len, tag);
5315 PS_CHECK(ifield);
5316 fdesc += ifield;
5317
5318 /* Skip union data */
5319 switch (wt) {
5320 case IOP_WIRE_BLK1:
5321 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 1, &u32));
5322 goto read_blk;
5323
5324 case IOP_WIRE_BLK2:
5325 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 2, &u32));
5326 goto read_blk;
5327
5328 case IOP_WIRE_BLK4:
5329 PS_CHECK(get_uint32(ps, 4, &u32));
5330
5331 read_blk:
5332 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_BLK_OK);
5333 PS_CHECK(ps_skip(ps, u32)); /* Skip block */
5334 return 0;
5335
5336 case IOP_WIRE_INT1:
5337 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_INT_OK);
5338 PS_CHECK(ps_skip(ps, 1));
5339 return 0;
5340
5341 case IOP_WIRE_INT2:
5342 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_INT_OK);
5343 PS_CHECK(ps_skip(ps, 2));
5344 return 0;
5345
5346 case IOP_WIRE_INT4:
5347 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_INT_OK);
5348 PS_CHECK(ps_skip(ps, 4));
5349 return 0;
5350
5351 case IOP_WIRE_QUAD:
5352 if ((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_INT_OK) {
5353 PS_CHECK(ps_skip(ps, 8));
5354 return 0;
5355 }
5356#if __FLOAT_WORD_ORDER != __BYTE_ORDER
5357 if (fdesc->type == IOP_T_DOUBLE) {
5358 PS_CHECK(ps_skip(ps, sizeof(double)));
5359 return 0;
5360 }
5361#endif
5362 PS_WANT((1 << fdesc->type) & IOP_QUAD_OK);
5363 PS_CHECK(ps_skip(ps, 8));
5364 return 0;
5365 default:
5366 return -1;
5367 }
5368}
5369
5370ssize_t iop_get_field_len(pstream_t ps)
5371{
5372 iop_wire_type_t wt;
5373 uint32_t tag, u32, tag_len, len_len;
5374
5375 if (ps_done(&ps))
5376 return 0;
5377 wt = IOP_WIRE_FMT(ps.b[0]);
5378 tag = IOP_TAG(ps.b[0]);
5379 if (likely(tag < IOP_LONG_TAG(1))) {
5380 tag_len = 1;
5381 } else {
5382 tag_len = 2 + tag - IOP_LONG_TAG(1);
5383 }
5384 switch (wt) {
5385 case IOP_WIRE_BLK1:
5386 len_len = 1;
5387 break;
5388 case IOP_WIRE_BLK2:
5389 len_len = 2;
5390 break;
5391 case IOP_WIRE_BLK4:
5392 len_len = 4;
5393 break;
5394 case IOP_WIRE_REPEAT: /* not supported by this function */
5395 return -1;
5396 case IOP_WIRE_INT1:
5397 return tag_len + 1;
5398 case IOP_WIRE_INT2:
5399 return tag_len + 2;
5400 case IOP_WIRE_INT4:
5401 return tag_len + 4;
5402 case IOP_WIRE_QUAD:
5403 return tag_len + 8;
5404 default:
5405 return -1;
5406 }
5407 if (ps_skip(&ps, tag_len) < 0)
5408 return 0;
5409 u32 = 0;
5410 if (get_uint32(&ps, len_len, &u32) < 0)
5411 return 0;
5412 return tag_len + len_len + u32;
5413}
5414
5415/* }}} */
5416/* {{{ Introspection */
5417
5418const iop_iface_t *iop_mod_find_iface(const iop_mod_t *mod, uint32_t tag)
5419{
5420 size_t l = 0, r = mod->ifaces_len;
5421
5422 while (l < r) {
5423 size_t i = (l + r) / 2;
5424 const iop_iface_alias_t *alias = &mod->ifaces[i];
5425
5426 if (tag == alias->tag) {
5427 return alias->iface;
5428 }
5429 if (tag < alias->tag) {
5430 r = i;
5431 } else {
5432 l = i + 1;
5433 }
5434 }
5435 return NULL;
5436}
5437
5438const iop_rpc_t *iop_iface_find_rpc(const iop_iface_t *iface, uint32_t tag)
5439{
5440 size_t l = 0, r = iface->funs_len;
5441
5442 while (l < r) {
5443 size_t i = (l + r) / 2;
5444 const iop_rpc_t *rpc = &iface->funs[i];
5445
5446 if (tag == rpc->tag) {
5447 return rpc;
5448 }
5449 if (tag < rpc->tag) {
5450 r = i;
5451 } else {
5452 l = i + 1;
5453 }
5454 }
5455 return NULL;
5456}
5457
5458const iop_rpc_t *iop_mod_find_rpc(const iop_mod_t *mod, uint32_t cmd)
5459{
5460 const iop_iface_t *iface = RETHROW_P(iop_mod_find_iface(mod, cmd >> 16));
5461 return iop_iface_find_rpc(iface, cmd & 0xffff);
5462}
5463
5464const iop_struct_t *
5465_iop_class_first_non_empty_parent(const iop_struct_t *cls)
5466{
5467 do {
5468 cls = cls->class_attrs->parent;
5469 } while (cls && !cls->fields_len);
5470
5471 return cls;
5472}
5473
5474const iop_field_t * nullable
5475iop_struct_get_next_field(const iop_field_t *nullable field,
5476 const iop_struct_t *nonnull *nonnull st)
5477{
5478 return _iop_struct_next_field(iop_struct_is_class(*st), field, st);
5479}
5480
5481/* }}} */
5482/* {{{ Altering IOP objects */
5483
5484void iop_prune(const iop_struct_t *st, void *obj, lstr_t gen_attr)
5485{
5486 iop_for_each_field_fast(st, obj, ^int (const iop_struct_t *st_desc,
5487 const iop_field_t *fdesc,
5488 void *st_ptr) {
5489 /* Check first if the field is repeated of optional for perfs. */
5490 if (fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED
5491 || fdesc->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL)
5492 {
5493 if (iop_field_get_bool_gen_attr(st_desc, fdesc, gen_attr,
5494 false))
5495 {
5496 int res;
5497
5498 t_seal();
5499 res = iop_skip_absent_field_desc(t_pool(), st_ptr, st_desc,
5500 fdesc);
5501 t_unseal();
5502 assert (res >= 0);
5503 return IOP_FIELD_SKIP;
5504 }
5505 } else {
5506 assert (!iop_field_get_bool_gen_attr(st_desc, fdesc, gen_attr,
5507 false));
5508 }
5509
5510 return 0;
5511 });
5512}
5513
5514/* }}} */
5515/* {{{ Introspection - iop_for_each_(field|st|obj) */
5516
5517/* {{{ Stack management */
5518
5519typedef struct field_stack_el_t {
5520 htnode_t link;
5521 const iop_struct_t *st_desc;
5522 const iop_field_t *f;
5523 const void *st_ptr;
5524 int index;
5525} field_stack_el_t;
5526
5527struct iop_field_stack_t {
5528 htlist_t flist;
5529};
5530
5531static inline iop_field_stack_t *
5532iop_field_stack_init(iop_field_stack_t *fstack)
5533{
5534 p_clear(fstack, 1);
5535 htlist_init(&fstack->flist);
5536
5537 return fstack;
5538}
5539
5540static field_stack_el_t *field_stack_el_init(field_stack_el_t *el)
5541{
5542 p_clear(el, 1);
5543 el->index = -1;
5544
5545 return el;
5546}
5547
5548static void field_path_print_rec(sb_t *sb, const field_stack_el_t *el)
5549{
5550 if (el->link.next) {
5551 field_stack_el_t *e;
5552
5553 e = htlist_entry(el->link.next, field_stack_el_t, link);
5554 field_path_print_rec(sb, e);
5555 sb_addc(sb, '.');
5556 }
5557
5558 sb_add_lstr(sb, el->f->name);
5559 if (el->index >= 0) {
5560 sb_addf(sb, "[%d]", el->index);
5561 }
5562}
5563
5564void sb_add_iop_field_stack(sb_t *nonnull buf,
5565 const iop_field_stack_t *nonnull fstack)
5566{
5567 field_stack_el_t *el;
5568
5569 el = htlist_first_entry(&fstack->flist, field_stack_el_t, link);
5570 if (el) {
5571 field_path_print_rec(buf, el);
5572 } else {
5573 sb_adds(buf, "<root>");
5574 }
5575}
5576
5577lstr_t t_iop_field_stack_to_lstr(const iop_field_stack_t *nonnull fstack)
5578{
5579 SB_1k(buf);
5580
5581 sb_add_iop_field_stack(&buf, fstack);
5582
5583 return t_lstr_dup(LSTR_SB_V(&buf));
5584}
5585
5586static void iop_field_stack_fill_head(iop_field_stack_t *fstack,
5587 const iop_struct_t *st_desc,
5588 const void *st_ptr,
5589 const iop_field_t *fdesc)
5590{
5591 field_stack_el_t *el;
5592
5593 el = htlist_first_entry(&fstack->flist, field_stack_el_t, link);
5594 el->st_desc = st_desc;
5595 el->st_ptr = st_ptr;
5596 el->f = fdesc;
5597}
5598
5599static int on_field_cb(const iop_struct_t *st_desc, void *st_ptr,
5600 const iop_field_t *fdesc,
5601 iop_field_stack_t *fstack,
5602 iop_for_each_field_cb_b nonnull cb)
5603{
5604 iop_field_stack_fill_head(fstack, st_desc, st_ptr, fdesc);
5605
5606 return cb(st_desc, fdesc, st_ptr, fstack);
5607}
5608
5609#define F_LOCAL_WSTACK \
5610 field_stack_el_t _stack_el; \
5611 \
5612 field_stack_el_init(&_stack_el); \
5613 htlist_add(&fstack->flist, &_stack_el.link)
5614
5615#define SET_INDEX_WSTACK(_index) \
5616 htlist_first_entry(&fstack->flist, field_stack_el_t, \
5617 link)->index = _index
5618
5619#define ON_FIELD_DONE_WSTACK() htlist_pop(&fstack->flist)
5620

5965/* }}} */
5966/* {{{ IOP iop_full_type_t */
5967
5968uint32_t qhash_iop_full_type_hash(const qhash_t *qhash,
5969 const iop_full_type_t *type)
5970{
5971 if (type->type == IOP_T_ENUM) {
5972 return u64_hash32((uint64_t)type->en);
5973 }
5974 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(type->type)) {
5975 return u64_hash32((uint64_t)type->st);
5976 }
5977
5978 return type->type;
5979}
5980
5981bool qhash_iop_full_type_equal(const qhash_t *qhash,
5982 const iop_full_type_t *t1,
5983 const iop_full_type_t *t2)
5984{
5985 THROW_FALSE_IF(t1->type != t2->type);
5986 if (t1->type == IOP_T_ENUM) {
5987 return t1->en == t2->en;
5988 }
5989 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(t1->type)) {
5990 return t1->st == t2->st;
5991 }
5992 return true;
5993}
5994
5995void iop_field_get_type(const iop_field_t *nonnull field,
5996 iop_full_type_t *nonnull type)
5997{
5998 p_clear(type, 1);
5999 type->type = field->type;
6000 if (field->type == IOP_T_ENUM) {
6001 type->en = field->u1.en_desc;
6002 } else
6003 if (!iop_type_is_scalar(field->type)) {
6004 type->st = field->u1.st_desc;
6005 }
6006}
6007
6008/* }}} */
6009/* {{{ IOP context */
6010
6011static void iop_env_copy(iop_env_t *dst, iop_env_t *src)
6012{
6013 iop_env_init(dst);
6014
6015 qm_for_each_pos(iop_class_by_id, pos, &src->classes_by_id) {
6016 qm_add(iop_class_by_id, &dst->classes_by_id,
6017 &src->classes_by_id.keys[pos], src->classes_by_id.values[pos]);
6018 }
6019 qm_for_each_pos(iop_dsos, pos, &src->dsos_by_pkg) {
6020 qm_add(iop_dsos, &dst->dsos_by_pkg, src->dsos_by_pkg.keys[pos],
6021 src->dsos_by_pkg.values[pos]);
6022 }
6023
6024 qm_set_minsize(iop_objs, &dst->iop_obj_by_fullname,
6025 qm_len(iop_objs, &src->iop_obj_by_fullname));
6026 qm_for_each_pos(iop_objs, pos, &src->iop_obj_by_fullname) {
6027 qv_t(iop_obj) vec;
6028 lstr_t obj_fullname;
6029
6030 obj_fullname = lstr_dup(src->iop_obj_by_fullname.keys[pos]);
6031 qv_init(&vec);
6032 qv_copy(&vec, &src->iop_obj_by_fullname.values[pos]);
6033 qm_add(iop_objs, &dst->iop_obj_by_fullname, &obj_fullname, vec);
6034 }
6035}
6036
6037void iop_env_set(iop_env_t *env)
6038{
6039 iop_env_wipe(&_G.env);
6040 _G.env = *env;
6041}
6042
6043void iop_env_get(iop_env_t *env)
6044{
6045 iop_env_copy(env, &_G.env);
6046}
6047
6048iop_env_t *iop_env_init(iop_env_t *env)
6049{
6050 qm_init(iop_class_by_id, &env->classes_by_id);
6051 qm_init(iop_dsos, &env->dsos_by_pkg);
6052 qm_init(iop_objs, &env->iop_obj_by_fullname);
6053 return env;
6054}
6055
6056void iop_env_wipe(iop_env_t *env)
6057{
6058 qm_wipe(iop_class_by_id, &env->classes_by_id);
6059 qm_wipe(iop_dsos, &env->dsos_by_pkg);
6060 qm_deep_wipe(iop_objs, &env->iop_obj_by_fullname, lstr_wipe, qv_wipe);
6061}

6063/* }}} */
6064/* {{{ Class manipulation */
6065
6066iop_static_field_t const *
6067iop_get_class_cvar_field_desc(const iop_struct_t * nonnull desc, lstr_t name)
6068{
6069 iop_static_field_t _search = { .name = name };
6070 iop_static_field_t *search = &_search;
6071
6072 const iop_class_attrs_t *cls = desc->class_attrs;
6073 bool found;
6074 int pos;
6075 cmp_b cmp = ^int (const void *a, const void *b) {
6076 const iop_static_field_t **v1 = (const iop_static_field_t **)a;
6077 const iop_static_field_t **v2 = (const iop_static_field_t **)b;
6078
6079 return lstr_cmp((*v1)->name, (*v2)->name);
6080 };
6081
6082 assert (iop_struct_is_class(desc));
6083
6084 pos = bisect_blk(&search, cls->static_fields,
6085 sizeof(iop_static_field_t *),
6086 cls->static_fields_len, &found, cmp);
6087 if (found) {
6088 const iop_static_field_t *f;
6089
6090 f = desc->class_attrs->static_fields[pos];
6091 return f;
6092 }
6093 return NULL;
6094}
6095
6096const iop_static_field_t * nullable
6097iop_get_cvar_field_desc(const iop_struct_t *desc, lstr_t name)
6098{
6099 assert(iop_struct_is_class(desc));
6100
6101 do {
6102 const iop_class_attrs_t *cls = desc->class_attrs;
6103 const iop_static_field_t *v;
6104
6105 if ((v = iop_get_class_cvar_field_desc(desc, name))) {
6106 return v;
6107 }
6108 desc = cls->parent;
6109 } while (desc);
6110
6111 return NULL;
6112}
6113
6114iop_value_t const *
6115iop_get_class_cvar_desc(const iop_struct_t *desc, lstr_t name)
6116{
6117 const iop_static_field_t *f;
6118
6119 f = iop_get_class_cvar_field_desc(desc, name);
6120 return f ? &f->value : NULL;
6121}
6122
6123const iop_value_t *iop_get_class_cvar(const void *obj, lstr_t name)
6124{
6125 return iop_get_class_cvar_desc(*(iop_struct_t **)obj, name);
6126}
6127
6128const iop_value_t *iop_get_cvar_desc(const iop_struct_t *desc, lstr_t name)
6129{
6130 assert (iop_struct_is_class(desc));
6131
6132 do {
6133 const iop_class_attrs_t *cls = desc->class_attrs;
6134 const iop_value_t *v;
6135
6136 if ((v = iop_get_class_cvar_desc(desc, name))) {
6137 return v;
6138 }
6139 desc = cls->parent;
6140 } while (desc);
6141
6142 return NULL;
6143}
6144
6145const iop_value_t *iop_get_cvar(const void *obj, lstr_t name)
6146{
6147 return iop_get_cvar_desc(*(iop_struct_t **)obj, name);
6148}
6149
6150bool iop_class_is_a(const iop_struct_t *cls1, const iop_struct_t *cls2)
6151{
6152 if (!iop_struct_is_class(cls1) || !iop_struct_is_class(cls2)) {
6153 assert (false);
6154 return false;
6155 }
6156
6157 do {
6158 if (cls1 == cls2) {
6159 return true;
6160 }
6161 } while ((cls1 = cls1->class_attrs->parent));
6162
6163 return false;
6164}
6165
6166static const qv_t(iop_obj) *
6167iop_get_objs_env(lstr_t fullname, const iop_env_t *env)
6168{
6169 int pos;
6170
6171 pos = RETHROW_NP(qm_find_safe(iop_objs, &env->iop_obj_by_fullname,
6172 &fullname));
6173
6174 return &env->iop_obj_by_fullname.values[pos];
6175}
6176
6177static const qv_t(iop_obj) *iop_get_objs(lstr_t fullname)
6178{
6179 return iop_get_objs_env(fullname, &_G.env);
6180}
6181
6182const iop_struct_t *
6183iop_get_class_by_fullname(const iop_struct_t *st, lstr_t fullname)
6184{
6185 const qv_t(iop_obj) *objs;
6186
6187 assert (iop_struct_is_class(st));
6188 while (st->class_attrs->parent) {
6189 st = st->class_attrs->parent;
6190 }
6191
6192 objs = RETHROW_P(iop_get_objs(fullname));
6193
6194 tab_for_each_ptr(obj, objs) {
6195 if (obj->type == IOP_OBJ_TYPE_ST
6196 && obj->ancestor == st)
6197 {
6198 return obj->desc.st;
6199 }
6200 }
6201
6202 return NULL;
6203}
6204
6205const iop_struct_t *
6206iop_get_class_by_id(const iop_struct_t *st, uint16_t class_id)
6207{
6208 class_id_key_t key = {
6209 .master = st,
6210 .child_id = class_id,
6211 };
6212
6213 if (st->class_attrs->class_id == class_id) {
6214 return st;
6215 }
6216
6217 while (key.master->class_attrs->parent) {
6218 key.master = key.master->class_attrs->parent;
6219 }
6220
6221 return qm_get_def_safe(iop_class_by_id, &_G.env.classes_by_id, &key,
6222 NULL);
6223}
6224
6225void iop_for_each_registered_classes(iop_for_each_class_b cb)
6226{
6227 qm_for_each_pos(iop_class_by_id, pos, &_G.env.classes_by_id) {
6228 cb(_G.env.classes_by_id.values[pos]);
6229 }
6230}
