6232/* }}} */
6233/* {{{ Snmp manipulation */
6234
6235int iop_struct_get_nb_snmp_indexes(const iop_struct_t *st)
6236{
6237 int nb = 0;
6238
6239 for (int i = 0; i < st->fields_len; i++) {
6240 if (iop_field_is_snmp_index(&st->fields[i])) {
6241 nb++;
6242 }
6243 }
6244 return nb;
6245}
6246
6247int iop_struct_get_nb_snmp_smiv2_indexes(const iop_struct_t *st)
6248{
6249 int nb = 0;
6250
6251 for (int i = 0; i < st->fields_len; i++) {
6252 const iop_field_t *field =&st->fields[i];
6253
6254 if (iop_field_is_snmp_index(field)) {
6255 if (field->type == IOP_T_STRING) {
6256 /* there is at most 128 sub-identifiers
6257 * (see RFC 2578, section 3.5). */
6258 return 128;
6259 } else {
6260 nb++;
6261 }
6262 }
6263 }
6264
6265 return MIN(nb, 128);
6266}
6267
6268const iop_snmp_attrs_t *iop_get_snmp_attrs(const iop_field_attrs_t *attrs)
6269{
6270 for (int i = 0; i < attrs->attrs_len; i++) {
6271 if (attrs->attrs[i].type == IOP_FIELD_SNMP_INFO) {
6272 return (iop_snmp_attrs_t*)attrs->attrs[i].args->v.p;
6273 }
6274 }
6275 e_panic("all snmpObj fields should have snmp attribute");
6276}
6277
6278const iop_snmp_attrs_t *iop_get_snmp_attr_match_oid(const iop_struct_t *st,
6279 int oid)
6280{
6281 assert (iop_struct_is_snmp_st(st));
6282
6283 for (int i = 0; i < st->fields_len; i++) {
6284 const iop_field_t *field = &st->fields[i];
6285
6286 if (field->tag == oid) {
6287 return iop_get_snmp_attrs(&st->fields_attrs[i]);
6288 }
6289 }
6290 e_panic("no field matches wanted OID");
6291}
6292
6293const iop_field_attrs_t *iop_get_field_attr_match_oid(const iop_struct_t *st,
6294 int tag)
6295{
6296 for (int i = 0; i < st->fields_len; i++) {
6297 const iop_field_t *field = &st->fields[i];
6298
6299 if (field->tag == tag) {
6300 return &st->fields_attrs[i];
6301 }
6302 }
6303 e_panic("no field matches wanted OID");
6304}
6305
6306/* }}} */
6307/* {{{ Packages registration / manipulation */
6308
6309static int iop_register_class(const iop_struct_t *desc, iop_env_t *env,
6310 sb_t *err)
6311{
6312 class_id_key_t key = {
6313 .master = desc,
6314 .child_id = desc->class_attrs->class_id,
6315 };
6316 uint32_t pos;
6317
6318 while (key.master->class_attrs->parent) {
6319 key.master = key.master->class_attrs->parent;
6320 }
6321
6322 /* Register in classes_by_id hash table */
6323 pos = qm_put(iop_class_by_id, &env->classes_by_id, &key, desc, 0);
6324 if (pos & QHASH_COLLISION) {
6325 pos ^= QHASH_COLLISION;
6326 if (env->classes_by_id.values[pos] != desc) {
6327 sb_setf(err,
6328 "conflicting class id %d: used by both '%*pM' and '%*pM'",
6329 desc->class_attrs->class_id, LSTR_FMT_ARG(desc->fullname),
6330 LSTR_FMT_ARG(env->classes_by_id.values[pos]->fullname));
6331 return -1;
6332 }
6333 }
6334 return 0;
6335}
6336
6337static int
6338iop_class_check_parents_are_registered(const iop_struct_t *st,
6339 const iop_struct_t *master,
6340 const iop_env_t *env,
6341 qh_t(cptr) *registered,
6342 sb_t *err)
6343{
6344 uint32_t pos;
6345 const iop_struct_t *child = st;
6346
6347 pos = qh_put(cptr, registered, st, 0);
6348 if (pos & QHASH_COLLISION) {
6349 return 0;
6350 }
6351
6352 while ((st = st->class_attrs->parent)) {
6353 class_id_key_t key = {
6354 .master = master,
6355 .child_id = st->class_attrs->class_id,
6356 };
6357
6358 pos = qh_put(cptr, registered, st, 0);
6359 if (pos & QHASH_COLLISION) {
6360 return 0;
6361 }
6362
6363 if (qm_find_safe(iop_class_by_id, &env->classes_by_id, &key) < 0) {
6364 sb_setf(err, "class `%*pM` is not registered while its child "
6365 "class `%*pM` is", LSTR_FMT_ARG(st->fullname),
6366 LSTR_FMT_ARG(child->fullname));
6367 return -1;
6368 }
6369 }
6370
6371 return 0;
6372}
6373
6374int iop_check_registered_classes(const iop_env_t *env, sb_t *err)
6375{
6376 /* Check all the parent classes of the registered classes are also
6377 * registered. */
6378 t_scope;
6379 qh_t(cptr) registered;
6380
6381 t_qh_init(cptr, &registered,
6382 qm_len(iop_class_by_id, &env->classes_by_id));
6383
6384 qm_for_each_pos(iop_class_by_id, pos, &env->classes_by_id) {
6385 const iop_struct_t *st = env->classes_by_id.values[pos];
6386 const iop_struct_t *master = env->classes_by_id.keys[pos].master;
6387
6388 RETHROW(iop_class_check_parents_are_registered(st, master, env,
6389 &registered, err));
6390 }
6391
6392 return 0;
6393}
6394
6395static const char *iop_obj_type_to_str(const iop_obj_t *obj)
6396{
6397 switch (obj->type) {
6398 case IOP_OBJ_TYPE_ST: {
6399 const iop_struct_t *st = obj->desc.st;
6400
6401 if (st->is_union) {
6402 return "union";
6403 }
6404
6405 if (iop_struct_is_class(st)) {
6406 return "class";
6407 }
6408
6409 return "struct";
6410 }
6411
6412 case IOP_OBJ_TYPE_ENUM:
6413 return "enum";
6414
6415 case IOP_OBJ_TYPE_PKG:
6416 return "package";
6417 }
6418
6419 assert (false);
6420 return NULL;
6421}
6422
6423static inline bool iop_obj_equals(iop_obj_t obj1, iop_obj_t obj2)
6424{
6425 THROW_FALSE_IF(obj1.type != obj2.type);
6426 return obj1.desc.st == obj2.desc.st;
6427}
6428
6429static int
6430iop_register_obj(lstr_t fullname, iop_obj_t obj, unsigned flags,
6431 iop_env_t *env, sb_t *err)
6432{
6433 qv_t(iop_obj) *vec;
6434 uint32_t pos;
6435
6436 pos = qm_reserve(iop_objs, &env->iop_obj_by_fullname, &fullname, 0);
6437 if (pos & QHASH_COLLISION) {
6438 vec = &env->iop_obj_by_fullname.values[pos & ~QHASH_COLLISION];
6439 tab_for_each_entry(_obj, vec) {
6440 if (iop_obj_equals(_obj, obj)) {
6441 return 0;
6442 }
6443 }
6444
6445 if (!(flags & IOP_REGPKG_FROM_DSO)) {
6446 sb_setf(err, "%s '%*pM' was already registered",
6447 iop_obj_type_to_str(&obj), LSTR_FMT_ARG(fullname));
6448 return -1;
6449 }
6450 } else {
6451 vec = qv_init(&env->iop_obj_by_fullname.values[pos]);
6452 env->iop_obj_by_fullname.keys[pos] = lstr_dup(fullname);
6453 }
6454
6455 qv_append(vec, obj);
6456 return 1;
6457}
6458
6459#define IOP_OBJ_ST(_st) \
6460 (iop_obj_t){ .desc = { .st = _st }, .type = IOP_OBJ_TYPE_ST }
6461#define IOP_OBJ_ENUM(_en) \
6462 (iop_obj_t){ .desc = { .en = _en }, .type = IOP_OBJ_TYPE_ENUM }
6463#define IOP_OBJ_PKG(_pkg) \
6464 (iop_obj_t){ .desc = { .pkg = _pkg }, .type = IOP_OBJ_TYPE_PKG }
6465
6466static int
6467iop_register_struct(const iop_struct_t *st, unsigned flags,
6468 iop_env_t *env, sb_t *err)
6469{
6470 iop_obj_t obj = IOP_OBJ_ST(st);
6471
6472 if (iop_struct_is_class(st)) {
6473 const iop_struct_t *parent = st;
6474
6475 while (parent->class_attrs->parent) {
6476 parent = parent->class_attrs->parent;
6477 }
6478 obj.ancestor = parent;
6479
6480 RETHROW(iop_register_class(st, env, err));
6481 }
6482
6483 return iop_register_obj(st->fullname, obj, flags, env, err);
6484}
6485
6486static int
6487iop_register_enum(const iop_enum_t *en, unsigned flags, iop_env_t *env,
6488 sb_t *err)
6489{
6490 return iop_register_obj(en->fullname, IOP_OBJ_ENUM(en), flags, env, err);
6491}
6492
6493static int
6494iop_register_pkg(const iop_pkg_t *pkg, unsigned flags, iop_env_t *env,
6495 sb_t *err)
6496{
6497 return iop_register_obj(pkg->name, IOP_OBJ_PKG(pkg), flags, env, err);
6498}
6499
6500static int iop_register_package_env(const iop_pkg_t *pkg, iop_dso_t *dso,
6501 iop_env_t *env, unsigned flags, sb_t *err)
6502{
6503 int ret;
6504
6505 /* Register the package itself. */
6506 ret = RETHROW(iop_register_pkg(pkg, flags, env, err));
6507 if (ret == 0) {
6508 return 0;
6509 }
6510 if (dso) {
6511 qm_add(iop_dsos, &env->dsos_by_pkg, pkg, dso);
6512 }
6513
6514 /* Register its structs/union/classes. */
6515 for (const iop_struct_t *const *it = pkg->structs; *it; it++) {
6516 const iop_struct_t *desc = *it;
6517
6518 RETHROW(iop_register_struct(desc, flags, env, err));
6519 }
6520
6521 /* Register its enums. */
6522 for (const iop_enum_t *const *it = pkg->enums; *it; it++) {
6523 const iop_enum_t *desc = *it;
6524
6525 RETHROW(iop_register_enum(desc, flags, env, err));
6526 }
6527
6528 /* Register its dependencies. */
6529 for (const iop_pkg_t *const *it = pkg->deps; *it; it++) {
6530 const iop_pkg_t *dep = *it;
6531
6532 RETHROW(iop_register_package_env(dep, dso, env, flags, err));
6533 }
6534
6535 return 0;
6536}
6537
6538int iop_register_packages_env(const iop_pkg_t **pkgs, int len, iop_dso_t *dso,
6539 iop_env_t *env, unsigned flags, sb_t *err)
6540{
6541 if (dso) {
6542 assert (flags & IOP_REGPKG_FROM_DSO);
6543 } else {
6544 assert (!(flags & IOP_REGPKG_FROM_DSO));
6545 }
6546
6547 /* Register the packages. */
6548 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
6549 const iop_pkg_t *pkg = pkgs[i];
6550
6551 RETHROW(iop_register_package_env(pkg, dso, env, flags, err));
6552 }
6553
6554 return 0;
6555}
6556
6557void iop_register_packages(const iop_pkg_t **pkgs, int len, unsigned flags)
6558{
6559 SB_1k(err);
6560
6561 if (iop_register_packages_env(pkgs, len, NULL, &_G.env, flags, &err) < 0)
6562 {
6563 e_panic("%*pM", SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
6564 }
6565}

6567const iop_enum_t *iop_get_enum(lstr_t fullname)
6568{
6569 const iop_obj_t *obj = RETHROW_P(iop_get_obj(fullname));
6570
6571 THROW_NULL_IF(obj->type != IOP_OBJ_TYPE_ENUM);
6572
6573 return obj->desc.en;
6574}

6579}

6584}

6600
6601iop_dso_t *iop_dso_get_from_pkg(const iop_pkg_t *pkg)
6602{
6603 return qm_get_def_safe(iop_dsos, &_G.env.dsos_by_pkg, pkg, NULL);

6605
6606static void iop_unregister_class(const iop_struct_t *desc)
6607{
6608 class_id_key_t key = {
6609 .master = desc,
6610 .child_id = desc->class_attrs->class_id,
6611 };
6612
6613 while (key.master->class_attrs->parent) {
6614 key.master = key.master->class_attrs->parent;
6615 }
6616
6617 qm_del_key(iop_class_by_id, &_G.env.classes_by_id, &key);
6618}
6619
6620static int iop_unregister_obj(lstr_t fullname, iop_obj_t obj)
6621{
6622 int pos;
6623 qv_t(iop_obj) *vec;
6624
6625 pos = RETHROW(qm_find(iop_objs, &_G.env.iop_obj_by_fullname, &fullname));
6626 vec = &_G.env.iop_obj_by_fullname.values[pos];
6627 tab_for_each_pos(obj_pos, vec) {
6628 if (iop_obj_equals(vec->tab[obj_pos], obj)) {
6629 if (vec->len > 1) {
6630 qv_remove(vec, obj_pos);
6631 } else {
6632 qv_wipe(vec);
6633 lstr_wipe(&_G.env.iop_obj_by_fullname.keys[pos]);
6634 qm_del_at(iop_objs, &_G.env.iop_obj_by_fullname, pos);
6635 }
6636
6637 return 0;
6638 }
6639 }
6640
6641 return -1;
6642}
6643
6644static int iop_unregister_struct(const iop_struct_t *st)
6645{
6646 return iop_unregister_obj(st->fullname, IOP_OBJ_ST(st));
6647}
6648
6649static int iop_unregister_enum(const iop_enum_t *en)
6650{
6651 return iop_unregister_obj(en->fullname, IOP_OBJ_ENUM(en));
6652}
6653
6654void iop_unregister_packages(const iop_pkg_t **pkgs, int len)
6655{
6656 SB_1k(err);
6657
6658 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
6659 const iop_pkg_t *pkg = pkgs[i];
6660
6661 /* Unregister the package itself. */
6662 if (iop_unregister_obj(pkg->name, IOP_OBJ_PKG(pkg)) < 0) {
6663 continue;
6664 }
6665 qm_del_key(iop_dsos, &_G.env.dsos_by_pkg, pkg);
6666
6667 /* Unregister its classes. */
6668 for (const iop_struct_t *const *it = pkg->structs; *it; it++) {
6669 const iop_struct_t *desc = *it;
6670
6671 if (iop_struct_is_class(desc)) {
6672 iop_unregister_class(desc);
6673 }
6674
6675 iop_unregister_struct(desc);
6676 }
6677
6678 /* Unregister its enums. */
6679 for (const iop_enum_t *const *it = pkg->enums; *it; it++) {
6680 const iop_enum_t *desc = *it;
6681
6682 iop_unregister_enum(desc);
6683 }
6684 }
6685
6686 if (iop_check_registered_classes(&_G.env, &err) < 0) {
6687 e_panic("%*pM", SB_FMT_ARG(&err));
6688 }
6689}
6690
6691void iop_for_each_registered_pkgs(iop_for_each_pkg_b cb)
6692{
6693 qm_for_each_pos(iop_objs, pos, &_G.env.iop_obj_by_fullname) {
6694 tab_for_each_entry(obj, &_G.env.iop_obj_by_fullname.values[pos]) {
6695 if (obj.type == IOP_OBJ_TYPE_PKG) {
6696 cb(obj.desc.pkg);
6697 }
6698 }
6699 }
6700}
6701
6702/* }}} */
6703/* {{{ Enum printf formatter %*pE */
6704
6705static ssize_t
6706iop_enum_formatter(int modifier, const void *_ev, size_t flags,
6707 FILE *stream, char *buf, size_t buf_len)
6708{
6709 const struct iop_enum_value *ev = _ev;
6710 lstr_t s = iop_enum_to_str_desc(ev->desc, ev->v);
6711
6712 if (flags & IOP_ENUM_FMT_FULL) {
6713 if (!s.s) {
6714 return formatter_writef(stream, buf, buf_len, "<unknown>(%d)",
6715 ev->v);
6716 }
6717
6718 return formatter_writef(stream, buf, buf_len, "%*pM(%d)",
6719 LSTR_FMT_ARG(s), ev->v);
6720 }
6721
6722 if (!s.s) {
6723 return formatter_writef(stream, buf, buf_len, "%d", ev->v);
6724 }
6725
6726 return formatter_write(stream, buf, buf_len, s.s, s.len);
6727}
6728
6729/* }}} */
6730/* {{{ Union type formatter */
6731
6732static ssize_t
6733iop_union_type_formatter(int modifier, const void *_desc, size_t iop_tag,
6734 FILE *stream, char *buf, size_t buf_len)
6735{
6736 const iop_struct_t *desc = _desc;
6737 lstr_t type_s;
6738 int pos;
6739
6740 pos = iop_ranges_search(desc->ranges, desc->ranges_len, iop_tag);
6741 if (unlikely(pos < 0)) {
6742 return formatter_writef(stream, buf, buf_len, "<unknown>(%zd)",
6743 iop_tag);
6744 }
6745
6746 type_s = desc->fields[pos].name;
6747
6748 return formatter_write(stream, buf, buf_len, type_s.s, type_s.len);
6749}
6750
6751/* }}} */
6752/* {{{ Backward compatibility checks */
6753
6754typedef struct iop_compat_couple_t {
6755 const void *st1;
6756 const void *st2;
6757 unsigned flags;
6758 unsigned padding;
6759} iop_compat_couple_t;
6760
6761static uint32_t qhash_hash_compat_couple(const qhash_t *qh,
6762 const iop_compat_couple_t *ptr)
6763{
6764 return mem_hash32(ptr, sizeof(*ptr));
6765}
6766static bool qhash_compat_couple_equal(const qhash_t *qh,
6767 const iop_compat_couple_t *ptr1,
6768 const iop_compat_couple_t *ptr2)
6769{
6770 return memcmp(ptr1, ptr2, sizeof(*ptr1)) == 0;
6771}
6772
6773qh_kvec_t(compat_couple, iop_compat_couple_t,
6774 qhash_hash_compat_couple, qhash_compat_couple_equal);
6775
6776struct iop_compat_ctx_t {
6777 qh_t(compat_couple) seen_couples;
6778 qh_t(cptr) seen_opt_st;
6779 sb_t *err;
6780 sb_t err_ctx;
6781 qv_t(i32) err_ctx_offs;
6782 int indent_lvl;
6783};
6784
6785static iop_compat_ctx_t *iop_compat_ctx_init(iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
6786{
6787 p_clear(ctx, 1);
6788 qh_init(compat_couple, &ctx->seen_couples);
6789 qh_init(cptr, &ctx->seen_opt_st);
6790 sb_init(&ctx->err_ctx);
6791 qv_init(&ctx->err_ctx_offs);
6792 return ctx;
6793}
6794static void iop_compat_ctx_wipe(iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
6795{
6796 qh_wipe(compat_couple, &ctx->seen_couples);
6797 qh_wipe(cptr, &ctx->seen_opt_st);
6798 sb_wipe(&ctx->err_ctx);
6799 qv_wipe(&ctx->err_ctx_offs);
6800}
6801DO_NEW(iop_compat_ctx_t, iop_compat_ctx);
6802DO_DELETE(iop_compat_ctx_t, iop_compat_ctx);
6803
6804static void iop_compat_make_indent(sb_t *sb, int indent_lvl)
6805{
6806 for (int i = 0; i < indent_lvl; i++) {
6807 sb_adds(sb, " | ");
6808 }
6809}
6810
6811__attr_printf__(2, 3)
6812static void
6813iop_compat_push_err_ctx(iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx, const char *fmt, ...)
6814{
6815 va_list ap;
6816
6817 qv_append(&ctx->err_ctx_offs, ctx->err_ctx.len);
6818
6819 iop_compat_make_indent(&ctx->err_ctx, ctx->indent_lvl);
6820 va_start(ap, fmt);
6821 sb_addvf(&ctx->err_ctx, fmt, ap);
6822 va_end(ap);
6823 sb_addc(&ctx->err_ctx, '\n');
6824
6825 ctx->indent_lvl++;
6826}
6827
6828static void iop_compat_pop_err_ctx(iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
6829{
6830 ctx->indent_lvl--;
6831 assert (ctx->indent_lvl >= 0);
6832 if (ctx->err_ctx_offs.len > 0) {
6833 sb_clip(&ctx->err_ctx, *tab_last(&ctx->err_ctx_offs));
6834 qv_remove_last(&ctx->err_ctx_offs);
6835 }
6836}
6837
6838__attr_printf__(2, 3)
6839static void iop_compat_add_err(iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx, const char *fmt, ...)
6840{
6841 va_list ap;
6842
6843 if (ctx->err->len > 0) {
6844 sb_addc(ctx->err, '\n');
6845 }
6846
6847 sb_addsb(ctx->err, &ctx->err_ctx);
6848 sb_reset(&ctx->err_ctx);
6849 qv_clear(&ctx->err_ctx_offs);
6850
6851 iop_compat_make_indent(ctx->err, ctx->indent_lvl);
6852
6853 va_start(ap, fmt);
6854 sb_addvf(ctx->err, fmt, ap);
6855 va_end(ap);
6856}
6857
6858static int
6859__iop_struct_check_backward_compat(const iop_struct_t *st1,
6860 const iop_struct_t *st2,
6861 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx);
6862
6863/* Add compat couple into the hash table. A special handler is needed as flags
6864 * must be added individually. Flags that need to be checked are returned. */
6865static unsigned
6866iop_compat_mark_couple(const void *st1, const void *st2,
6867 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
6868{
6869 iop_compat_couple_t couple = {
6870 .st1 = st1,
6871 .st2 = st2,
6872 };
6873 unsigned chk_flags = flags;
6874
6875 for (unsigned i = 0; flags && i < bitsizeof(flags); i++) {
6876 if (!TST_BIT(&flags, i)) {
6877 continue;
6878 }
6879
6880 couple.flags = 1 << i;
6881 if (qh_add(compat_couple, &ctx->seen_couples, &couple) < 0) {
6882 /* Couple already checked with this flag. */
6883 RST_BIT(&chk_flags, i);
6884 }
6885 RST_BIT(&flags, i);
6886 }
6887
6888 return chk_flags;
6889}
6890
6891static int
6892__iop_enum_check_backward_compat(const iop_enum_t *en1,
6893 const iop_enum_t *en2,
6894 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
6895{
6896 int res = 0;
6897
6898 /* XXX: do not simply test en1 == en2 because it allows to easily write
6899 * "compatible" z-tests. */
6900
6901 if (!(flags = iop_compat_mark_couple(en1, en2, flags, ctx))) {
6902 /* No checks to be done. */
6903 return 0;
6904 }
6905
6906 if (!TST_BIT(&en1->flags, IOP_ENUM_STRICT)
6907 && TST_BIT(&en2->flags, IOP_ENUM_STRICT))
6908 {
6909 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "enum is strict and was not before");
6910 res = -1;
6911 }
6912
6913 for (int i = 0; i < en1->enum_len; i++) {
6914 int pos2_bin = -1;
6915 int pos2_json = -1;
6916
6917 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN) {
6918 pos2_bin = iop_ranges_search(en2->ranges, en2->ranges_len,
6919 en1->values[i]);
6920 if (pos2_bin < 0) {
6921 iop_compat_add_err(ctx,
6922 "numeric value %d does not exist anymore",
6923 en1->values[i]);
6924 res = -1;
6925 }
6926 }
6927
6928 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON) {
6929 pos2_json = iop_enum_pos_from_str(en2, en1->names[i].s,
6930 en1->names[i].len);
6931 if (pos2_json < 0) {
6932 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "value `%*pM` does not exist anymore",
6933 LSTR_FMT_ARG(en1->names[i]));
6934 res = -1;
6935 }
6936 }
6937
6938 if (pos2_bin >= 0 && pos2_json >= 0 && pos2_bin != pos2_json) {
6939 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "value `%*pM` (%d): name and value "
6940 "lookups mismatch: `%*pM` (%d) != `%*pM` (%d)",
6941 LSTR_FMT_ARG(en1->names[i]), en1->values[i],
6942 LSTR_FMT_ARG(en2->names[pos2_json]),
6943 en2->values[pos2_json],
6944 LSTR_FMT_ARG(en2->names[pos2_bin]),
6945 en2->values[pos2_bin]);
6946 res = -1;
6947 }
6948 }
6949
6950 return res;
6951}
6952
6953static void
6954backward_compat_build_tables(uint32_t table_bin[IOP_T_max + 1],
6955 uint32_t table_json[IOP_T_max + 1],
6956 uint32_t table_bin_r[IOP_T_max + 1])
6957{
6958 STATIC_ASSERT (IOP_T_max <= bitsizeof(uint32_t));
6959
6960 /* A type is always compatible with void and itself. */
6961 for (int i = 0; i <= IOP_T_max; i++) {
6962 table_bin[i] = TO_BIT(VOID) | 1U << i;
6963 }
6964
6965 /* Build authorized binary types transition table. */
6966 table_bin[IOP_T_U32] |= TO_BIT(U64) | TO_BIT(I64);
6967 table_bin[IOP_T_I32] |= TO_BIT(U64) | TO_BIT(I64);
6968 table_bin[IOP_T_U16] |= table_bin[IOP_T_U32] | table_bin[IOP_T_I32];
6969 table_bin[IOP_T_I16] |= table_bin[IOP_T_U32] | table_bin[IOP_T_I32];
6970 table_bin[IOP_T_U8] |= table_bin[IOP_T_U16] | table_bin[IOP_T_I16];
6971 table_bin[IOP_T_I8] |= table_bin[IOP_T_U16] | table_bin[IOP_T_I16];
6972 table_bin[IOP_T_BOOL] |= table_bin[IOP_T_U8] | table_bin[IOP_T_I8];
6973 table_bin[IOP_T_ENUM] |= table_bin[IOP_T_I32];
6974
6975 table_bin[IOP_T_STRING] |= TO_BIT(DATA) | TO_BIT(XML);
6976 table_bin[IOP_T_DATA] = table_bin[IOP_T_STRING];
6977 table_bin[IOP_T_XML] = table_bin[IOP_T_STRING];
6978
6979 /* Build authorized json types transition table. */
6980 p_copy(table_json, table_bin, IOP_T_max + 1);
6981 table_json[IOP_T_ENUM] = TO_BIT(ENUM) | TO_BIT(VOID);
6982 table_json[IOP_T_STRING] = TO_BIT(STRING) | TO_BIT(VOID);
6983 table_json[IOP_T_DATA] = TO_BIT(DATA) | TO_BIT(VOID);
6984 table_json[IOP_T_XML] = TO_BIT(XML) | TO_BIT(VOID);
6985
6986 /* build repeated table for binary format due to special array packing
6987 * (cf : IOP_REPEATED_OPTIMIZE_OK) */
6988 p_copy(table_bin_r, table_bin, IOP_T_max + 1);
6989 table_bin_r[IOP_T_U16] = TO_BIT(U16);
6990 table_bin_r[IOP_T_I16] = TO_BIT(I16);
6991 table_bin_r[IOP_T_U8] = TO_BIT(U8);
6992 table_bin_r[IOP_T_I8] = TO_BIT(I8);
6993 table_bin_r[IOP_T_BOOL] = TO_BIT(U8) | TO_BIT(I8) | TO_BIT(BOOL);
6994}
6995
6996static bool _iop_struct_is_optional(const iop_struct_t *st,
6997 bool forbid_abstract,
6998 bool check_parents,
6999 iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx);
7000
7001static int
7002iop_field_check_backward_compat(const iop_field_t *f1,
7003 const iop_field_t *f2,
7004 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7005{
7006 static int first_call = true;
7007 static uint32_t table_bin[IOP_T_max + 1];
7008 static uint32_t table_json[IOP_T_max + 1];
7009 static uint32_t table_bin_r[IOP_T_max + 1];
7010
7011 if (unlikely(first_call)) {
7012 first_call = false;
7013 backward_compat_build_tables(table_bin, table_json, table_bin_r);
7014 }
7015
7016 /* Check type transition. */
7017 if (f1->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED && f2->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED) {
7018 if ((flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN
7019 && !TST_BIT(&table_bin_r[f1->type], f2->type))
7020 || (flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON
7021 && !TST_BIT(&table_json[f1->type], f2->type)))
7022 {
7023 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "incompatible types");
7024 return -1;
7025 }
7026 } else {
7027 if ((flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN
7028 && !TST_BIT(&table_bin[f1->type], f2->type))
7029 || (flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON
7030 && !TST_BIT(&table_json[f1->type], f2->type)))
7031 {
7032 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "incompatible types");
7033 return -1;
7034 }
7035 }
7036
7037 /* Check repeated -> non-repeated: always forbidden
7038 * (except when replacing with non-repeated void)
7039 * (non-repeated -> repeated is always supported) */
7040 if (f1->repeat == IOP_R_REPEATED && f2->repeat != IOP_R_REPEATED
7041 && f2->type != IOP_T_VOID)
7042 {
7043 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "was repeated and is not anymore");
7044 return -1;
7045 }
7046
7047 /* Check non-required -> required:
7048 * forbidden iff it isn't an optional struct or void. */
7049 if ((f1->repeat == IOP_R_DEFVAL || f1->repeat == IOP_R_OPTIONAL)
7050 && f2->repeat == IOP_R_REQUIRED && f2->type != IOP_T_VOID
7051 && (f2->type != IOP_T_STRUCT
7052 || !_iop_struct_is_optional(f2->u1.st_desc, true, true, ctx)))
7053 {
7054 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "is required and was not before");
7055 return -1;
7056 }
7057
7058 /* Check backward compat of complex types. */
7059 switch (f2->type) {
7060 case IOP_T_UNION:
7061 case IOP_T_STRUCT:
7062 assert (f1->type == f2->type);
7063 return __iop_struct_check_backward_compat(f1->u1.st_desc,
7064 f2->u1.st_desc,
7065 flags, ctx);
7066
7067 case IOP_T_ENUM:
7068 assert (f1->type == f2->type);
7069 if (!f1->u1.en_desc || !f2->u1.en_desc) {
7070 /* This happens for SNMP traps using an enumeration... */
7071 return 0;
7072 }
7073 return __iop_enum_check_backward_compat(f1->u1.en_desc,
7074 f2->u1.en_desc,
7075 flags, ctx);
7076 case IOP_T_I8:
7077 case IOP_T_I16:
7078 case IOP_T_I32:
7079 case IOP_T_I64:
7080 case IOP_T_BOOL:
7081 case IOP_T_DOUBLE:
7082 case IOP_T_U8:
7083 case IOP_T_U16:
7084 case IOP_T_U32:
7085 case IOP_T_U64:
7086 case IOP_T_STRING:
7087 case IOP_T_DATA:
7088 case IOP_T_XML:
7089 case IOP_T_VOID:
7090 break;
7091 }
7092
7093 return 0;
7094}
7095
7096static const iop_struct_t *
7097get_parents_until_id(const iop_struct_t *st, const uint16_t *class_id,
7098 qv_t(iop_struct) *vec)
7099{
7100 while ((st = st->class_attrs->parent)) {
7101 if (class_id && st->class_attrs->class_id == *class_id) {
7102 break;
7103 }
7104 qv_append(vec, st);
7105 }
7106
7107 return st;
7108}
7109
7110static const iop_struct_t *
7111get_parents_until_name(const iop_struct_t *st, const lstr_t *name,
7112 qv_t(iop_struct) *vec)
7113{
7114 while ((st = st->class_attrs->parent)) {
7115 if (name && lstr_equal(st->fullname, *name)) {
7116 break;
7117 }
7118 qv_append(vec, st);
7119 }
7120
7121 return st;
7122}
7123
7124static bool are_all_parents_empty(const iop_struct_t *st)
7125{
7126 while ((st = st->class_attrs->parent)) {
7127 if (st->fields_len) {
7128 return false;
7129 }
7130 }
7131
7132 return true;
7133}
7134
7135/* Check that none of the classes added as parents contain a required
7136 * field. */
7137static int
7138check_parent_required_fields(const qv_t(iop_struct) *parents,
7139 iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7140{
7141 tab_for_each_entry(parent, parents) {
7142 for (int i = 0; i < parent->fields_len; i++) {
7143 const iop_field_t *f = &parent->fields[i];
7144
7145 if (f->repeat == IOP_R_REQUIRED
7146 && (f->type != IOP_T_STRUCT
7147 || !_iop_struct_is_optional(f->u1.st_desc, true, true, ctx)))
7148 {
7149 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "class `%*pM` was added in the "
7150 "parents with a required field `%*pM`",
7151 LSTR_FMT_ARG(parent->fullname),
7152 LSTR_FMT_ARG(f->name));
7153 return -1;
7154 }
7155 }
7156 }
7157 return 0;
7158}
7159
7160static int
7161check_class_parent(const iop_struct_t *st1,
7162 const iop_struct_t *parent,
7163 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7164{
7165 int res = 0;
7166
7167 iop_compat_push_err_ctx(ctx, "parent `%*pM`:",
7168 LSTR_FMT_ARG(parent->fullname));
7169 res = __iop_struct_check_backward_compat(st1->class_attrs->parent,
7170 parent, flags, ctx);
7171 iop_compat_pop_err_ctx(ctx);
7172
7173 return res;
7174}
7175
7176static int
7177check_parent_classes(const iop_struct_t *st1, const iop_struct_t *st2,
7178 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7179{
7180 const iop_struct_t *st2_parent_bin = NULL;
7181 const iop_struct_t *st2_parent_json = NULL;
7182 qv_t(iop_struct) parents;
7183 int res = 0;
7184
7185 if (!st1->class_attrs->parent && !st2->class_attrs->parent) {
7186 return 0;
7187 }
7188
7189 qv_init(&parents);
7190
7191 /* Get the classes added in the parents between 'st2' and 'st1'. */
7192 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN) {
7193 const uint16_t *class_id = NULL;
7194
7195 if (st1->class_attrs->parent) {
7196 class_id = &st1->class_attrs->parent->class_attrs->class_id;
7197 }
7198 st2_parent_bin = get_parents_until_id(st2, class_id, &parents);
7199 if (class_id && !st2_parent_bin) {
7200 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "cannot find class with id %d in the "
7201 "parents of `%*pM`",
7202 *class_id, LSTR_FMT_ARG(st2->fullname));
7203 res = -1;
7204 }
7205
7206 if (res >= 0 && check_parent_required_fields(&parents, ctx) < 0) {
7207 res = -1;
7208 }
7209
7210 qv_clear(&parents);
7211 }
7212
7213 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON) {
7214 const lstr_t *class_name = NULL;
7215
7216 if (st1->class_attrs->parent) {
7217 class_name = &st1->class_attrs->parent->fullname;
7218 }
7219 st2_parent_json = get_parents_until_name(st2, class_name, &parents);
7220 if (class_name && !st2_parent_json
7221 && (!are_all_parents_empty(st1) || !are_all_parents_empty(st2)))
7222 {
7223 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "cannot find class `%*pM` in the parents "
7224 "of `%*pM`", LSTR_FMT_ARG(*class_name),
7225 LSTR_FMT_ARG(st2->fullname));
7226 res = -1;
7227 }
7228
7229 if (res >= 0 && check_parent_required_fields(&parents, ctx) < 0) {
7230 res = -1;
7231 }
7232 }
7233
7234 /* Check upper level. */
7235 if ((st2_parent_bin || st2_parent_json)
7236 && st1->class_attrs->parent)
7237 {
7238 if (st2_parent_bin == st2_parent_json) {
7239 if (check_class_parent(st1, st2_parent_bin, flags, ctx) < 0) {
7240 res = -1;
7241 }
7242 } else {
7243 if (st2_parent_bin
7244 && check_class_parent(st1, st2_parent_bin,
7245 IOP_COMPAT_BIN, ctx) < 0)
7246 {
7247 res = -1;
7248 }
7249
7250 if (st2_parent_json
7251 && check_class_parent(st1, st2_parent_json,
7252 IOP_COMPAT_JSON, ctx) < 0)
7253 {
7254 res = -1;
7255 }
7256 }
7257 }
7258
7259 qv_wipe(&parents);
7260 return res;
7261}
7262
7263bool _iop_struct_is_optional(const iop_struct_t *st, bool forbid_abstract,
7264 bool check_parents, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7265{
7266 if (forbid_abstract && iop_struct_is_class(st)
7267 && st->class_attrs->is_abstract)
7268 {
7269 return false;
7270 }
7271
7272 if (qh_find(cptr, &ctx->seen_opt_st, st) >= 0) {
7273 return true;
7274 }
7275
7276 for (int i = 0; i < st->fields_len; i++) {
7277 const iop_field_t *f = &st->fields[i];
7278
7279 if (f->repeat != IOP_R_REQUIRED || f->type == IOP_T_VOID) {
7280 continue;
7281 }
7282 if (f->type != IOP_T_STRUCT
7283 || !_iop_struct_is_optional(f->u1.st_desc, true, true, ctx))
7284 {
7285 return false;
7286 }
7287 }
7288
7289 if (check_parents && iop_struct_is_class(st) && st->class_attrs->parent
7290 && !_iop_struct_is_optional(st->class_attrs->parent, false, true, ctx))
7291 {
7292 return false;
7293 }
7294
7295 qh_add(cptr, &ctx->seen_opt_st, st);
7296 return true;
7297}
7298
7299bool iop_struct_is_optional(const iop_struct_t *st, bool check_parents)
7300{
7301 iop_compat_ctx_t ctx;
7302 int ret;
7303
7304 iop_compat_ctx_init(&ctx);
7305 ret = _iop_struct_is_optional(st, false, check_parents, &ctx);
7306 iop_compat_ctx_wipe(&ctx);
7307 return ret;
7308}
7309
7310static int
7311__backward_compat_check_new_field(const iop_struct_t *st1,
7312 const iop_field_t *f1,
7313 const iop_field_t *f2,
7314 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7315{
7316 if (f1) {
7317 int res = 0;
7318 SB(name_fmt, 128);
7319
7320 if (!lstr_equal(f1->name, f2->name)) {
7321 sb_addf(&name_fmt, "`%*pM` -> `%*pM`", LSTR_FMT_ARG(f1->name),
7322 LSTR_FMT_ARG(f2->name));
7323 } else
7324 if (f1->tag != f2->tag) {
7325 sb_addf(&name_fmt, "`%*pM` %hu -> %hu", LSTR_FMT_ARG(f2->name),
7326 f1->tag, f2->tag);
7327 } else {
7328 sb_addf(&name_fmt, "`%*pM`", LSTR_FMT_ARG(f2->name));
7329 }
7330
7331 iop_compat_push_err_ctx(ctx, "field %*pM:", SB_FMT_ARG(&name_fmt));
7332
7333 if (iop_field_check_backward_compat(f1, f2, flags, ctx) < 0) {
7334 res = -1;
7335 }
7336 iop_compat_pop_err_ctx(ctx);
7337 return res;
7338 }
7339
7340 if (f2->type == IOP_T_VOID) {
7341 return 0;
7342 }
7343
7344 if (st1->is_union || f2->repeat != IOP_R_REQUIRED) {
7345 return 0;
7346 }
7347
7348 if (f2->type == IOP_T_STRUCT
7349 && _iop_struct_is_optional(f2->u1.st_desc, true, true, ctx))
7350 {
7351 return 0;
7352 }
7353
7354 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "new field `%*pM` must not be required",
7355 LSTR_FMT_ARG(f2->name));
7356
7357 return -1;
7358}
7359
7360static unsigned
7361iop_generic_compat_ignored(unsigned flags,
7362 int (^get_gen_attr)(lstr_t, iop_value_t *))
7363{
7364 iop_value_t val;
7365
7366 if (get_gen_attr(LSTR("compat:ignore"), &val) >= 0 && val.b) {
7367 return 0;
7368 }
7369 if (get_gen_attr(LSTR("compat:ignoreJson"), &val) >= 0 && val.b) {
7370 flags &= ~IOP_COMPAT_JSON;
7371 }
7372 if (get_gen_attr(LSTR("compat:ignoreBin"), &val) >= 0 && val.b) {
7373 flags &= ~IOP_COMPAT_BIN;
7374 }
7375
7376 return flags;
7377}
7378
7379static unsigned
7380iop_struct_compat_ignored(const iop_struct_t *new_st, unsigned flags)
7381{
7382 return iop_generic_compat_ignored(flags,
7383 ^int (lstr_t attr, iop_value_t *val) {
7384 return iop_struct_get_gen_attr(new_st, attr, IOP_T_BOOL, NULL, val);
7385 });
7386}
7387
7388static unsigned iop_rpc_compat_ignored(const iop_iface_t *iface,
7389 const iop_rpc_t *rpc, unsigned flags)
7390{
7391 return iop_generic_compat_ignored(flags,
7392 ^int (lstr_t attr, iop_value_t *val) {
7393 return iop_rpc_get_gen_attr(iface, rpc, attr, IOP_T_BOOL, NULL, val);
7394 });
7395}
7396
7397static unsigned
7398iop_iface_compat_ignored(const iop_iface_t *iface, unsigned flags)
7399{
7400 return iop_generic_compat_ignored(flags,
7401 ^int (lstr_t attr, iop_value_t *val) {
7402 return iop_iface_get_gen_attr(iface, attr, IOP_T_BOOL, NULL, val);
7403 });
7404}
7405
7406static int
7407__iop_struct_check_backward_compat(const iop_struct_t *st1,
7408 const iop_struct_t *st2,
7409 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7410{
7411 int res = 0;
7412
7413 /* XXX: do not simply test st1 == st2 because it allows to easily write
7414 * "compatible" z-tests. */
7415
7416 if (!(flags = iop_compat_mark_couple(st1, st2, flags, ctx))) {
7417 /* No checks to be done. */
7418 return 0;
7419 }
7420
7421 /* Check types of the objects. */
7422 if (st1->is_union && !st2->is_union) {
7423 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "was a union and is now a %s",
7424 iop_struct_is_class(st2) ? "class" : "struct");
7425 return -1;
7426 }
7427 if (!st1->is_union && st2->is_union) {
7428 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "was a %s and is now a union",
7429 iop_struct_is_class(st1) ? "class" : "struct");
7430 return -1;
7431 }
7432
7433 if (iop_struct_is_class(st1) && !iop_struct_is_class(st2)) {
7434 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "was a class and is now a struct");
7435 res = -1;
7436 }
7437 if (!iop_struct_is_class(st1) && iop_struct_is_class(st2)) {
7438 if (st2->class_attrs->is_abstract) {
7439 iop_compat_add_err(ctx,
7440 "was a struct and is now an abstract class");
7441 res = -1;
7442 } else
7443 if (st2->class_attrs->parent) {
7444 /* TODO: this is theoretically possible for JSON, but the checks
7445 * on all the fields are missing and should be added here. */
7446 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "was a struct and is now a child class");
7447 res = -1;
7448 }
7449 }
7450
7451 if (iop_struct_is_class(st1) && iop_struct_is_class(st2)) {
7452 if (!st1->class_attrs->is_abstract && st2->class_attrs->is_abstract) {
7453 iop_compat_add_err(ctx,
7454 "is an abstract class but was not abstract");
7455 res = -1;
7456 }
7457 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN
7458 && st1->class_attrs->class_id != st2->class_attrs->class_id)
7459 {
7460 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "class id changed (%u != %u)",
7461 st1->class_attrs->class_id,
7462 st2->class_attrs->class_id);
7463 res = -1;
7464 }
7465 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON
7466 && !lstr_equal(st1->fullname, st2->fullname))
7467 {
7468 iop_compat_add_err(ctx,
7469 "class fullname changed (`%*pM` != `%*pM`)",
7470 LSTR_FMT_ARG(st1->fullname),
7471 LSTR_FMT_ARG(st2->fullname));
7472 res = -1;
7473 }
7474 }
7475
7476 /* Check fields of st2. */
7477 for (int i = 0; i < st2->fields_len; i++) {
7478 const iop_field_t *f2 = &st2->fields[i];
7479 const iop_field_t *f1_name;
7480 const iop_field_t *f1_tag = NULL;
7481 bool got_err = false;
7482 int pos;
7483
7484 f1_name = __iop_field_find_by_name(st1, f2->name);
7485 pos = iop_ranges_search(st1->ranges, st1->ranges_len, f2->tag);
7486 if (pos >= 0) {
7487 f1_tag = &st1->fields[pos];
7488 }
7489
7490#define CHECK_NEW_FIELD(f1, flags) \
7491 do { \
7492 if (__backward_compat_check_new_field(st1, f1, f2, flags, \
7493 ctx) < 0) \
7494 { \
7495 got_err = true; \
7496 res = -1; \
7497 } \
7498 } while (0)
7499
7500 if (flags == IOP_COMPAT_JSON) {
7501 CHECK_NEW_FIELD(f1_name, IOP_COMPAT_JSON);
7502 } else
7503 if (flags == IOP_COMPAT_BIN) {
7504 CHECK_NEW_FIELD(f1_tag, IOP_COMPAT_BIN);
7505 } else {
7506 assert (flags == IOP_COMPAT_ALL);
7507 if (f1_name && f1_tag) {
7508 if (f1_name == f1_tag) {
7509 CHECK_NEW_FIELD(f1_name, IOP_COMPAT_ALL);
7510 } else {
7511 iop_compat_add_err(ctx,
7512 "field `%*pM` (%d): name and tag lookups mismatch: "
7513 "`%*pM` (%d) != `%*pM` (%d)",
7514 LSTR_FMT_ARG(f2->name), f2->tag,
7515 LSTR_FMT_ARG(f1_name->name), f1_name->tag,
7516 LSTR_FMT_ARG(f1_tag->name), f1_tag->tag);
7517 res = -1;
7518 }
7519 } else {
7520 CHECK_NEW_FIELD(f1_name, IOP_COMPAT_JSON);
7521 if (!got_err) {
7522 CHECK_NEW_FIELD(f1_tag, IOP_COMPAT_BIN);
7523 }
7524 }
7525 }
7526 }
7527#undef CHECK_NEW_FIELD
7528
7529 /* Check that no field disappeared for json backward compat and union
7530 * case. */
7531 if (st1->is_union || flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON) {
7532 for (int i = 0; i < st1->fields_len; i++) {
7533 const iop_field_t *f1 = &st1->fields[i];
7534
7535 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON
7536 && !__iop_field_find_by_name(st2, f1->name))
7537 {
7538 iop_compat_add_err(ctx,
7539 "field `%*pM` does not exist anymore",
7540 LSTR_FMT_ARG(f1->name));
7541 res = -1;
7542 } else
7543 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN
7544 && iop_ranges_search(st2->ranges, st2->ranges_len, f1->tag) < 0)
7545 {
7546 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "field with tag %d (`%*pM`) does "
7547 "not exist anymore", f1->tag,
7548 LSTR_FMT_ARG(f1->name));
7549 res = -1;
7550 }
7551 }
7552 }
7553
7554 /* Specific class checks. */
7555 if (iop_struct_is_class(st1) && iop_struct_is_class(st2)
7556 && check_parent_classes(st1, st2, flags, ctx) < 0)
7557 {
7558 res = -1;
7559 }
7560
7561 return res;
7562}
7563
7564int iop_struct_check_backward_compat(const iop_struct_t *st1,
7565 const iop_struct_t *st2,
7566 unsigned flags, sb_t *err)
7567{
7568 int res;
7569 iop_compat_ctx_t ctx;
7570
7571 assert (flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN || flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON);
7572
7573 flags = iop_struct_compat_ignored(st2, flags);
7574 if (!flags) {
7575 return 0;
7576 }
7577
7578 iop_compat_ctx_init(&ctx);
7579 ctx.err = err;
7580
7581 res = __iop_struct_check_backward_compat(st1, st2, flags, &ctx);
7582
7583 iop_compat_ctx_wipe(&ctx);
7584 return res;
7585}
7586
7587static int
7588__iop_rpc_check_backward_compat(const iop_rpc_t *rpc1,
7589 const iop_rpc_t *rpc2,
7590 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7591{
7592 int res = 0;
7593
7594#define CHECK_RPC(_what) \
7595 do { \
7596 iop_compat_push_err_ctx(ctx, "RPC `%*pM` " TOSTR(_what) ":", \
7597 LSTR_FMT_ARG(rpc1->name)); \
7598 if (__iop_struct_check_backward_compat(rpc1->_what, rpc2->_what, \
7599 flags, ctx) < 0) \
7600 { \
7601 res = -1; \
7602 } \
7603 iop_compat_pop_err_ctx(ctx); \
7604 } while (0)
7605
7606 CHECK_RPC(args);
7607
7608 if (rpc1->async && !rpc2->async) {
7609 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "RPC `%*pM` was async and is not anymore",
7610 LSTR_FMT_ARG(rpc1->name));
7611 return -1;
7612 }
7613 if (!rpc1->async && rpc2->async) {
7614 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "RPC `%*pM` is async but was not before",
7615 LSTR_FMT_ARG(rpc1->name));
7616 return -1;
7617 }
7618
7619 CHECK_RPC(result);
7620 CHECK_RPC(exn);
7621#undef CHECK_RPC
7622
7623 return res;
7624}
7625
7626static const iop_rpc_t *
7627__iop_iface_get_rpc_by_name(const iop_iface_t *iface, lstr_t name)
7628{
7629 for (int i = 0; i < iface->funs_len; i++) {
7630 if (lstr_equal(iface->funs[i].name, name)) {
7631 return &iface->funs[i];
7632 }
7633 }
7634
7635 return NULL;
7636}
7637
7638static int
7639__iop_iface_check_backward_compat(const iop_iface_t *if1,
7640 const iop_iface_t *if2,
7641 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7642{
7643 int res = 0;
7644
7645 /* XXX: do not simply test if1 == if2 because it allows to easily write
7646 * "compatible" z-tests. */
7647
7648 /* Skip SNMP interfaces: they do not have the same backward compatibility
7649 * rules as the standard interfaces, and it would be quite useless for us.
7650 */
7651 if (TST_BIT(&if1->flags, IOP_IFACE_IS_SNMP_IFACE)
7652 && TST_BIT(&if2->flags, IOP_IFACE_IS_SNMP_IFACE))
7653 {
7654 return 0;
7655 }
7656
7657 for (int i = 0; i < if1->funs_len; i++) {
7658 const iop_rpc_t *fun1 = &if1->funs[i];
7659 const iop_rpc_t *fun2;
7660
7661 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON) {
7662 if ((fun2 = __iop_iface_get_rpc_by_name(if2, fun1->name))) {
7663 unsigned rpc_flags;
7664
7665 if ((rpc_flags = iop_rpc_compat_ignored(if2, fun2, flags))
7666 && __iop_rpc_check_backward_compat(fun1, fun2,
7667 rpc_flags, ctx) < 0)
7668 {
7669 res = -1;
7670 continue;
7671 }
7672 } else {
7673 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "RPC `%*pM` does not exist anymore",
7674 LSTR_FMT_ARG(fun1->name));
7675 res = -1;
7676 continue;
7677 }
7678 }
7679
7680 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN) {
7681 if ((fun2 = iop_iface_find_rpc(if2, fun1->tag))) {
7682 unsigned rpc_flags;
7683
7684 if ((rpc_flags = iop_rpc_compat_ignored(if2, fun2, flags))
7685 && __iop_rpc_check_backward_compat(fun1, fun2,
7686 rpc_flags, ctx) < 0)
7687 {
7688 res = -1;
7689 }
7690 } else {
7691 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "RPC with tag %d (`%*pM`) does not "
7692 "exist anymore",
7693 fun1->tag, LSTR_FMT_ARG(fun1->name));
7694 res = -1;
7695 }
7696 }
7697 }
7698
7699 return res;
7700}
7701
7702static const iop_iface_alias_t *
7703__iop_mod_get_iface_by_name(const iop_mod_t *mod, lstr_t name)
7704{
7705 for (int i = 0; i < mod->ifaces_len; i++) {
7706 if (lstr_equal(mod->ifaces[i].name, name)) {
7707 return &mod->ifaces[i];
7708 }
7709 }
7710
7711 return NULL;
7712}
7713
7714static int
7715__iop_mod_check_backward_compat(const iop_mod_t *mod1,
7716 const iop_mod_t *mod2,
7717 unsigned flags, iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx)
7718{
7719 int res = 0;
7720
7721 /* XXX: do not simply test mod1 == mod2 because it allows to easily write
7722 * "compatible" z-tests. */
7723
7724 /* We just perform naive tests here (we check that the interfaces are not
7725 * renamed or re-tagged without checking their compatibility). The
7726 * interfaces themselves are tested before anyway.
7727 */
7728 for (int i = 0; i < mod1->ifaces_len; i++) {
7729 const iop_iface_alias_t *if1 = &mod1->ifaces[i];
7730
7731 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON) {
7732 if (!__iop_mod_get_iface_by_name(mod2, if1->name)) {
7733 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "interface `%*pM` does not exist "
7734 "anymore", LSTR_FMT_ARG(if1->name));
7735 res = -1;
7736 }
7737 }
7738
7739 if (flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN) {
7740 if (!iop_mod_find_iface(mod2, if1->tag)) {
7741 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "interface with tag %d (`%*pM`) does "
7742 "not exist anymore",
7743 if1->tag, LSTR_FMT_ARG(if1->name));
7744 res = -1;
7745 }
7746 }
7747 }
7748
7749 return res;
7750}
7751
7752static lstr_t iop_get_name_from_fullname(lstr_t fullname)
7753{
7754 pstream_t ps = ps_initlstr(&fullname);
7755 pstream_t elem;
7756
7757 while (ps_get_ps_chr_and_skip(&ps, '.', &elem) >= 0);
7758
7759 return LSTR_PS_V(&ps);
7760}
7761
7762#define BUILD_GET_BY_NAME(_fun, _type, _vec) \
7763const _type *_fun(const iop_pkg_t *pkg, lstr_t name) \
7764{ \
7765 for (const _type *const *it = pkg->_vec; *it; it++) { \
7766 const _type *obj = *it; \
7767 \
7768 if (lstr_equal(iop_get_name_from_fullname(obj->fullname), name)) { \
7769 return obj; \
7770 } \
7771 } \
7772 return NULL; \
7773}
7774
7775BUILD_GET_BY_NAME(iop_pkg_get_struct_by_name, iop_struct_t, structs)
7776static BUILD_GET_BY_NAME(iop_pkg_get_iface_by_name, iop_iface_t, ifaces)
7777static BUILD_GET_BY_NAME(iop_pkg_get_mod_by_name, iop_mod_t, mods)
7778
7779#undef BUILD_GET_BY_NAME
7780
7781int iop_pkg_check_backward_compat_ctx(const iop_pkg_t *pkg1,
7782 const iop_pkg_t *pkg2,
7783 iop_compat_ctx_t *ctx,
7784 unsigned flags, sb_t *err)
7785{
7786 int res = 0;
7787
7788 assert (flags & IOP_COMPAT_BIN || flags & IOP_COMPAT_JSON);
7789
7790 ctx->err = err;
7791
7792 iop_compat_push_err_ctx(ctx, "pkg `%*pM`:", LSTR_FMT_ARG(pkg2->name));
7793
7794 /* Check structs. */
7795 for (const iop_struct_t *const *it = pkg1->structs; *it; it++) {
7796 const iop_struct_t *st1 = *it;
7797 const iop_struct_t *st2;
7798 lstr_t name = iop_get_name_from_fullname(st1->fullname);
7799 const char *what;
7800 unsigned st_flags;
7801
7802 if (st1->is_union) {
7803 what = "union";
7804 } else
7805 if (iop_struct_is_class(st1)) {
7806 what = "class";
7807 } else {
7808 what = "struct";
7809 }
7810
7811 if (!(st2 = iop_pkg_get_struct_by_name(pkg2, name))) {
7812 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "%s `%*pM` does not exist anymore",
7813 what, LSTR_FMT_ARG(st1->fullname));
7814 res = -1;
7815 continue;
7816 }
7817
7818 iop_compat_push_err_ctx(ctx, "%s `%*pM`:",
7819 what, LSTR_FMT_ARG(st1->fullname));
7820 if ((st_flags = iop_struct_compat_ignored(st2, flags))
7821 && __iop_struct_check_backward_compat(st1, st2, st_flags, ctx) < 0)
7822 {
7823 res = -1;
7824 }
7825 iop_compat_pop_err_ctx(ctx);
7826 }
7827
7828 /* Check interfaces. */
7829 for (const iop_iface_t *const *it = pkg1->ifaces; *it; it++) {
7830 const iop_iface_t *if1 = *it;
7831 const iop_iface_t *if2;
7832 lstr_t name = iop_get_name_from_fullname(if1->fullname);
7833 unsigned if_flags;
7834
7835 if (!(if2 = iop_pkg_get_iface_by_name(pkg2, name))) {
7836 iop_compat_add_err(ctx,
7837 "interface `%*pM` does not exist anymore",
7838 LSTR_FMT_ARG(if1->fullname));
7839 res = -1;
7840 continue;
7841 }
7842
7843 iop_compat_push_err_ctx(ctx, "interface `%*pM`:",
7844 LSTR_FMT_ARG(if1->fullname));
7845 if ((if_flags = iop_iface_compat_ignored(if2, flags))
7846 && __iop_iface_check_backward_compat(if1, if2, if_flags, ctx) < 0)
7847 {
7848 res = -1;
7849 }
7850 iop_compat_pop_err_ctx(ctx);
7851 }
7852
7853 /* Check modules. */
7854 for (const iop_mod_t *const *it = pkg1->mods; *it; it++) {
7855 const iop_mod_t *mod1 = *it;
7856 const iop_mod_t *mod2;
7857 lstr_t name = iop_get_name_from_fullname(mod1->fullname);
7858
7859 if (!(mod2 = iop_pkg_get_mod_by_name(pkg2, name))) {
7860 iop_compat_add_err(ctx, "module `%*pM` does not exist anymore",
7861 LSTR_FMT_ARG(mod1->fullname));
7862 res = -1;
7863 continue;
7864 }
7865
7866 iop_compat_push_err_ctx(ctx, "module `%*pM`:",
7867 LSTR_FMT_ARG(mod1->fullname));
7868 if (__iop_mod_check_backward_compat(mod1, mod2, flags, ctx) < 0) {
7869 res = -1;
7870 }
7871 iop_compat_pop_err_ctx(ctx);
7872 }
7873
7874 iop_compat_pop_err_ctx(ctx);
7875
7876 return res;
7877}
7878
7879int iop_pkg_check_backward_compat(const iop_pkg_t *pkg1,
7880 const iop_pkg_t *pkg2,
7881 unsigned flags, sb_t *err)
7882{
7883 int res;
7884 iop_compat_ctx_t ctx;
7885
7886 iop_compat_ctx_init(&ctx);
7887
7888 res = iop_pkg_check_backward_compat_ctx(pkg1, pkg2, &ctx, flags, err);
7889
7890 iop_compat_ctx_wipe(&ctx);
7891
7892 return res;
7893}
7894
7895/* }}} */
7896
7897static int iop_initialize(void *arg)
7898{
7899 iop_env_init(&_G.env);
7900 iprintf_register_formatter('E', &iop_enum_formatter);
7901 iprintf_register_formatter('U', &iop_union_type_formatter);
7902 iop_dso_initialize();
7903 return 0;
7904}
7905
7906static int iop_shutdown(void)
7907{
7908 iop_dso_shutdown();
7909 iop_env_wipe(&_G.env);
7910 return 0;
7911}
7912
7913module_t *iop_module_g;
7914
7915_MODULE_ADD_DECLS(iop);
7916
7917void iop_module_register(void)
7918{
7919 if (!iop_module_g) {
7920 iop_module_g = module_implement(MODULE(iop), &iop_initialize,
7921 &iop_shutdown, NULL);
7922 }
7923}
